SUMMARY: Vehicle 1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection going straight; V2 entered the intersection turning left. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 departed the roadway on the north-west corner and the front of V1 contacted a traffic signal control box.

V1 was traveling south on a 4 lane two way roadway attempting to maneuver through a roundabout. The front of V1 made contact with a water cap, then continued through the center of the roundabout, striking landscaping rocks with the left side. V1 then contacted a breakaway pole with the right side. V1 continued south before coming to rest on the center median.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four-lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic light. V2 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway approaching the intersection. The front of V1 struck the right side of V2. After initial impact V2 departed the roadway on the southwest corner where the front plane struck a utility pole.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway approaching a stop sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1, after impact V1 travelled off the roadway and the front struck two fence poles.

Vehicle #1 was traveling eastbound crossing thru the intersection of a seven lane median divided roadway. Vehicle #1 entered into the travel lanes of Vehicle #2, which was traveling northbound. The frontal plane of Vehicle #1 contact the left side plane of Vehicle #2. After contact both vehicles left the roadway and came to rest on the grass shoulder area of the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northbound making a left turn within the intersection, while Vehicle #2 was traveling eastbound entering the intersection. Vehicle #1's frontal plane contacted the right side plane of Vehicle #2. Both Vehicles #1 and #2 after contact, crossed over westbound traffic lanes and came to rest on the shoulder of the roadway. Vehicle #3 was traveling westbound within the intersection and vehicle's windshield was contacted by debris from Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 impact.
V1 was exiting a parking lot, making a left turn. V2 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane roadway. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.
V1 was traveling southbound on a divided, four-lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck a tree.

V1 was traveling east in the inside lane on a four lane roadway. V2 was traveling east in front of V1. The front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2. After initial impact with V1, V2 departed the left lane line and onto oncoming traffic where the front plane of V2 contacted the front plane of V3.

V2 was traveling east bound on a two lane non divided bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the left. V1 was entering the same roadway, turning left from a private drive. V1 frontal plane impacted V2 frontal plane, causing V1 to rotate clockwise. V2 came to final rest off the north side of the roadway. V1 came to final rest off  the south side of the roadway.

V1 was south bound on a 2 lane roadway. The roadway had a curve to the right. V1 left the roadway to the left, where it traveled approximately 135 meters parallel with the roadway. V1 began to yaw clockwise then rolled, left side leading, 5 quarter turns before the vehicle came to final rest on its left side.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southbound on a two lane roadway while Vehicle #2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway. Vehicle #2's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #1's right side plane.

Vehicles #1, #2, #3 were all traveling southbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V2 and V3 slowed for debris in the roadway.  Vehicle #1's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #2's rear plane. Vehicle #2's frontal plane then contacted Vehicle #3's rear plane.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, through a 4 leg intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway through the same intersection. The front plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1. V1 went off the south west side of the intersection striking a stop sign. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing south. V2 came to final rest near the point of impact facing north east.

V1 was traveling south east in the #2 lane of a 2 lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the left where the front left tire impacted the center median curb. V1 returned to the roadway from the left and then departed the roadway again to the right. The front right tire impacted a curb. V1 continued over the sidewalk where the front of V1 impacted a wooden post holding a large electrical box which fell on the hood of V1. V1 continued forward where the right side of V1 impacted a barbed wire fence post. V1 rotated clockwise before coming to rest.

V1 was westbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. A deer entered the path of V1 causing V1 to depart its travel lane to the left then the left side of the roadway. V1 then traveled down an embankment impacting three trees (event 1-3) with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 continued down the embankment striking a tree with the left side A pillar causing damage to the occupant compartment (event 4). V1 then impacted two more trees (event 5 & 6) before coming to final rest at the final point of impact facing southwest.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane 1 on a two lane roadway. The front of V1 contacted an animal.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted a deer.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound in lane two approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north bound in lane three attempting to turn west bound at the intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north bound. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and contacted the front bumper on an embankment.

V1 was passing through an intersection going northwest on a two-way, two-lane road while ascending a long gradual incline.  V2 was traveling northeast on a two-way, two-lane road passing through the same intersection.  The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 then initiated into a two quarter, left-leading roll landing on its roof. The front of V2 then impacted a guardrail face while sliding on its roof.

Vehicle 1 was traveling on a two-lane two-way not physically divided roadway in the number 1 lane negotiating a curve to the left. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway on the right side in the middle of the turn. The front of V1 contacted a sign and continued into a tree located of the right side of the roadway. Vehicle 1 came to final rest against the tree facing in the easterly direction.

V1 was heading north, approaching an intersection, on a two lane roadway that was under construction. V2 was headed eastbound and V3 was headed westbound, both vehicles approaching the intersection. V1 turned left and V1's left side contacted V2's front. V1 then rotated clockwise and V1's front contacted V3's left side.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway traveling into a ditch impacting the the ditch bank with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact facing west.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two-way not physically divided roadway in the #1 lane. Vehicle 2 is not in transport and is parked legally on the side of the roadway. Vehicle 1's right side made contact with Vehicle 2's left side.

V1 was heading east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 attempted to turn right at a 4 way intersection and entered a clockwise yaw. V1 departed the south east corner of the roadway striking a sign with its frontal plane. V1 then began to roll, left side leading, down an embankment. V1 rolled 3 quarter turns onto its right side and then fell back onto its top plane where it came to final rest heading south west.

V1 was traveling north in the first lane on a four lane non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in the second lane.  V1 departed lane to the left. The left side of V1 impacted with the right side of V2. V2 came to final rest facing north in original lane. V1 came to final rest straddling the lane line between the first lane and second lane.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, non-physically divided roadway, V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 departed lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2, V1 came to final rest facing north in southbound lane. V2 came to final rest facing south in original lane.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on the same roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection V1 turned left and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west, negotiating a right curve. V2 was parked facing south in a private driveway. V1 departed the road to the left and began to rotate clockwise. The front plane of V1 contacted a utility pole, then the left plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 began to rotate counter clockwise and flipped over four quarter turns to the left. V1's left plane contacted three trees.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling in front of V1. As V2 approached the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 made impact with the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling in a southeast direction on a five lane undivided roadway in lane number 2.  V2 was trveling northeast on a three lane intersecting roadway in lane number 1. V1 and V2 entered into the intersection at the same time. The right side of V1 collided with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest near point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane not physically divided roadway.  V1 exited the roadway to the left and struck a utility pole with its front then continued to travel and the front and sides struck a barbed wire fence.  V1 continued to travel through a field and came to rest.

V3, V4, V5 were stopped at a traffic signal facing southbound on a 7 lane non physically divided roadway V2 and V6 were traveling northbound. V1 (heavy truck) was westbound toward the intersection. The front of V1 struck the right side of V2 causing V2 to strike the front of V3 the front of V4 causing the rear of V2 to contact the front of V5. V6 (motorcycle) laid down the motorcycle to avoid a collision with V1 and V2.

V1 was traveling south bound on a 2 lane divided roadway in lane 1. V1 departed the roadway to the right, V1 then impacted a parking sign pole with it's front. V1 continued through the parking sign pole and the front of V1 impacted a wooden utility pole.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a four lane, two way divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped at the same intersection, facing east and turning left to travel north. As V2 attempted to turn left V1 traveled straight through the intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 then rotated clockwise and the front of V2 contacted a light pole.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the roadway on the left side. The LF wheel contact the curb. V1 continued west on the raised median where the front of V1 then contacted a tree.
V1 and V2 were traveling south west on a 5 lane highway in the #4 lane. V2 was slowing due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.
V1 was traveling east on a 2 lane, 2 way, undivided roadway. V1 struck a cow with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest in its original travel lane, headed east, near the point of impact.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, cresting a hill. V1 attempted to miss a deer in the roadway by steering right and went off the right side of the roadway. V1 steered back onto the roadway, over correcting, and entered a clockwise yaw. V1 departed the right side of the roadway again traveling southeast down an embankment striking a barbwire fence with its front and an unknown object contacting the undercarriage. V1 came to final rest just south of the fence, heading south.
V1 was traveling south east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer crossed the path of V1 striking the frontal plane of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling north on a 2 lane non physically divided roadway. V1 made contact to the rear of V2 which was legally parked with no occupants facing north on the east side of the road.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north.  At at T-intersection V1 began to turn left and departed the end of the road.  The front right wheel of V1 impacted a curb.  V1 continued off road and contacted a stand of 4 trees.  3 trees contacted the front plane and one contacted the right plane.

Vehicle 1 was northbound in lane two on a two way, five lane, with two way center turn lane, undivided roadway, stopped in traffic. Vehicle 2 was northbound on the same roadway in lane 3, the two way left turn lane. Vehicle 1 started an U-Turn to travel southbound. The left side of V1 struck the right side of V2.

V1 was westbound on a two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound on the intersecting two lane roadway approaching the intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V2 slightly rotated clockwise and came to final rest facing south. V1 continued forward approximately another 10 meters and came to final rest facing west.

V1 was north bound on a two lane, bidirectional paved roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right, and traveled approximately 140 meters parallel with the roadway before V1 impacted an embankment with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted a cement block/4"x4" fence, a large rock,  a decorative antique plow, a chain link fence, and a utility pole with its frontal plane. After impact with the utility pole, V1 rotated counter clockwise, rolling over 2 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its roof, on top of a chain link fence.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, bidirectional paved roadway, when a deer entered the roadway from the left side of the road. V1's frontal plane impacted the animal.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the right road edge.  V1 struck a utility pole with its frontal plane, rotated approximately 180 degrees clockwise, and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling south on a 3 lane undivided roadway in lane 2 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on 4 lane one way road approaching the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road approaching an intersection to make a left turn. V2 was traveling west on the same road. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road that curved to the left and ascended an incline. V1 departed the right side of the road climbed up a rock formation causing V1 to roll onto its left side. V1 slid nearly 36 meters and came to rest in the roadway.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound. V1 departed the road on the right side and contacted the front bumper on two trees, a pole, and then three more trees.

V1 was traveling north east through an intersection in the #2 lane of a 5 lane roadway. V2 was traveling south east turning left in an intersection to head north east. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was negotiating a right hand curve southbound on a 2 lane freeway off-ramp in the number 2 lane. V1 departed the roadway to the left side. The left side of V1 impacted a tree.  The collision caused V1 to be split in half at the B-Pillar.  The back half rotated counter clockwise coming rest just past the first tree impact.  The front half of V1 rotated counter clockwise and traveled forward where the front of V1 impacted the ground and the front of V1 impacted a second tree. The front half of V1 came to rest near the second tree impact.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way undivided tw- lane roadway approaching a T intersection. V1 continued straight through the intersection and departed the roadway on the west edge. The front of V1 contacted an embankment and came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on two lane, two way undivided roadway with V1 behind V2. V3 was traveling north on the same roadway. V2 stopped to make left turn into driveway. V1 attempted to pass V2 on the west berm and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 was pushed forward and left into the northbound travel lane. The front of V1 then contacted the left side of V3.
V1 was traveling north in lane two of five on a one way roadway. V2 was stopped facing north in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to turn at the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V2 was traveling east in the number one lane of a three lane roadway composed of one lane of eastbound traffic and two lanes of westbound traffic separated by a painted median. V1 was traveling west in the number one lane on the same roadway. V1 departed the left side of its travel lane and crossed the number 2 westbound land and traveled through the painted median into the eastbound travel lane. The front of V2 collided with the front of V2. After colliding with V2, V1 continued to travel in a westerly direction while rotating counterclockwise and came to final rest facing south straddling the painted median and the eastbound travel lane.  After colliding with V1, V2 traveled in a southeasterly direction with a counter clockwise rotation off the right side of its lane of travel and onto the dirt shoulder ultimately coming to final rest on the south shoulder of the road facing north.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a four lane two-way undivided roadway. V1 departed the lane at left entering the third and fourth lanes before departing the roadway. The LF wheel of V1 contacted the curb (Event 1). V1 continued over the curb and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the wall (Event 2). V1 continued through the wall and rolled over onto the right side (Event 3). V1 continued forward rolling onto the roof. V1 then went back onto the right side and onto the wheels before hitting an embankment and rolling onto it's left side with final rest on the left side plane.

V1 was traveling north a two way, three lane, undivided roadway negotiating a curve.  V2 was stopped on the northbound shoulder of the same roadway.  V1 departed the right side (eastern) lane line and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.  Both V1 and V2 came to final rest slightly off of the east edge of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a three-lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a three-lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Subsequently, V2 rotated clockwise then tripped and rolled over one-quarter turn to the left and came to final rest on its left side.
V1 was heading south on a two lane two way roadway. V2 was legally parked facing south on the same two lane two way roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel and a two way left turning lane in each direction. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in the same direction in the third, two way left turn lane. As V1 was making a left turn, the left side plane of V1 made impact with the frontal plane of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling SE. V1 lost control, and in initiated a counterclockwise (CCW) yaw before departing the left roadside, into the median area. The right front bumper corner area (right side) impacted the dense shrubbery as the vehicle continued to rotate CCW, engaging the entire right side plane. The driver was fully ejected out of the right side window glazing as the vehicle spun off of the shrubbery lined median to its final rest position.

Vehicle #1 was traveling North, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the road to the left, and the left plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise, the front plane contacted an unknown object and the right plane contacted another tree.

V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection. V2 was travelling north on the exit road of a shopping mall, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V2 attempted to turn left into the westbound lanes. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling south on the same roadway behind V2. As V1 was overtaking V2, V2 began to turn left onto the intersecting roadway and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling east in lane 2 (of 2 lanes) on an interchange ramp behind V2, which was also in lane 2. V1 attempted to overtake V2 on its right and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a 6-lane, two-way not physically divided, roadway in the #2 lane approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on one-way, 4-lane roadway approaching the same intersection in the #2 lane. Vehicle 1's right side and Vehicle 2's front end made contact with each other as they both proceeded straight through the intersection. Vehicle 1 after initial contact rotated clockwise and rolled primarily to its left 2 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its roof.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling north on an unmarked access roadway. V2 entered on the four lane roadway going straight. The front of V1 impacted with the left of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest near point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east, exiting a driveway and Vehicle 2 was traveling south, in the first of two lanes on the intersecting roadway. V1 entered the roadway turning right. The left side of V1 was contacted by the front of V2.

V1 was westbound on a two-lane, one-way, roadway divided by a grass median. V1 impacted a deer with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 traveled to the right side of the road coming to final rest facing west.

V1 was traveling south on a six lane non physically divided highway (4 travel lanes and 2 turn lanes). V1 began to yaw then crossed into north-bound traffic lanes and the right side of V1 struck the front of V2. V1 rotated counter-clockwise along with V2 rotating counter-clockwise where they stayed engaged as the right side of V1 and the left side of V2 and caused more damage.

V1 was eastbound on two lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound on a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered into the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 impacted with the right side of V2.

V1 was northbound on two-lane roadway negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 traveled off the roadway going northbound and rotated counter-clockwise. V1 right front and right rear wheels dug into the ground resulting in the vehicle rolling over it's right side. V1 rolled 4 quarter turns coming to final rest on it's wheels in the westbound lane of a two-lane roadway facing west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a two-lane undivided roadway and departed the road to the right onto a grass residential lawn. V1 impacted a mailbox with the front plane then re-entered, crossed and departed the road to the left. V1 impacted a 3 strand barb-wire fence with the front plane and came to rest beyond the fence.

V1 was headed north on a two lane, two way, unmarked and undivided roadway. V2 was parked partially on the right shoulder and partially in the northbound lane of the same roadway, headed north. V1 was passing V2, when V2 began to move forward turning left toward a westbound driveway. V1 struck the left side plane of V2 with its right side plane. V1 came to final rest headed north on the left (west) side of the roadway. V2 came to final rest, behind V1, headed north on the left (west) side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway.  A deer entered the roadway from the westbound lane (left side) contacting the front plane of V1.  V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was east bound on a two lane, two way, non divided, narrow, dirt road. A non contact vehicle was south bound on the same roadway. V1 attempted to make room to get by the non contact vehicle, in doing so V1 lost control, departed the roadway to the left, where it impacted a tree with its frontal plane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, in the first lane of a two lane highway. Vehicle 2 was stopped facing north, in the first lane ahead of V1. Vehicle 3 was stopped facing north, in the second lane. Vehicle 4 was stopped facing north, in the first lane ahead of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of V4. V1 departed the lane to the left side and the front of V1 contacted the back of V3, V3 was pushed forward and the front of V3 contacted the rear of V4, then the front of V3 contacted a concrete traffic barrier.

V1 was traveling north on an undivided two lane roadway. V2 was legally parked in a drive way. V1 departed the roadway and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. This pushed the front of V2 to impact a garage door.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, unmarked roadway. V1 went off the right side of the roadway to miss an animal in the roadway. The front of V1 struck a barbed wire fence, and a clump of bushes at the end of the barbed wire fence. V1 came to final rest off the roadway headed north.

V1 was westbound in the number 2 lane of a two way, four-lane, undivided roadway. V2 was behind V1 in the same westbound lane. V3 was westbound in the number one travel lane of the same four-lane roadway. V4 was eastbound in the number 2 lane on the same four-lane roadway. V4 began to cross into the westbound lanes. V1 made an avoidance maneuver resulting in the right side of V1 impacting the left side of V3 (event 1). V3 came to final rest on the edge of the westbound roadway facing west. Then the front of V1 impacted the front of V4 (event 2). V1 rotated counter-clockwise across the westbound travel lanes and came to final rest next to the north concrete barrier facing east. V4 rotated counter clockwise resulting in the right side of V4 impacting the left side of V2 (event 3). V4 continued rotating counter-clockwise crossing both eastbound lanes and impacting the concrete barrier with its right rear bumper corner (event 4).  V4 came to final rest facing east in the number 1 lane of the eastbound lanes. V2 came to final rest next to V4 in the middle of the eastbound lanes facing west.

All vehicles were traveling northbound on a major highway in lane one. V2, V3 and V4 were stopped ahead of V1. V2 attempted to drive onto the paved shoulder in order to avoid being rear-ended by V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 started to rotate clockwise and impacted the back of V3. V2 rotated counter clockwise and impacted the concrete median on the east side of the roadway. After the impact with V2, V3 was pushed forward and rotated counter clockwise. The right side of V3 impacted the left side of V4.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling westbound on a median divided roadway entering the intersection. Both Vehicles #1 and #2 were making a right hand turn from adjacent travel lanes. Vehicle #1 was contacted on the right side plane by the frontal plane of Vehicle #2. Vehicle #1 continued to travel across the three northbound lanes of the cross street, crossed over a grass median and contacted Vehicle #3 on its frontal plane with its' frontal plane while Vehicle #3 was stopped in its lane. Vehicle #3 then contacted its right frontal plane with the left side plane of Vehicle #4, which was also stopped and in the adjacent travel lane to Vehicle #3.

V2 was northbound on a seven-lane roadway in the first lane. V1 was northbound on the same seven-lane roadway in the second lane. V1 merged into the first lane. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 then spun clockwise and came to final rest in the middle of the roadway facing northwest. V2 came to final rest at the point of impact with V1.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on the intersecting two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching the intersection where it turned left when the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V1 came to final rest off the roadway and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway, V1 departed the roadway on the right side before the front plane made impact with a utility pole.  V1  came to final rest at the pole and caught fire.
V1 was west bound on a two lane non-divided roadway, when the front of V1 impacted a deer in the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 4 lane physically divided roadway, toward a diverging diamond intersection, in the number 2 lane.  V1 moved into the number 1 lane to pass a non-contact vehicle. V2 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane, approaching the diverging diamond. The front of V2 struck the front of V1. Then V1 departed the roadway to the south, and the left side of V1 struck an electrical box.

V1 was traveling south through a four leg intersection on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling east through the same four leg intersection on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front plane of V1 struck the left side plane of V2. V1 came to final rest south of the intersection, headed south, on the left side of the roadway. V2 came to final rest south of the intersection, headed south, in the middle of the roadway.

V1 was originally facing west in a two-way, physically divided parking lot entrance/exit. V1 turned left, going south out of the parking lot. V1 drove onto the center median and the front of V1 impacted a crosswalk sign pole.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling north on the same roadway.  V2, while entering a private driveway was contacted on its rear right plane by V1's frontal plane.  Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a 3 lane roadway in lane two (turn lane) attempting to turn left onto an intersecting road. V2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway and going straight through the intersection. V1's front contacted V2's front within the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound, and Vehicle 2 was traveling Northbound, on the same 3 lane roadway. Vehicle 1 began to rotate clockwise, and traveled over the left lane line. Vehicle 1 entered lane 1 northbound travel, and the left side of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 left, and Vehicle 2 left, contacted in a side slap fashion, and Vehicle 1 then traveled across all travel lanes to the right, and departed the west roadside. V1 traveled down a hill before coming to final rest. After initial impact, Vehicle 2 went off the roadway to the right and contacted a utility trailer with it's front where it also came to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with three lanes of travel in each direction. As V1 was crossing an intersection, V1 departed the roadway on the right side and traveled approximately 25 meters before the frontal plane of V1 made contact with a corner of a building.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southwest bound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. As V1 was making a left turn at the above intersection, the left side plane of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling northeast on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left and continued off the left side of the roadway in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 impacted a tree with the right side (event 1) causing damage. Continuing the counter clockwise rotation V1 impacted another tree with the back plane causing damage (event 2) before impacting another tree with the back plane causing damage (event 3). V1 came to final rest near the final point of impact facing southwest.
Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest when it departed the right road edge. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted a utility pole.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west when it departed the right road edge. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted a utility pole.

V1 was traveling southbound on a single lane ramp . V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The right side plane of V1 impacted the guardrail face. V1 reentered the roadway. V1 then departed the roadway on the left side. The left side plane of V1 impacted the guardrail face. V1 crossed a median and entered the northbound lanes of the roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the left and impacted a tree with its frontal plane. The final rest position of V1 was facing eastbound.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 and V3 were traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway ahead of V1. V2 and V3 were stopped in the road to let another vehicle cross from the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the back of V2. The frontal plane of V2 then contacted the back of V3.
V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was legally parked facing west. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a one-way, two lane road approaching an interstate toll booth. The front left tire impacted a concrete barrier surrounding the toll booth. V1 then rolled to the right a total of 2 quarter turns and came to final rest next to the toll booth on its roof.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was legally parked south on the same two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a three lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection  the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  V1 then fled the scene.
V1 and V2 were traveling north west on a 4 lane divided highway in the #3 lane. V2 decelerated due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane 2 of a 3 lane interstate. V2 was traveling in the same direction in lane 1. V1 crossed the lane to the right where the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.  V2 then rotated clockwise and departed the road on the right side. V2 then tripped over, leading left, and rolled down an embankment for 8 quarter turns before coming to rest on its wheels. After impacting V2, V1 continued straight for a quarter mile and the front of V1 impacted a guardrail face, coming to rest with the left side of V1 against the face of the guardrail.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the right in the #1 lane of a 2 lane road. V2 was negotiating a curve to the left in the #1 lane of a 2 lane road. V1 departed their travel lane to the left where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  The front of V1 contacted an animal in the road.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  The front of V2 contacted an animal.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west. Vehicle #2 was traveling south. Both vehicles entered an intersection, and the front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. V1 was deflected towards the southwest intersection quadrant where it departed the roadway and its right side plane contacted a utility pole.

Vehicle 1 was turning right from a driveway to travel westbound on a two way with center turn lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was westbound on the same roadway. Vehicle 2 front end struck the left side of Vehicle 1.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the right hand side contacting an embankment with its frontal plane.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north, negotiating a left curve. Driver passed out and lost directional control of vehicle. V1 started to rotate clockwise and departed the roadway to the right. V1 impacted the curb of the roadway with its left side wheels in two separate events. V1 rolled onto its left side for a one quarter turn rollover. The top of V1 impacted a tree and a wire fence.

V1 was northbound on a two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was westbound on a two-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered into the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing northwest.  V2 continued forward, slightly rotating counter-clockwise and came to final rest facing southwest in the middle of the roadway.

V1 was southeast on a four lane undivided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right where the RF tire contacted a curb, V1 continued off road and the front of V1 contacted a utility pole where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane, two-way roadway entering a light controlled four-legged intersection. V2 traveling north on a three-lane, two-way roadway entering the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 was westbound on a 4 lane, 2 way, physically divided roadway. V1 veered off the right side of the roadway striking a bridge with its right side plane. V1 came to final rest on the bridge headed west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound in lane two. V1 departed the roadway on the left side while spinning counter clockwise and contacted the front bumper on a guardrail. V1 continued spinning counter clockwise and contacted the right side on the guardrail.
Vehicle was traveling north bound in lane two. V1 contacted the front bumper on an object laying on the roadway. The object also made contact on the right side of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane roadway passing through a T-intersection. V2 was traveling south on the intersecting four lane median divided roadway turning left at the intersection to travel east. The front of V1 struck the back of V2. After initial impact, V2 traveled off the south side of the roadway and the front of V2 struck an embankment, before coming to final rest. After initial impact, V1 traveled across the westbound lanes and V1s LF wheel struck the curb on the north side of the roadway. V1 continued, departing the roadway and the undercarriage struck the curb. As V1 continued off the roadway, the front of V1 struck a wooden post, then a tree and then a second wooden post, before coming to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was northbound in lane one on a two way five lane roadway entering an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was eastbound in lane one on a two way three lane roadway crossing through the same intersection.  The front of Vehicle 1 contacted the right side of Vehicle 2.

Vehicle  1 was westbound on a two way four lane bridge roadway.  Vehicle # 2 was eastbound on a two way four lane bridge roadway.  Vehicle # 1 traveled into the eastbound lane where the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles then contacted the guardrail face with the front planes.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane two of a two-way 4-lane roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in lane two of a two-way four-lane roadway. At an intersection, as V1 was making a left turn, the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling south on the Interstate (divided trafficway - median strip with positive barrier) in lane 1 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the right.  V1 vaulted into a culvert where its front end came into contact with the dirt floor of the culvert, a wire fence and the vertical concrete wall on the opposite side of the culvert.

V1 was traveling south at a high rate of speed when it exited the Interstate (at a designated exit ramp) and end departed the roadway (skidding longitudinally with less than 30 degrees rotation).  V1's front/left and back/left wheel/tire came into contact with the curb at the road edge.  V1 then vaulted a downward sloping embankment (and an adjacent wire fence), and while airborne, began to rotate left about its longitudinal axis.  Beyond the wire fence, V1's left/front came into contact with the ground and V1 completed its overturn (4 quarter turns in total from vault to final rest; leading left).  During the rollover, both occupants were totally ejected.

V1 was traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 1 (of a two lanes) and was approaching V2, which was also traveling west in lane 1 at a lower steady speed. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane road in lane one approaching an intersection. V1 entered the intersection and the front left tire of V1 impacted a curb. The vehicle continued forward and the front of V1 impacted a pole. V1 rotated clockwise and continued forward, where the front of V1 impacted a sign. V1 then rotated clockwise and the back of V1 impacted 2 shrubs and a tree where it came to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two-way not physically divided roadway attempting to make a left hand turn onto a private drive. V2 was traveling south in the number 2 lane going straight. Vehicle 1's right and Vehicle's 2 front made contact with each other. Vehicle 1 came to final rest in the roadway facing south. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the right side of the same roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway crossing through an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane roadway approaching a stop sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling westbound approaching the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2, after initial contact V2 departed the roadway on the southbound side. V2 rolled over 2 quarter turns before contacting a large tree on the right side while on its roof.
V1 was traveling west in the far right lane. V2 was exiting a business driveway making a right turn to head west on the same road way. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was going southbound on a five lane non divided roadway and entered into the intersection. Vehicle #2 was going eastbound on an intersecting three lane non divided roadway and entered into the intersection. Vehicle #2 front contacted the right plane of Vehicle #1.

V2 was traveling north on a 2 lane, two way roadway. V1 was traveling south on the same roadway after departing a parking lane on the right side of the roadway. V1 began to turn left to perform a U-turn maneuver to head north on the roadway. During the maneuver, V1's right side plane contacted the frontal plane of V2. After impact, V1 traveled northwest on the roadway and departed the roadway on the west side. V1 then traveled down an embankment and the front of V1 struck an apartment building before coming to final rest.

V2 was traveling west on a 2 lane non-divided roadway. V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane non-divided roadway approaching a ' T ' intersection with V2's roadway. V2 frontal plane impacted V1's left side plane as V1 attempted a left turn. After impact V1 spun counterclockwise and the front of V1 contacted an embankment on the south side of the intersection.
Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were both traveling north with Vehicle 2 ahead of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 2 had stopped for traffic. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's rear plane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest, on a two way, four lane, undivided roadway, approaching a four way, traffic light, intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling west, on a two way, five lane, undivided roadway, approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's right plane as both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection.

V1 was traveling west in lane two on a two lane one way roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the south edge then re-entered the roadway.  V1 then entered a clockwise rotation, crossing both westbound travel lanes.  V1 departed the north road edge and rolled two quarter turns, coming to rest on its roof.
Vehicle # 1 was eastbound on a two way, three lane roadway, traveling behind vehicle # 2. Vehicle # 2 stopped for a crossing pedestrian, and  Vehicle # 1 front end struck the rear end of Vehicle # 2.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane one way interchange roadway approaching an intersection. The front of V1 contacted a curb.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the right in the first northbound lane on a four lane, two way divided roadway.  V1 began a clockwise yaw and departed the roadway to the right. V1 then rolled two quarter turns to the left and became fully submerged in standing water.

V1 was traveling west on a six lane, two way, divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 and V3 were traveling east on a six lane, two way, divided roadway approaching the same intersection in lanes one and two. In the intersection, V1 attempted a left turn and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in lane two of eastbound travel. V2 moved right and the front of V2 then contacted the left side of V3 in lane one.

V1 was eastbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway. V2 was westbound on the same roadway.  V1 crossed  the left lane line and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Upon impact, V1 rotated clockwise and departed the left (north) side of the roadway. V1 continued down an embankment, leading with its left side and initiated a four-quarter turn rollover sequence. V1 came to rest on its wheels and was facing southeast. Upon impact, V2 rotated clockwise and departed the south roadside, coming to rest facing northwest.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling north on a two way two lane roadway with a center left turn lane. V1 and V2 stopped behind a long string of vehicles that were stopped at a 4 leg intersection stop light. V3 struck the rear plane of V2 with its frontal plane. V2 then struck V1 in its rear plane with its frontal plane. V4 then struck V3 in its rear plane with its frontal plane. All 4 vehicles came to final rest in their travel lane, near the points of impact, headed north.

V1 was traveling northbound in the #1 lane of a two lane roadway. V1 steered left to avoid impacting a vehicle leaving the parking lot and drove over the center median across traffic. V1 then made contact with the curb and continued to impact a fence.

V1 was traveling north in the #1 lane on a two lane road. V1 lost control due to weather conditions and departed the road on the left. The front of V1 impacted a concrete block. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 impacted a fence. V1 as it came to rest had the right side come to rest against a tree.

V1 was traveling east on a five lane interstate in the number four lane. V2, V3, and V4 were stopped facing eastbound on the same five lane interstate in the number four lane due to traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of the collision forced the front of V2 to impact the rear of V3. The force from the collision forced the front of V3 to impact the rear of V4
V1 was eastbound on a three lane, two way road. A deer crossed the road north to south in front of V1. The front of V1 struck the deer.

V1 was traveling northwest on a  two-lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southeast on same roadway. The driver of V1 lost control as V1 initiated a counterclockwise yaw. V1 traversed the centerlines and ultimately crossed the left (west) road edge line. The driver of V2 detected V1 encroaching and steered right, placing V2 on the shoulder. The front of V2 impacted the left fender of V1 (Event 1). The initial impact rotated V1 rapidly CCW as the right side (V1) impacted the left side of V2 (Event 2), before both vehicles came to their respective final rest positions.

V1 was traveling north when slushy roadway conditions caused V1 to yaw, counter clockwise, and depart the travel lanes to the left. The front of V1 made contact a center concrete barrier. V1 then continued to yaw and the back of V1 contacted the same concrete traffic barrier. V1 came to rest facing south against the concrete barrier.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane roadway passing through an intersection, V2 was traveling west through the same intersection on the intersecting roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling eastbound on a four-lane roadway. V2 and V3 were stopped at a traffic light. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2 which pushed V2 forward where the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3.
V1 was traveling west on a four lane physically divided roadway. V2 was stopped in traffic traveling west on the same roadway. Resulting in V1 front plane contacting the rear of V2.
V1 and V2 were eastbound on a two lane two way non divided roadway. V2 came to a stop to make a left turn across traffic. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's rear plane.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west and Vehicle #2 was traveling northeast; both vehicles were approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2 within the intersection.

V1 was backing southeast out of a private driveway onto a two way two lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southwest on the same two way two lane undivided roadway. The rear plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane two. Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane one. V1 departed the lane on the right side and contacted the front bumper on the back of V2's trailer.

V1 and V2 were both traveling southbound on the same 4 lane major highway. V1 was traveling in lane 3, V2 was traveling in lane 4. V1 attempted to change lanes, into lane 4. The left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a 5 lane major highway negotiating a right curve. V1 was traveling in lane 3, V2 was traveling in lane 2. V1 attempted to change lanes into lane 2, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two-way, two-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the right road edge and struck a cluster of trees.  V1 then rolled left two-quarter turns, contacting more trees during the rollover before coming to final rest on its top on the roadside.

V1 was northbound on a 4 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound in a 4 lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 was eastbound on a two lane roadway stopped at the intersection. Traffic in the southbound lanes were at a stop due to a traffic jam. V1 was attempting to make a left turn across the southbound lane after a NCV driver waved the driver of V1 though. The RF corner of V1 collided with the front of V2 (event 1). As the vehicles rotated after initial impact, the RRBC of V1 collided with the left side of V2 (event 2). V2 then rolled forward resulting in the front of V2 colliding with the front of V3 (event 3). V2, facing westbound, and V3, facing eastbound, came to final rest after their impact. V1 came to final rest facing southbound in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound on an unmarked two-lane roadway. V1 began to negotiate a left curve when a NCV crossed into V1's travel lane. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a tree where it came to final rest.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both north bound on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway with a left-hand turn lane.  Vehicle 1 was traveling in the two lane while vehicle 2 was traveling in the turn lane.  While V1 was making a lane change into the turn lane, the Front Right Side of V2 made contact with the Front Left Side of V1.  V2 was towed from the scene.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V1 struck the left side plane of V2 with its frontal plane. V2 went off the right side (east side) of the roadway striking the ditch with its right wheels, where it came to final rest headed north. V1 entered a clockwise yaw and came to final rest on the southbound lane headed north.

V1 was traveling north and entering intersection V2 was traveling east through intersection D1 attempted to try and avoid collision by steering left. D1 noticed V2 and attempted to avoid collision by accelerating. Neither vehicle was successful in avoiding collision. V2 made contact with left side of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a two way two lane roadway. A non-contact vehicle entered V1's travel lane in an attempt to make a U turn to travel northbound on the same roadway. V1 steered left to avoid contact with the vehicle causing V1 to travel off the roadway on the left, down an embankment where the front of V1 contacted a fence. V1 continued to travel off the roadway until V1's front contacted a large pile of dirt/rock coming to rest upon the dirt pile.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and departed the western road edge. V1 contacted two trees with its frontal plane before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was northbound on a four-lane divided highway when it departed the left (west) side of the road and its left side impacted a cable guardrail (event 1). V1 spun and its front came to rest against the cable guardrail (event 2).
Vehicle 2 was traveling eastbound in the third lane of four on a restricted access roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling behind V2 in the third lane of four when V1 contacted V2 in the rear.
Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound down a two way traffic way. V1 attempted to make a left turn, departed the road and struck a utility pole with the front.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a freeway in the first of four lanes. Vehicle 2 was eastbound on a freeway in the second of four lanes. V2 changed lanes to the right to avoid slowing traffic ahead. The front of V2 contacted the back of V1's trailer.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane one on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel and a left turning lane in each direction. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in the same direction in front of V1. The frontal plane of V1 made impact with the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a four lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a four lane divided roadway.  V1 was attempting to take a left turn in the roadway to travel southbound. A non-contact vehicle stopped to let V1 pass. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the right side plane of V1, as V1 was attempting to make the left turn.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a third lane undivided two-way roadway. V1 then made a left turn at the intersection to travel eastbound in the first lane of a five lane divided roadway. After making the turn, V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The frontal plane impacted a curb first before impacting a utility pole with the frontal plane. The vehicle came to rest after the second point of impact.

V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a one lane one-way roadway approaching an intersection with a stop sign. V2 was traveling south in the first lane of a two lane two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to cross through the intersection and the frontal plane of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was passing northbound through an intersection controlled by a flashing light on a two-lane, two-way road.  V2 was traveling east through the same intersection controlled by a flashing light on a two-lane, two-way road.  The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling northbound on a four-lane major highway, in lane 3. V1 departed multiple lanes to the right and then departed the roadway. The front of V1 impacted the guardrail. V1 then rotated clockwise and impacted the guard rail again with it's left side plane. V1 continued rotating clockwise and came to rest back on the roadway in lane 1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound approaching an intersection attempting to turn left. Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound in lane two approaching the intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front bumper of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound in lane one. V1 departed the lane on the left side three times and departed the roadway on the left side and contacted the front bumper on a wall. V1 then rotated clockwise and rolled one quarter turn on the left side.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane road. V2 and V3 were stopped due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of the impact pushed the front of V2 into the rear of V3.

V1 was heading westbound in the #2 lane of a 4 lane, one-way roadway traveling through an intersection. V2 was heading northbound in the #2 lane of a 4 lane, one-way roadway traveling through the same intersection. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 in the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north. V1 departed the road to the right. The front of V1 contacted a fence. V1 continued north and contacted another fence with its frontal plane. V1 passed over an intersecting roadway and the front of V1 contacted two trees and came to rest.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two-lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front and left plane struck two signposts. V1 then overturned continuing to head westbound where it struck a vinyl fence and the rear plane struck the steps to a house while upside down.

Vehicles #1, #2, #3, and #4 were going southbound on a six lane positively divided roadway. Vehicles #2, #3, and #4 were slowing. Vehicle #1's frontal plane contacted Vehicle # 2's back plane. Vehicle #2's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #3 back plane. Vehicle #3's frontal plane contacted the back plane of Vehicle #4. All vehicles came to final rest within the travel lane.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two way roadway when it's front plane struck the left side planes of V2 and V3  which were parked in the opposite direction facing the northwest. V1 then traveled past the parked vehicles and departed the roadway on the right side. After departing the roadway, the vehicle traveled over a curb and struck a utility pole with the right side plane of the vehicle before coming to final rest.

V2 was traveling east in lane 2 of a 4 lane divided roadway, V1 was traveling south in a median cross-through toward the eastbound lanes. As V1 entered the eastbound lanes the front plane of V2 impacted the right side plane of V1.
V1 was traveling north on a 2 way non-divided roadway and departed the right side of the roadway.  V1 went down a slope and impacted a fence post with the right plane.

V1 was northbound on a two-lane roadway. V2 was westbound on an intersecting two-lane roadway. V1 and V2 entered into the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 (event 1).
V1 was traveling east on a one way two lane highway. A deer crossed the path of V1. V1 contacted the deer with its front plane. V1 came to final rest on the road way.
V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way undivided roadway. A deer crossed the path of v1 contacting the left plane of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was west bound on a two lane two way non divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, and traveled down a steep embankment, where it impacted the bottom of the embankment/ditch with its frontal plane. V1's frontal plane, dug into the embankment edge and rotated rapidly counterclockwise coming to rest upright and facing east.

V2 and V3 were stopped in traffic going northwest on a two-lane, one way road. V1 was traveling northwest on same roadway, behind V2. All three vehicles were traveling in the second travel lane. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The front of V2 impacted the back of V3. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a sign post.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast when it departed the right road edge. Vehicle 1 contacted a mile marker sign then a stop sign and then overturned leading with the left plane. Vehicle 1 rolled four quarter turns coming to final rest on it wheels.
Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were both travelling southeast with Vehicle 2 ahead of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's rear plane.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling northbound in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane road. V2 was slowing due to traffic and V3 was stopped due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of the impact pushed V2 into V3, where the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.

V1 was negotiating a curve heading northbound in the #1 lane of a 2 lane road. V2 was legally parked on the right shoulder facing north. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 came to rest in the middle of the roadway and V2 got pushed forward and came to final rest off the road on the right.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with one lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling westbound in the right lane on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, the left plane of V1 made impact with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V3 was parked on the west side of the roadway facing southbound. At the above intersection, the right plane of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2. V2 then proceeded southbound crossing through the intersection and the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the rear plane of V3.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same two lane, two way roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was turning left out of a private parking lot heading westbound. V2 was eastbound on a four lane undivided roadway. The front of V2 impacted with the left of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest near the initial point of impact.
V1 was eastbound on a four lane roadway, divided by a grass median. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the south side of the roadway, facing east.
V1 was southbound in lane 1 on a 2 way physically divided roadway. V2, a semi tractor trailer, was ahead of V1 in the same lane. The front of V1 struck the back of V2's trailer.

V2 was traveling south in lane two of a four-lane, two-way undivided highway with a steady incline.  V1 was traveling in the same direction and same lane. V2 stopped to make a left hand turn.  The front plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane road in the number 1 lane. V2 was traveling southbound on a 2 lane road in the number 1 lane. V2 traveled over the lane line to the left to overtake vehicles in front of them and was unable to return to the original travel lane. For an unknown reason V1 was traveling on the shoulder off the roadway. V2 steered left and departed the roadway to the shoulder where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound in the #2 lane of a 5 lane two way not physically divided roadway. V2 was stopped due to traffic. V1 was slowing but was distracted and did not stop in time before the front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was exiting a 5 lane freeway in the exit lane heading south. As V1 was exiting the freeway another vehicle crossed solid lines and was heading towards V1. The driver of V1 steered right to avoid a collision with the vehicle causing V1 to depart the roadway on the right and impact a wall. V1 bounced off of the wall and traveled back across the initial travel lane and impacted a barrier wall on the left side of the roadway and came to rest on the left shoulder of the exit lane.

V1 was traveling north on a physically divided Interstate in lane 3 (of four lanes) and was approaching V2. V2 was stopped, in the same lane, facing a northerly direction, due to a previous crash. The driver of V2 was standing on the roadway to the left of V2. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2, and the driver of V2 (now a pedestrian) was contacted by V2.
Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were traveling north in the same lane. Vehicle 2 slowed for traffic and the front plane of vehicle 1 struck the back plane of vehicle 2.
V1 and V2 were headed south in the #2 lane of a 5 lane divided traficway.  V1 front made contact with V2 rear.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in the number 2 lane on a two-way not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in the number 2 lane on a two-way not physically divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1's left and Vehicle 2's right side made contact with each other on the south western part of the the intersection. Both Vehicles departed the roadway to the left. Vehicle 1 continued though the center median in the intersection making contact with two trees, followed by tow larger boulders. Vehicle 1 returned to the roadway and continued across it making contact to the roadway markers and departing the roadway on the right side. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the east side of the intersection. Vehicle 2 came to final rest on the south side of the intersection.
