V1 was traveling south on two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right side, struck a utility pole with the right plane, then continued traveling into the wooded area adjacent to roadway, where V1 struck a tree, with the front plane, and came to final rest.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a six-lane roadway. The front of V1 struck a pedestrian crossing the road.

V1 was traveling northbound on a five-lane roadway; V2 was traveling southbound. V1 was making a left turn at an intersection when the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. After initial impact, V1 rolled over two quarter turns and came to final rest on its roof.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway toward a T intersection. V1 went straight across the intersecting north/south roadway and departed the road edge. The front of V1 contacted a post and V1 continued to travel east. The front of V1 then contacted an embankment and traveled southeast until the front of V1 contacted a wire fence.

V1 was westbound in lane two on a six lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was southbound on a four lane undivided roadway in lane three approaching the same intersection. As V2 attempted to turn to its left and travel east on the intersecting roadway the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 then rotated counter clockwise and departed the southeast intersection apex. The rear of V2 contacted a pole and came to rest.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on the intersecting two lane two way roadway.  As V1 and V2 proceeded to travel straight through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road that curved slightly to the left, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south behind V1. V3 was traveling north on the same roadway approaching the intersection, with V3 ahead of V2. As V1 turned left to travel east the front of V1 contacted the front of V3 in the intersection. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane two on a 5 lane non physically divided roadway. V2 was entering the roadway from the east, exiting a driveway. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1 in lane two of northbound travel.

V1 was traveling west on a 2-lane, two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling north on the intersecting two-lane, two-way undivided roadway.  As V1 and V2 proceeded to travel straight through the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  V2 rotated counter-clockwise and departed the northeast corner and the front of V2 contacted a fence.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a three lane road with a center left turn lane. V2 was stopped and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 then rolled two quarter turns  right side leading and came to rest on its roof facing south on the roadway shoulder.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north bound in lane one. Vehicle #2 was traveling north bound in lane one. V1 contacted the front bumper on the back of V2's trailer.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided road way. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V1 was negotiating a left hand curve and crossed the center line and into the path of V2. The front left plane of V1 contacted the front left plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on an unpaved dirt/gravel road, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 entered a clockwise yaw, departed the road to the right onto a dirt and grass foreslope, and contacted a small tree with the left plane. V1 continued to rotate and sustained 2 impacts to a barbed wire fence; first with the right plane and then with the front plane.
V1 exited a private drive and turned left onto a two-way non divided roadway. V2 was legally parked facing south on the two-way roadway. The front right of V1 struck the back of V2.

V1 was traveling east in the third lane on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in the center lane of a five lane non-physically divided roadway. Both vehicles traveled into intersection. The front of V2 impacted with the right side of V1. Impact forced V1 to rotate counter clockwise and come to final rest facing North. V2 came to final rest facing southwest.

V1 was traveling east in the first lane on a five lane physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling east in the second lane. V1 departed original lane to the left. The front of V2 impacted with the left side of V1. V1 came to final rest facing north in second lane. V2 came to final rest in original lane facing east.

V1 was southbound on a four lane undivided roadway. V2 was northbound on the same roadway. V1 was in the process of making a left turn into a private parking lot.  The front of V2 impacted with the right of V1 (event 1). V1 rotated clockwise, tripped over a planter (event 2), and the left of V1 impacted the same planter (event 3) before coming to final rest on the left side of the vehicle. V2 continued in a forward motion and came to final rest less than 10 feet from point of impact.
V1 traveling west on a two-way, 2 lane road going west. V2 was stopped facing west waiting to make a left turn into a private parking lot. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was northbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the east side of the roadway striking a line small trees with the frontal plane causing damage (events 1-8). V1 then struck a tree with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 rotated clockwise and overturned left side leading rolling 2 quarter turns coming to final rest on its roof facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 was stopped facing east attempting to turn left into a private lot.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.
V1 was traveling west on a four lane two way roadway. V2 was traveling east on a four lane two way roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north, negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1 departed the road to the right, and the front plane struck a tractor implement.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north. Vehicle #2 was traveling south. V1 departed its lane to the left and the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 departed the road to the left, and the front plane of V1 contacted a ditch then a fence.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was parked and unoccupied on the parking shoulder lane on the south side of the roadway facing eastbound. The frontal plane of V1 made impact with the rear plane of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south in a driveway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling east on an intersecting roadway.  V1 began to turn right and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling south in the same lane.  V2 began to slow and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest, on a one way, five lane roadway, in lane three, approaching an intersection; Vehicle 2, a medium/heavy van, was stopped, ahead of V1 and Vehicle 3 was stopped, ahead of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2, then the front of V2 contacted the back of V3.
Vehivle 1 was traveling southbound in the first of two lanes, Vehicle 2 was stopped southbound in the first of two lanes for a flagman at a construction entrance. V1 contacted V2 in the rear.

Vehicle 1, Vehicle 2, and Vehicle 3 were traveling east on a two lane one-way roadway in the number one lane. Vehicle 1's front and Vehicle 2's back made contact then Vehicle 2's front made contact with Vehicle 3's back.

V1 was southbound on a side street entering a five-lane roadway. V2 was westbound on the five-lane thoroughfare when V1 initiated a turn at the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2 (event 1). V2 continued west where its left side struck a sign (event 2), its back impacted a sign (event 3) a tree (event 4).
Vehicle 1 was eastbound in the second of two lanes. V1 attempted to enter the exit ramp for roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted a concrete barrier.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling west on 6 lane two-way physically divided roadway in the #1 lane. Vehicle 1 attempted to change lanes to the #2 lane. During the attempt to change lanes Vehicle 1's front end and Vehicle 2's back end made contact with each other. Vehicle 1 was unable to maintain control of the vehicle after the initial impact and rolled one quarter turn on to its left side. Vehicle 1 came rest on its left side.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling west in lane one on a six lane divided roadway. V1 was behind V2 and V2 was behind V3. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3.

Vehicle 1 was attempting the cross all lanes of traffic to the other side of the roadway from one private drive to another. Vehicle 2 was driving west in the number two lane on a 5 lane roadway with a continuous left hand turn lane. Vehicle 1's right and Vehicle 2's front end made contact with each other.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way undivided roadway with one lane of travel southbound and two lanes of travel northbound. V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in front of V1. V3 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in front of V2. The frontal plane of V1 made impact with the rear plane of V2. Then the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the rear plane of V3.

Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2, a medium/heavy straight truck, were traveling west, in adjacent lanes, on a 5-lane physically divided roadway; V2 was ahead of, and in the lane to the right of V1. V1 steered to the right to avoid a non-contact vehicle which was entering V1's lane of travel from the left, and entered the number 2 lane behind V2. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling southwest on a 2-lane divided roadway when it departed the roadway on the left and struck two separate delineator posts.  V1 reentered the roadway skidding laterally in a clockwise rotation, and then departed the roadway on the right.  V1 overturned (4 quarter turns, leading left) on the roadside.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane two way roadway approaching a T intersection. V2 and V3 were traveling north on the intersecting four lane two way divided roadway, approaching the same intersection. V2 was in lane one and V3 was in lane two of northbound travel. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V2 then rotated to counterclockwise and into lane two of northbound travel. The front of V3 then impacted the left side of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling northwest in lane five on a five lane divided highway. V2 was traveling ahead of V1. V2 slowed down for traffic and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was stopped in the center median facing south. V2 was traveling the same direction as V1 in lane two of three southbound travel lanes. V1 attempted to turn right across all three southbound travel lanes to enter a private drive. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in lane two of southbound travel. V1 then departed the west edge of the roadway and the front of V1 contacted a pole. V2 also departed the west road edge and the front of V2 contacted a fence.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane one of a 2 lane one way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound in lane one of a two lane roadway at the same intersection.  In the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 struck the right side plane of V2.

V1 was westbound in lane one on a two lane one way roadway. V2 was parked facing westbound along the north curb on the same roadway. V1 departed its initial lane of travel to the right. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 came to final rest near the point of impact. V2 came to final rest at point of impact.
V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane roadway. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the roadway facing west. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V2 was traveling west in lane two of a five lane two way undivided roadway with a center turn lane, approaching an intersection. V1 was attempting to turn to its left from the intersecting two lane undivided roadway. The front of V2 contacted the front of V1 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching a Y style intersection. V2 was traveling south on the intersecting two lane two way divided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V2 proceeded south through the intersection V1 attempted to turn to its left and travel north on the intersecting roadway. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound in the fourth of four lanes approaching an exit ramp. Vehicle 2 was westbound in the third lane of the same roadway. V3 was westbound in the second lane of the same roadway. V1 attempted to change lanes to its right and the front of V1 contacted an impact attenuator. V1 the began to rotate counterclockwise and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 was redirected to the right and the right side of V2 contacted the left side of V3. V2 and V3 traveled northeast and the front of both V2 and V3 contacted a concrete barrier.

V1 was traveling east on a two way two lane undivided roadway approaching a T intersection. V1 entered the intersection and skidded through it, then departed the east road edge of the intersection. The right side of V1 then contacted a tree.

V1 was traveling south in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V1 approached a Non-contact vehicle ahead and departed the lane at left to pass it on the left. Upon re-entering the initial travel lane V1 lost control and re-entered the first lane at the right, departed the first lane at right and then departed the roadway at right with a slight clockwise rotation. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the fence (Event 1). The vehicle continued through and the left side of V1 contacted the fence (Event 2).

V1 was southbound in lane three (turn-lane) of a five lane, two-way road approaching an intersection. V2 was northbound in lane one of the same roadway approaching the intersection. As V1 turned to its left to travel east on the intersecting roadway the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was westbound on the intersecting two lane, two way roadway. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was southbound in lane three (turning lane) on a five lane, two way road attempting to turn left at an intersection. V2 was northbound in lane one of the same five lane, two way road crossing through the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling south in lane one on a one way ramp onto a highway. V1 departed the roadway on the right and the right side of V1 contacted a concrete wall.
V1 was traveling north in lane three of three on a divided roadway. V2 was stopped for traffic in lane 3, directly in front of V1. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two way, non-positively divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V1's frontal plane impacted the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was facing north and attempting to cross over into the roadway from a parking lot to the adjacent parking lot. V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a three lane, two way undivided roadway. V1 drove northbound across three lanes. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2.

The crash took place at the intersection of a three lane east/west roadway and a three lane south roadway.V1 was traveling in the second lane of the three lane, two way undivided roadway heading westbound. V2 was traveling in the second lane of a three lane, two way undivided roadway heading eastbound. V1 was attempting to take a left turn at the intersection to travel southbound. V2 passed through the intersection. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 continued straight as V2 also continued straight and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2 (Event 1). As V2 rotated counterclockwise the left side plane contacted the left side plane of V1 (Event 2). V1 rotated clockwise and the left side plane contacted a fire post (Event 3).  V2's right side plane then contacted a chain link fence (Event 4). V2 came to final rest as the frontal plane contacted a utility pole (Event 5).
V2 was eastbound on a two lane, two way street. V2 stopped in traffic for another vehicle that was stopped in traffic. V1 was also eastbound on this street. The front of V1 struck the back of V2.

Vehicle # 1 was westbound on a three lane two way roadway following Vehicle # 2. Vehicle #2 was westbound on a three lane two way roadway stopped for Vehicle # 3.  Vehicle # 3 was westbound on a three lane two way roadway stopped for crossing pedestrian.  Vehicle # 1 front end collided with Vehicle # 2 rear end.  Vehicle # 2 front end was pushed into vehicle # 3 rear end. The front of Vehicle #1 then contacted the back of Vehicle #2 for a second time.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way road. V1 swerved to avoid a deer. V1 left the road on the right side into a wide bottom ditch and rolled 4 quarter turns, ending up on its wheels.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north in the first of three lanes. Vehicle 2 and 3 were slowing for traffic ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted V2 in the rear, and the front of V2 then contacted V3 in the rear.

V1 was traveling west on a two way divided roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted a tree. V1 then started to yaw in the clockwise direction and the front of V1 impacted with a light pole. V1 continued to yaw clockwise while traveling in a northwest direction. As V1 approached an elevated culvert, the left rear wheel gouged the lip of the culvert causing V1 to roll counterclockwise. While V1 was still in the counterclockwise roll motion, the top side of V1 made impact with a tree at the first quarter turn. V1 continued traveling in a northwest direction while starting to yaw clockwise but still rolling counterclockwise. V1 came to rest upright facing southeast.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a two way four lane roadway with a center turn lane. V1 turned right (north) crossing over an east west running two way two lane roadway that runs closely adjacent. V2 was traveling west on the two way two lane roadway and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 of a 5 lane divided roadway and was turning right to travel north on a single lane on-ramp to a 4 lane divided roadway. While turning right , V1 departed the road way on the left side and struck a drain culvert with the undercarriage of the vehicle. The vehicle then traveled forward and struck an embankment with the frontal plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound in center turn lane of a two-way roadway with a left turn lane in each direction approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound in lane one on the same roadway approaching the intersection. As V1 turned to its left to travel east on the intersecting roadway the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was eastbound on a two way, two-lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where the front plane of V1 struck a tree. V1 rotated clockwise after striking the tree. The vehicle traveled back onto the roadway, crossed the left lane line, and came to final rest facing north after partially leaving the roadway on the north side.

V1 was traveling behind V2 on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, headed north. V2 slowed down, as a vehicle in front of it was slowing to make a right turn. V1 struck the rear plane of V2 with its frontal plane. V1 then departed the right side of the roadway striking an embankment, with it's front plane. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact with the embankment headed west. V2 came to rest in its original travel lane headed north.
V1 was traveling northbound on a 6 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound, turning left. V1's front contacted V2's front.

V1 was traveling north on a major highway. Driver lost directional control of the vehicle and departed the roadway to the right. V1 started to rotated clockwise. The left side impacted the posts of a cable guard rail with the front section and the rear section of the left side.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two way road with a slight decline in grade.  V2 was legally parked on the side of the road between the lane line and the sidewalk. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 rotated clockwise and came to rest across the road.  V2 came to rest on the sidewalk.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 entered the southbound lane, then departed the road to the left and entered a shallow grass roadside.V1 contacted a tree on the west road edge. V1 re-entered the roadway in a clockwise yaw and rolled over to the left an unknown number of quarter-turns.
Vehicles 1, 2 and 3 were traveling west, when the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.  V2 front then contacted the back of V3.

V1, V2, and V3 were all northbound on a two-lane roadway. V1 and V2 came to stop due to traffic. The front of V3 impacted with the rear of V2 (event 1). The front of V2 impacted with the rear of V1 (event 2). All vehicles came to final rest facing north in the original travel lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane non-divided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound on a two lane non-divided roadway.  Vehicle 1 and 2 were approaching the same intersection.  Vehicle 1's frontal plane struck the left side of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 and 2 rotated and Vehicle 2's left side struck the right side of Vehicle 1.  This caused Vehicle 1 and 2 to be re-directed and travel off the roadway into the northeast corner of the intersection.  The front of Vehicle 1 struck an embankment.  Vehicle 1 then rotated 180 degrees coming to rest on the embankment facing in a southwest direction.  The initial impacts caused Vehicle 2 to depart the right side of the roadway and travel up an embankment and become airborne.  The front of Vehicle 2 struck a small tree.  Then the front of Vehicle 2 struck a large tree and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling north and attempting a left turn into intersection. V2 was traveling east in the first lane on a three lane roadway. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 came to final rest facing north in intersection. V2 came to final rest facing east in original lane.

V1 and V2 were traveling northeast in lane one and two of a three lane non-physically divided roadway respectively. V1 departed lane to the left. The left of V1 impacted with the right side of V2. V2 came to final rest in intersection facing northeast. V1 continued traveling through the intersection, veered right onto curb then entered north bound lane of crossing roadway, traveled over double yellow line into southbound lane. V1 departed roadway and the front of V1 impacted a light pole and came to final rest at impact.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a two lane divided roadway.V1 departed the roadway on the left side. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the guardrail end. V1 rotated counterclockwise with final rest facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a curve to the left and departed the road to the right into a shallow grass ditch. V1 impacted the head wall of a culvert with the front plane, then crossed over a private driveway and impacted a small tree with the front plane.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west and Vehicle #2 was traveling east. V1 entered the eastbound lane and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two-lane, undivided roadway negotiating a curve.  V2 was traveling north on the same roadway.  The front left side of V1 contacted the front left side of V2.  V1 rotated counter clockwise briefly departing the roadway before coming to final rest on the roadway facing north.  V2 stopped and came to final rest on the roadway also facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane physically divided highway in the number 2 lane. V1 departed the roadway, began to yaw clockwise 180 degrees, finally V1 rolled 1/4 turn on to the left side coming to rest. V1 was towed. V1O1 received medical treatment.

V2 and V3 were stopped in traffic facing east at an intersection on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 was following same roadway going east. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. The front of V2 then impacted the back of V3.
V1 was traveling east through a stop sign intersection and turning left. V2 was traveling south, on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway and going straight. V2's front contacted V1's left side.

V1 was headed northbound on a one way 2 lane roadway. V1 attempted to pass  a non contact vehicle on the left and went off of the roadway. Vehicle 1 struck a tree with it's left side and then struck another tree with it's front before re-entering the roadway and coming to rest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a five lane undivided roadway attempting to turn left at an intersection.  V2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway attempting to crossover the same intersection.  The front of V1 contact the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to final rest facing south in the northbound lanes. V2 deflected to the right, departing the roadway where the front contacted a buried utility box. V2 came to final rest facing northeast just beyond the sidewalk.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way roadway with a left turn lane. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V1 traversed the center lines and entered the west travel lanes. V1's front, right corner impacted V2's right front corner, in sideswipe type impact (Event 1). V1 traversed the west and eastbound travel lanes before departing the south (right) roadside. The front of V1 impacted an embankment (Event 2) before coming to rest. V2 came to rest in it's original westbound travel lane.

V1 and V2 were traveling south in Lane 1 on a 2 lane non-physically divided roadway.  V2 and its trailer were slowing down for a non contact vehicle that was making a right hand turn.  As V2 began to accelerate once the roadway was clear and the front of V1 made contact with the rear of V2's trailer.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south in lane two on the intersecting five- lane two-way undivided roadway.  V1 turned to its left at the intersection, and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 in the intersection.  V2 then departed the southeast intersection apex and the left plane of V2 contacted a cable box.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a two-lane one way roadway and Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane 1 on an intersecting two-lane one way roadway.  As both vehicles continued straight through the intersection the front of V2 struck the front right side of V1. V1's right plane contacted V2's left plane as the vehicles rotated. V1 continued off road and the front plane contacted a utility pole.

Vehicle #1 and vehicle #2 were traveling south, vehicle #3 was stopped facing east waiting to enter the roadway from an alley. V2 stopped for traffic and the front plane of V1 struck the back plane of V2. The front plane of V2 then struck the front plane of V3.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, curved right roadway.  V1 departed the road to the left and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail end.  V1 rotated clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted 7 trees.  V1 rolled over two quarter-turns to the left and came to rest upside down.
V1 was legally parked on a two-lane, two-way unmarked road heading southeast.  V2 was traveling in the same direction. The right side of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two-lane road. V1 departed the left side of the road and impacted a chain link fence with it's front plane causing it to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 then hit several other trees with it's front plane, finally coming to rest down a slight slope.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound in the second of five lanes. The driver of V1 attempted to change lanes to the right and departed the roadway on the right side. Vehicle 1 tripped and rolled right four quarter turns coming to rest on its wheels.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection going straight; V2 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. The vehicles rotated towards each other and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in a side-slap configuration. V2 was redirected off the road on the southwest corner. The front of V2 contacted a tree.

V1 was traveling south in the right lane of a two way undivided roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V1 then departed roadway on the right side mounting the curb for approximately 16 meters. V1 then returned to the roadway on the left side traveling southwest and proceeded to cross over to the northbound side of the roadway. V1 crossed over all lanes of travel of both southbound and northbound lanes and then departed the roadway on the left side impacting the curb. The frontal plane of V1 then made impact with a Tree.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a four lane non-positively divided roadway attempting to make a left hand turn eastbound into a shopping center. Vehicle #2 was traveling north on the same four lane roadway. Vehicle #2's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #1's frontal plane.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two-way roadway. V2, V3 and V4 were all parked and unoccupied facing south on the west side curb. V1 right plane made contact with V2 and V3 left plane. and V1 front plane made contact with V4s right plane.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a four-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V1 departed its lane on the left side where the front plane of V2 struck the left side of V1. V2 then continued eastbound across the intersection where it struck a utility pole located on the north side of the roadway.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane roadway crossing through an intersection. V2 was traveling west passing thru the same intersection. The V1 front plane contacted the left side of V2.

V3, V2, and V1 were all traveling west in lane 2 of a 3 lane, two way, non divided roadway. V3 and V2 had come to a stop at an intersection. V1's frontal plane contacted the back plane of V2. Due to the impact, V2 's frontal plane then contacted the back plane of V3.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 of a 2 lane divided highway. V1 lost control on the roadway and departed the right side of the roadway in a flat skid. While rotating clockwise vehicle launched across a small creek and impacted the undercarriage on the ground creating a large gouge. V1 continued and launched across the creek again and impacted the left plane on the far, near vertical embankment.

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 of two way, non-divided roadway when it departed the roadway on the right side. V1's front plane then struck the back plane of V2, which was legally parked on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south east on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the road way. The right side of V1 contacted a tree. The front plane of V1 contacted an embankment, and V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast. A pedestrian ran across the road from the right. The front plane of V1 contacted the pedestrian.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south on the same roadway.  Vehicle #3 was stopped facing east on an intersecting roadway.  V1 began to turn left at the intersection.  The right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and the front of V1 contacted the front of V3.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west. V1 lost control and departed the road to the left. The left of V1 contacted a sign post. V1 rolled over 8 quarter turns to the left.

Vehicle #1 was going westbound on a two lane non-divided roadway entering an intersection. Vehicle #2 was going northbound on a three lane non-divided roadway entering the same intersection. Vehicle #2 contacted the left side plane of Vehicle #1 with its frontal plane.

V1 was turning right, south, onto a 4 lane divided roadway from a private business drive. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway in lane one. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 as it entered the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a 2 lane non-divided roadway when it departed the right side of the roadway and impacted a tree with the front plane.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a two way roadway and was turning left at an intersection to travel north on a 5 lane non-divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 2 of  the 5 lane non-divided roadway. At the intersection, the front plane of V1 struck the front plane of V2.

V1 was northbound on a five-lane roadway in the center turn lane. V2 was southbound on the same five-lane roadway in the second lane. Vehicle 1 and vehicle 2 were traveling east approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was stopped ahead of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2 rear plane.

V1 was traveling north bound in left turn lane on a 7 lane non physically divided roadway without a positive barrier. V1 was traveling west on a one way, two lane road, taking a south bound on ramp. V1 was towing a trailer. The truck and trailer jackknifed. V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a three lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection controlled by traffic signals. V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane, of a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane, of a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane, undivided roadway. V2 was parked facing eastbound on the right side of road.  The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1, V2, and V3 were traveling south on a three-lane divided highway approaching an intersection. V3 was in front of V2 in lane three which is a left turn only lane. V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road approaching the same intersection ascending a prominent incline. V1 was traveling south, taking a left turn at an intersection controlled by traffic lights on a three-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling north through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed roadway to the right, traveled over grassy area, sidewalk, and into a private yard. The front of V1 then impacted with a building where it came to final rest.
Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling southeast approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's left plane.

V1 was traveling southeast in lane 2 on a four lane physically divided roadway when V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 continued to rotate and the front of V1 struck the concrete barrier.  V1 came to rest on side of roadway.

V1 was turning right from a two lane, 2 way, undivided roadway, facing north. V2 was traveling eastbound on a 3 lane, one-way roadway. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a three lane, one way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling west on a five lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on the same five lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a two way two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve to its left. V1 then departed the roadway on the right side and contacted two trees with its right side. V1 drove off the right side of the roadway and impacted 2 trees with the front plane and then a tree impacted the undercarriage.
V1 was traveling south in lane 1 of an 8 lane divided highway. A deer was in the path of V1 and was impacted by the front plane.

V1 was traveling east, backing onto a two way two lane undivided roadway from a private driveway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. V1 was traveling south in lane two of four on a divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane two on a three lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crested a hill and and there was a deer in its travel lane. Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound in lane one of an adjacent access road approaching an intersection to attempt to turn left. Vehicle #1 was traveling south bound. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front bumper impacted two fence posts.

V1 was traveling north in the first lane on a 3 lane, two way, non- physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in the second lane on a three lane non-physically divided roadway. V2 rotated clockwise and came to a final rest facing north in the intersection .V1 came to final rest in the original lane facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a 3-lane divided highway in lane 2.  V1 rotated clockwise as it crossed the lanes to the right then departed the right road edge. V1 was traveling west on two-way, two lane road. V1 left its original travel lane on the left and departed the roadway on the left. V1 went down an embankment and the front of V1 impacted an embankment and a small tree in the embankment.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south attempting a left turn from private drive to head east. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in the #3 lane of 5 lane divided roadway, attempting a left turn into a private drive.  Vehicle 1 front made contact with Vehicle 2 right side.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling north on a one-way 3 lane roadway exiting the freeway in the number 2 lane. Vehicle 2 was stopped for traffic. Vehicle 1's front and Vehicle 2's back end made contact with each other.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east in the number 3 lane of a 6 lane divided highway and Vehicle #2 was stopped, ahead of V1.  The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling NE, leaving a parking lot. Vehicle #2 was traveling SE. V1 exited the parking lot and began to turn left. V2 entered the two-way left turn lane in preparation to turn left into another parking lot. The front of V1 contacted the right of V2.

Vehicles #1, 2, 3 and 4 were all traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway. V2, V3, and V4 stopped for traffic. The front plane of V1 struck the back plane of V2. The front plane of V2 struck the back plane of V3. The front plane of V3 struck the back plane of V4.

V1 continued east whilst yawing counter-clockwise and the left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V3. V1 then caught fire.

V1 was traveling eastbound, approaching an intersection, in the left turning lane of a two-way, 5 lane road. V1 was attempting to make a left turn to go northbound on a two-way, two lane road. V2 was traveling westbound on the same roadway, approaching the intersection, in the second travel lane. At the above intersection, the frontal plane of V1 made impact with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the #2 lane of a 5 lane roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the #1 lane of a 2 lane intersecting roadway. V1 was traveling eastbound on a 5 lane interstate in the number 4 lane. V1 then fell over and rolled for 4 quarter turns before coming to rest on its wheels facing northwest.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound. Vehicle #2 was traveling east bound in the same lane. V1 contacted the front bumper on the back bumper of V2.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were eastbound on the interstate. V2 and V3 were decelerating and V4 was stopped for traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. V2 came to final rest at the second point of impact. V3 came to final rest at its second point of impact. V4 came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was westbound on an undivided four lane roadway.  V1 exiting out of the left curve, departed the roadway to the right and the front impacted a concrete wall (event 1). The rollover was interrupted when V1 made contact with the traffic sign (event 3), displacing it from its base, and an utility pole (event 4) with its right side. V1 came to final rest on its top facing a northwest position partially in the curb lane of travel.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west, in lane number three, approaching a traffic signal controlled four-way intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east, in lane number one, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left; V2 entered the intersection going straight, and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was travelling east in the second lane. V1 departed lane to the right and then departed roadway to the right before impacting the front of vehicle with a traffic light pole. V1 rotated slightly left and came to final rest in front of the traffic light pole, facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast approaching Vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 was unoccupied and legally parked next to the right road edge. Vehicle 1 departed it's travel lane to the right and the front plane contacted the rear plane of Vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling ahead of V2 westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was approaching a crosswalk with a crossing guard stopping traffic. V2 stopped and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling NE, approaching a T-intersection. V1 began to turn left, lost control, and departed the road to the right. The front plane of V1 contacted a fiberglass road edge reflector. V1 traveled down an embankment, and the undercarriage of V1 contacted the embankment. The right plane of V1 contacted the embankment.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north and departed the roadway to the left. The front plane of V1 struck a pole, then a fence. V1 re-entered the roadway and departed it to the right.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east and departed the road on the left side. The front plane of V1 struck a guy wire and a tree.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 was stopped, facing south on the same roadway ahead of V1.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling north while negotiating a curve right on a rural two-lane road when it departed the left (west) side of the roadway. The front of V1 struck three different mailbox posts (events 1, 2, 3). V1 continued to travel north on the roadside when it struck a tree with its front (event 4) and impacted a utility pole with an unknown plane (event 5). V1 finally struck a tree with its front end (event 6) and came to final rest.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the third lane of a four lane roadway.  V2 was traveling southbound in the right lane of the intersecting two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, as V2 was making a left turn, the frontal plane of V1 made impact with the right plane of V2. After the first impact, V2 started to yaw clockwise and the left rear wheel made impact with the curb.

V1 was traveling westbound in the middle lane of a two-way, seven lane roadway. V2 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in the right lane. V3 was traveling in the same direction on the same roadway in front of V2. As V3 crossed through the intersection, the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the rear plane of V3. V2 then went into the middle lane, and the left plane of V2 made contact with the right back trailer of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southwest in lane 2 of a 3 lane roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling northwest in lane 3 of a 4 lane intersecting roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southerly in lane No. 2 of a divided, six-lane roadway (four north lanes and two south lanes with a curbed center median). The driver of Vehicle #1 was traveling northerly in lane No. 4 of the divided seven-lane roadway and turned left at the intersection. The front of Vehicle #1 impacted the right side plane of Vehicle #2.

V2 was stopped (due to traffic ahead) on the Interstate in lane 2 (of two lanes) and was facing a southerly direction.  V1 was traveling south in the same lane and was approaching V2.  The front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2.

V1 was traveling east on the Interstate in lane 1 (of five lanes) and was to the rear of V2, which was also traveling east in the same lane. V2 stopped (due to traffic ahead), and the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2.
V1 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the lanes on the left and contacted an electrical box with the front.

V2 stopped on red light a significant distance from the intersection. V1 was traveling in the same direction at a higher rate of speed. The front end of V1 made contact with the rear end of V2. D1 of V1 was transported by EMT from the scene. V1 was towed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was stopped prior to the intersection facing west in the same lane ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left; V2 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V1 and V2 were westbound on a one-lane highway on-ramp.  At the end of the ramp, V2 slowed to yield for traffic in the travel lane the ramp was merging into.  The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was southbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 RR tire blew out causing a loss of control that resulted in V1 departing its travel lane to the left (east) and departing the left side of the roadway in a counter-clockwise yaw. V1 then overturned right side leading. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast and was experiencing transmission problems. Vehicle 2, a medium/heavy truck, was also traveling northeast behind Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1's rear plane was contacted by Vehicle 2's front plane.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling west on the same road.  V2 turned left into a driveway.  The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2 causing V2 to rotate clock-wise.  The front of V1 then impacted a split rail fence.

V1 was traveling east on a level two-lane, two-way road. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the same road. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 continued off of the right side of the road and struck a utility pole with its front plane.
V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound in the same lane of a five-lane divided highway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1, V2, and V3 were stopped in a long line of traffic on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway headed south. V4 was traveling south on the same roadway and the front plane of V4 struck the rear plane of V3. The front plane of V3 then struck the rear plane of V2. The front plane of V2 then struck the rear plane of V1. All 4 vehicles came to final rest headed south near the points of impact.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, two-lane roadway pulling a trailer.  V1 went off the right side of the roadway, re-entered the road then departed the left side of the road while rotating counter-clockwise where the lower front plane contacted an embankment.  During the crash, the trailer jackknifed and contacted the left side of the bed of V1.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way road. V1 rotated counter clockwise, crossed over the left road edge and impacted a concrete culvert head-wall with the right front wheel. V1 then overturned striking the interior upper perimeter of the concrete head-wall and dropped approximately 3 meters onto its top in a water filled creek.

Vehicle # 1 was eastbound on a two-lane, two-way roadway.  Vehicle # 1 departed the roadway to the right.  Vehicle # 1 corrected back to the left, crossing both lanes of travel.  Vehicle # 1 departed the roadway to the left and struck a dirt embankment.  Vehicle # 1 rolled 4-quarter turns coming to rest on its wheels.

Vehicle # 1 was eastbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  Vehicle # 1 traveled off the road to the right. Vehicle # 1 steered back left re-entering the roadway.  Vehicle # 1 steered back right, and rotated clock-wise off the road to the right, striking a plastic reflective post, and rolling 4 quarter turns.

V1 was traveling east on a six lane, two way median divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right into an interchange area that was filled with standing water.  V1 became partially submerged and came to final rest off of the roadway.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway approaching a stopped school bus. V2 was stopped on a two lane two way roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 and V2 were northbound on a three lane roadway in the right lane. The center and far left lane were closed due to construction. V1 came to a stop due to traffic. The front of V2 collided with the back of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was southbound approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was westbound approaching the same intersection. V1 initiated a left turn as both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped at the intersection, facing south. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 started to rotate counter clockwise and moved towards the northwest corner of the intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V3. V1 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the northwest. The front of V1 impacted a wall located in the northwest corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling on a 2 lane undivided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the left side engaging in a series of events.  V1 made contact with a bush (1), rock steps (2), and another bush (3).  V1 continued traveling across a yard, crossing an alley, driving through a wooden fence (4), striking the ground (5) and coming to final rest by hitting a house (6).  V1 was towed from the scene.  Both the driver and passenger fled the scene.

V1 (NCV) was turning left out of a private drive. V2 was southbound on a five lane two-way roadway.  V1 entered into the southbound lanes. V2 steered to the right and braked in an avoidance maneuver.  V2 crossed over the right lane, over the curb, and the front of V2 impacted a utility pole. V2 came to final rest at the point of impact. V1 continued southbound out of the area.

V1, V2, and V3 were westbound on a five lane one way roadway. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 was propelled forward, and the front of V2 collided with the rear of V3.

V1 was westbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left continuing off the left side of the roadway. V1 entered a ditch striking the bottom of the ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 then overturned left side leading 1 quarter turn and came to rest at the point of impact on its left side facing west.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a three lane undivided roadway.  V2 was exiting from a private drive. The front of V2 impacted with the right of V1. V1 rotated clockwise before coming to final rest. V2 rolled forward slightly after impact where it came to final rest.
V1 was traveling southbound in lane 2 of a 3 lane roadway. V1 lost control and exited the roadway to the left before hitting a tree with it's left side and coming to rest.
V1 and V2 were heading in the same general northerly direction on a one way roadway. V2's front contacted V1's right side.
V1 was traveling southbound on a four-lane, two-way road in lane one. A deer crossed the road in front of V1. The front of V1 impacted the deer.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest in lane three of a five-lane roadway approaching a three-leg intersection. The driver of V1 attempted a left turn at the intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast in lane 1 of the same roadway and was approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1s front plane contacted Vehicle 2s front plane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north approaching an intersection attempting a left turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast stopped at the same intersection waiting to turn left. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's front plane.
V1 was westbound on a two lane, two- way road. V2 was northbound on a two lane, two-way intersecting road. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was going eastbound on a nine lane non-positively median divided roadway entering an intersection. Vehicle #2 was going westbound on the same roadway turning left at the intersection. Vehicle #1 front  contacted the right side plane of Vehicle #2.

V1 was west bound on a two lane non divided roadway. V2, which was towing a trailer, was stopped in the west bound lane of travel, to let traffic pass so that it could turn left into a parking lot. V1's frontal plane impacted the rear plane of the towed trailer. V1 then rotated counterclockwise, departing the roadway to the right where it impacted the embankment with its right plane. V1's frontal plane then impacted the right plane of V2 before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling north toward a four-way intersection and V2 was traveling south toward the same intersection. V1 initiated a left turn as both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. Subsequently, the right side of V1 slapped the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling west in the first lane on a four lane  physically divided roadway.  V1 departed roadway to the right, the front of V1 impacted with a speed limit sign (event 1). The front of V1 then impacted with two trees (events 2 and 3). V1 continued north bound impacted the front of vehicle with a fence (event 4),  traveled through the fence, up an embankment impacting the front of vehicle with the embankment (event 5), and another fence (event 6). V1 then traveled onto an under pass ramp where the front of vehicle impacted with a bridge abutment (event 7). V1 then proceeded to slide down the underpass ramp left side leading. V1 came to a final rest facing west against bridge supports.

V1 was negotiating a curve traveling northbound to westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was negotiating a curve traveling northbound to westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway behind V1. V1 stopped and reversed in the lane. The back plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2.

Vehicle #1 was making a left turn southbound in the intersection of an 8 lane, non-positively divided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway. Vehicle #2's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #1's frontal plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a two way, non-positively divided roadway. Vehicle departed the roadway to the right and contacted a mailbox with it's frontal plane and then continued traveling forward and contacting a drain pipe with its front. V1 continued forward and contacted a tree with its frontal plane before coming to final rest.

Vehicles #1 and #2 ,were traveling eastbound in lane 2 of a 4 lane non-positive median divided roadway. Vehicle #1 contacted the back plane of Vehicle #2 with its' frontal plane. After this event, Vehicle #1 continued on contacting a guard rail with its frontal plane and a second contact with its right side plane.

V1 was traveling east on a 3 lane non-divided roadway, approaching a stop sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling south on a 6 lane divided roadway. As V1 turned left to travel north the front plane of V2 impacted the left plane of V1. After the initial impact, the right plane of V2  then impacted the left plane of V1

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling north on a four-lane, two-way roadway, approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north around a left curve. V1 departed the road to the right and the front plane of V1 contacted a fiberglass road edge reflector. V1 re-entered the road, overcorrected to the right, and began to rotate clockwise. V1 departed the road to the right and the right plane of V1 contacted a fence. V1 tripped over and rolled four quarter turns to the left. During the rollover, the top plane, then the undercarriage of V1 contacted trees.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the road to the right and the front plane of V1 contacted a guardrail.

V1 was traveling southbound in lane one of a a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. As V1 crossed the intersection, it departed the roadway on the right side and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with a utility pole.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west on an intersecting roadway.  V1 began to turn right into the same path as V2 and the left of V1 contacted the right of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, in the fourth of four lanes and Vehicle 2 was traveling north, in the third of four lanes. V1 attempted to change lanes to the right. The right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated counterclockwise and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two way two lane roadway negotiating a curve to the left.  Vehicle 1 lost control left the roadway to the right, steered left and then steered back to the right.  Vehicle 1 began rotating clockwise leaving the roadway to the right.  Vehicle 1 struck an embankment with its front end.  Vehicle 1 continued its clockwise rotation with the left front side and back end impacting the embankment.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way two lane roadway turning left, eastbound, onto a five lane two way roadway.  Vehicle 2 was westbound on five lane two way roadway in lane two.  Vehicle 2 front contacted the left side of vehicle 1 in the westbound lane two.

V1 was traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 1 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2, which was ahead in the same lane at a lower steady speed.  The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2, causing V2 to depart the roadway on the left and overturn (4 quarter turns, leading left).

V3 was traveling west on an interstate (physically divided with positive barrier) in lane 4 (of 5 lanes). V1 and V2 were traveling behind V3 (also in lane 4) with V1 behind V2. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V1 then continued traveling westbound, and the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V3.

V1 was traveling east on a two-way not physically divided roadway in lane 1 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2, which was on the same roadway traveling west in lane 1 (of two lanes).  V1 was turned to the left and into the path of V2, and the front end of V1 came into contact with the front end of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north around a right curve. V1 departed the road to the right and overcorrected to the left. It re-entered the road, rotating clockwise, then departed it to the left. The left plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and the left plane contacted another tree. A limb from the contacted trees fell over the vehicle and caused light damage to the right side of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west. V1 departed the road to the right and began to slide down a steep hill. The right plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 rolled an unknown number of quarter turns to the right. V1 contacted at least three trees with unknown planes. During the rollover, two occupants were ejected in an unknown manner. V1 came to rest on its right side.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in the number 2 lane of a 4-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and sustained a front to unknown plane impact with Vehicle #2, which was legally parked in a parking lane off the north edge of the travel lanes. After impact to V2, V1 crossed a sidewalk into a parking lot and the front plane impacted two sign posts and then a low block wall.

V1 was traveling south on a two-way, two lane road. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left and went on to depart the roadway on the left. V1's left plane impacted a small tree. The front of V1 impacted a larger tree causing V1 to spin counterclockwise and come to final rest facing east.

V1 was traveling west on a 4 lane, 2 way roadway, divided by a grass median with a cable barrier guardrail. V1 hydroplaned and entered into a counter clockwise yaw. V1 departed the left side of the roadway striking the cable barrier guardrail and came to final rest on the north side of cable guardrail heading north east.

V1 was traveling south west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south east on a two lane, two way, undivided road way approaching the same intersection. V1 crossed the intersection, crossing the path of V2. The front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was west bound on a two lane, non divided roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right and impacted the bottom of a ditch with its frontal plane. V1 then rolled over, left side leading, 5 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its left side.

Vehicle 1 and 2 were traveling south on a two-way physically divided roadway in the number 4 lane. Vehicle 3 was traveling south on the same roadway in the number 3 lane. Vehicle 1's front made contact with Vehicle 2's back then Vehicle 2's front to made contact with Vehicle 3's rear. All vehicles maintained a southerly direction for final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way street coming to a stop at a T-intersection.  V2 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road.  V1 attempted a left hand turn onto the same street as V2 in the opposite direction.  The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was westbound on a five-lane divided roadway approaching a four-way intersection. V2 was traveling east toward the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection as V1 initiated a left turn. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a four-lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2, V3, V5 were traveling north on a four-lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection. V4 was traveling west on a private parking lot approaching the same intersection. V1 departed the right (south) roadside and the left side contacted a traffic signal control box (Event 1).  The left rear tire and rim impacted a traffic signal pole (Event 2) prior to V1 entering the adjoining north/south roadway. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 (Event 3). The right side of V2 contacted the left side of V3 (Event 4). The right fender of V3 contacted the left side of V4 (Event 5). The front of V5 contacted the right side of V3 (Event 6). The front of V3 impacted the left side of V4 in a secondary impact (Event 7) and the left side of V4 contacted the left side of V1 (Event 8).

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a two lane, one way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling southbound in the left lane on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction approaching a westbound "T" intersection. V2 was traveling northbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, as V1 was making a left turn, the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the right plane of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a curve to the left and Vehicle #2 was traveling south, negotiating a curve to the right. V1 sustained a control loss on the wet road surface, rotated counter-clockwise and entered the southbound lane. The right plane of V1 impacted the front plane of V2. After impact to V1, V2 departed the road to the right and impacted a fence and a tree with the back plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane 2, overtaking vehicle #2. V2 was traveling north in lane 1. V1 began to change lanes to the right, and V2 steered sharply right attempting to avoid a crash and began rotating clockwise. The right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. Both vehicles departed the road. The left side of V2 contacted a tree. The front end of V1 contacted a tree and then a barbed wire fence.

Vehicle #1 was traveling SW and vehicle #2 was traveling NW. Both vehicles entered an intersection, and the front plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1. Both vehicles rotated sharply and the right plane of V2 contacted the left plane of V1.
V1 was traveling west on a three lane undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a deer.  V1 came to final rest near point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the southbound lane on the right hand side striking a tree with its frontal plane.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the westbound travel lane into the opposing eastbound travel lane and then departed the southern road edge. V1 struck a sign and two trees with its frontal plane before overturning. V1 rolled 2-quarter turns coming to rest on its roof.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane road way approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on a 4 lane divided roadway in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling south in reverse on an undivided two lane roadway. V2,V3,V4 were all parked legally on the street facing north. V1 impacted V2,V3, and V4 with an unknown plane. V1 came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane two of three on a two-way street passing through an intersection. V2 traveling west in lane one of three on a two-way street passing through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2 causing both to rotate clock-wise.  V1 came to rest in the road while the front of V2 impacted a utility pole and the left side impacted a curb.

V1 was traveling southeast in the first lane on a two way non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling northeast in the first lane on a two lane non-physically divided roadway. Both vehicles entered intersection. The front of V2 impacted with the right side of V1 (event 1). The impact forced V1 to roll over onto it's left side (event 2) , where it came to final rest. V2 came to final rest facing northeast.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway and was approaching a right curve in the road. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway and was approaching a left curve in the road. While negotiating the curve in the roadway, V1 's left side plane contacted the front plane of V2.     V1 then departed the roadway on the right side.  The undercarriage of V1 struck an embankment.  V1 then returned back to the roadway before coming to final rest approx. 100 meters  from the impact site.
V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right, where it impacted a tree with its frontal plane.
V1 was traveling east on a two way two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway. The left side of V1 contacted a tree before coming to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was southbound on a two lane non-divided roadway. V1 was traveling northbound on the same two lane divided roadway. V1 looked but did not see V2 and attempted a left hand turn in front of V2. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 came to rest on the shoulder of the northbound lane. V1 came to rest facing south in the northbound lane. Both vehicles were towed and all occupants were transported by EMS.

V1 was westbound on a 2 lane roadway. V1 lost control of the vehicle and exited the roadway to the right. V1 rotated clockwise and then tripped over rolling 4 quarter turns (event 1). V1 continued to rotate clockwise while rolling. V1 came to final rest after the rear of the vehicle impacted a fence (event 2) and tree (event 3).

V1 was traveling northbound in lane 2 of a 5 lane, 2-way turn lane divided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the left and the front of V1 contacted a curb then a tree.  V1 then rotated counterclockwise where the left rear tire impacted a curb and then the left side contact a tree.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane, 2-way, undivided roadway, attempting to turn left at an intersection.  V2 was traveling eastbound in lane 1 of a not physically divided roadway, attempting to crossover the same intersection.  The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After initial contact, the front of V1 contacted the right rear wheel area of V2.  Both vehicle came to rest within the intersection.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a curve to the right and noticed a non-contact, oncoming vehicle entering the northbound lane. V1 steered to the left, entered the southbound lane, then departed the road to the left and impacted a large tree with the front plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a 5 lane, positively divided roadway making a left turn within the intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling southbound within the same intersection. Vehicle #2 frontal plane contacted the frontal plane of Vehicle #1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way, undivided roadway and contacted an animal in the roadway with its frontal plane. Vehicle #2 was traveling south on the same roadway and contacted the same animal within its travel lane with its frontal plane. Vehicle #3 was traveling north behind V1 and braked to avoid contact. V4 was traveling north behind V3. The front of V4 contacted the rear of V3.

V2 was traveling west in lane 1 of  a 2 lane non-divided roadway. V1 was traveling east initially in lane one on the same roadway. The front plane of V1 impacted the front plane of V2 in the westbound travel lane.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two way, roadway when the vehicle departed the right side of the roadway. After departing the roadway, the vehicle entered a drainage ditch area and the undercarriage of the vehicle struck a metal drain pipe that ran under a private driveway. The vehicle then returned to the roadway, veered to the right, departed the roadway again on the right side and struck a tree with the frontal plane. The vehicle then rolled over 1 quarter turn onto its left side plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling southwest on a 2 lane non-divided roadway. V2 was traveling east on an intersecting 2 lane non-divided roadway, approaching a stop sign controlled intersection with V1's through roadway. V2 turned left at the intersection and the front plane of V1 impacted the front plane of V2.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane undivided roadway when it departed the roadway on the left side and the front plane struck a tree.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane divided traffic way roadway. V2 was traveling east, stopped in the travel lane, attempting to make a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V3 was traveling west on the same roadway.  After initial impact, V2 continued east where it's front plane made contact with the left side of V3.

V1 was traveling eastbound approaching a four-way intersection, V2 was traveling southbound crossing through the intersection. The front plane of V1 struck the right plane of V2. After initial impact V2 departed the roadway on the east side where it struck a small pole.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 4 lane non physically divided roadway and entered into an interchange/intersection area. V1 departed the roadway to the left, crossed a northbound off-ramp lane and then vaulted off the roadway embankment and rolled end over end landing on its top.

V1 was northbound on a six-lane roadway. V2 was southbound on the same roadway. V2 merged into the left turn lane and proceeded to make a left turn across the northbound traffic lanes. The front of V2 impacted the front of V1.

V1 was southbound on a two-lane oneway roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was eastbound on a three-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The front of V1 impacted the left of V2. V1 came to final rest facing southeast on the two-lane roadway. V2 rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest in the northern most lane of the three-lane roadway facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 lost control and departed the right side of the road.  Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise, traveled down an embankment and struck a tree with it's left side.  Vehicle 1 then turned over 2 quarter turns, coming to final rest on it's top.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection going straight; V2 entered the intersection turning left. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west and the vehicle departed the road to the left. The front plane contacted a rocky embankment.

V1 was starting in an intersection from a two-way, two lane, private road. V2 was traveling south following a two way, two lane roadway. At the intersection above, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 (of two lanes) on a divided traffic way (median strip without positive barrier) and was approaching V2, which was also traveling east in lane 1 at a lower steady speed. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway on the right where it overturned (8 quarter turns, leading left). V1 also departed the roadway on the right, where it rotated counterclockwise and overturned (5 quarter turns, leading right). During the rollover, V1's top contacted an earthen embankment, and its right side contacted a sign post.

V1 was traveling south through an intersection (in lane 2 of seven lanes; on a two-way, not physically divided roadway). V2 was making a left turn through the same intersection, traveling from north to west (from lane 3 of five lanes; on a two-way, not physically divided roadway). In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane undivided roadway while V2 was traveling southbound on a 2 lane undivided roadway. In the intersection, the front of V1 made contact with the left side front of V2. The two vehicles rotated together slapping the right side of V1 and the left side of V2. V2 rolled up an adjacent curb coming to final rest.

V1 was southbound in lane two on a four lane divided roadway. V2 was westbound in lane one on a four lane undivided roadway. V3 was eastbound on a three lane undivided roadway in lane one. V4 was eastbound on a four lane undivided roadway in the first lane from the right. The front of V1 impacted with the right of V2 (event 1). V2 went southeast and the front of V2 impacted with the front of V2 (event 2). V1 also went southeast where the front of V1 impacted with the front of V3 (event 3). V1 and V2 came to final rest at the their second point of impact. V3 and V4 came to final rest at their first point of impact.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. As V1 made a left turn onto the intersecting two lane roadway V1 departed the right side of the roadway. The right front wheel of V1 contacted a raised cement curb. V1 continued to travel off the roadway in an easterly direction across a grass covered area, sidewalk, and residential driveway before returning to the roadway. As V1 traveled along the sidewalk the right front wheel contacted a section concrete lawn edging. Upon returning to the road V1 traveled in a northeasterly direction came to final rest facing northeast in the westbound lane of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane road. The vehicle traveled over the lane line to the left and departed the roadway on the left side. The front corner of V1 impacted a tree and continued forward where the front impacted a second tree. V1 came to final rest facing southeast partially in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a 3 lane non-divided road way.  V1 departed the roadway on right side.  The front of V1 contacted a sign post then the corner of a building. V1 then contacted a utility pole with its front plane where V1 came to rest.

V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane, two-way roadway.  V2 was traveling east on the intersecting 2-lane, one-way roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling northbound about to enter an intersection. A bicycle was traveling west when it came in contact with the right side of V1 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling east bound on a two lane, non divided roadway. V1 left the roadway to the right, where it's frontal plane impacted a guardrail end. V1 then impacted a ditch with its right plane, and then impacted an embankment with its back plane before coming to final rest.
