V1 was traveling north west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north west on the same roadway. V2 stopped in the roadway to make a left hand turn. V1's frontal plane contacted the back plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on an access road. V1 made contact with low hanging wires, which pulled the wires and broke a pole. The wires then fell across a six lane physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway and the wires from the broken pole made contact with V2 windshield and hood.
V1 was northbound on a 3 lane roadway in the number 3 lane. A deer entered the roadway from the right. The front of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to final rest shortly after impact.

V1 and V2, towing a trailer, were both traveling southbound on a two lane divided highway. V1 was in the number two lane and V2 was in the number one lane. V1 drifted into lane 1 and the front of V1 struck the rear of V2's trailer. V2 then started to yaw counter-clockwise when the trailer rolled one quarter turn to the right coming to rest. V2 did not roll. V1 drove off the roadway to the left and came to rest. V1 was towed. V2's trailer was towed. V2 was not towed.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 and V2 entered the intersection, the left plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. V2 came to final rest on the road way, and V1 came to final rest off the road way.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 crossed the left lane line and went off the west side of the roadway making contact with several trees on the front, left and right planes. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 rotated counter clockwise and V1 rotated clockwise. Both vehicles impacted each other in a side slap impact. V1 continued to move north and departed the intersection to the northeast. The undercarriage of V1 impacted a concrete culvert.

V1 was traveling south, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left into the eastbound lanes. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling south in a private lot. V2 was traveling west in the second lane on a five lane physically divided roadway. V1 began turning left and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V2 rotated slightly clockwise and came to final rest facing northwest in the intersection. V1 came to final rest in intersection facing southwest.
V1 and V2 were traveling south in the left lane on a three lane, divided highway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in their original lane facing south.

All vehicles were headed northbound in a one way, 4 lane interstate. V1, V4 and V5 were all in lane 1. V1's front contacted V4's back. V4's front then contacted V5's rear. V1 moved forward and over the lane line to the left into lane 2 where V2 and V3 were. V1's left side contacted V2's right side. V2 rotated clockwise into lane 3 and it's front end contacted V3's left side. V2 continued to rotate counterclockwise and was struck on it's left side by V3's front. V2 then rolled over onto it's right side.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west, negotiating a right hand curve on a two lane undivided roadway and Vehicle #2 was traveling east negotiating a left hand curve. V1 entered the eastbound lane and the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.  V2 then contacted an unknown object with the right rear wheel before coming to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-way not physically divided trafficway in the number 2 lane approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling north approaching the same intersection in the left hand turn lane. Vehicle 1's front  and Vehicle 2's right made contact with each other in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling north on a two-way physically divided roadway in the number 1 lane. Vehicle 2 was stopped prior to the crash, for congested traffic. Vehicle 1's front made contact with Vehicle 2's rear.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane #3 of a 6-lane highway and sustained a control loss following a right rear tire blowout. V1 crossed over the adjacent lanes to the left, departed the road to the left and impacted a concrete median wall with the front plane. After the frontal impact to the wall, V1 rotated counter-clockwise and recontacted the wall with the right plane.

V2 was traveling north on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane 1 (of two lanes). V1 was entering the same roadway from the shoulder (a former roadway now closed to through travel) and was turning right from west to north. In the roadway, V2 sideswiped the left side of V1. V1 departed the roadway on the right, where its front/right wheel and tire came into contact with a curb, and then its front end came into contact with a post. V2 also departed the roadway on the right, where its front/right wheel and tire came into contact with a curb, and then it overturned (3 quarter turns; leading left) as it descended into a ditch/culvert.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way not physically divided roadway in lane 1 when it departed the roadway on the left, contacted a utility pole with its front end and a fence with its top as it overturned (2 quarter turns, leading left).

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, 5 lane, not physically divided roadway in lane 2.  V2 was entering the roadway from a driveway, turning left and traveling from southbound to eastbound.  In the roadway, the front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the #1 lane of a 5 lane road with two way left turn lane. V2 previously turned right onto the same  5 lane road. V2 was traveling in the #1 lane while accelerating. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 traveled to the right off the road and the front of V1 impacted a wall where it came to rest. V2 was spun around counter clockwise and came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a 2-lane road in the number 1 lane.  V2 was parked facing east on the same 2-lane road, partially blocking the travel lane. V3 was traveling west on the same 2-lane road in the number 1 lane. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.  After the initial collision, V1 departed the travel lane on the left and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V3.  V3 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing eastbound on the north shoulder.  V1 came to rest in the middle of the road blocking the number 1 and number 2 lane.  V2 came to rest on the eastbound shoulder.

V1 was traveling southeast in the first lane on a two way non-physically divided roadway and entered into the two way left turn lane. V2 was traveling northwest in the first lane. V1 attempted to turn left into a private drive. The front of V2 impacted with the right side of V1. V2 came to final rest in its original lane facing northwest. V1 came to final rest facing north.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four lane two way roadway divided by a grass median. V1 was coming towards a construction zone with the left lane closed. V1 attempted to pass in the left lane and struck 12 construction arrow markers and two traffic barrels with the front end causing damage. V1 continued into the right lane coming to final rest in the right lane facing east.

V1 was westbound on a two lane two way undivided road. V2 was eastbound on the same road. V1 departed its lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2 causing damage. Upon impact V1 rotated clockwise coming to final rest on the north side of the roadway facing north east. V2 continued eastward coming to final rest on the south side of the road.

The collision occurred within a four way intersection in which each leg of the intersection is comprised of one lane traveling away form the intersection and two lanes entering the intersection. The lanes entering the intersection are comprised of a dedicated right turn lane and a lane for left turns or straight travel through the intersection. V1 was making a left turn from the northbound leg into the westbound leg while V2 was traveling south across the intersection and V3 was stopped facing eastbound right turn lane.The front of V2 collided with the right side of V1.  V1 continued west, and the front of V1 collided with the front of V3.

Vehicle #1 was at an intersection of a 3 lane, non-positively divided roadway attempting to make a left turn. Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the intersecting 3 lane not-physically divided roadway approaching the intersection. Vehicle 2's frontal plane contacted the left side plane of Vehicle 1.

Vehicle #1 was going northbound on a six lane positively divided roadway. Vehicle #1 departed initial travel lanes to the right and contacted an off road object, with its frontal plane. Vehicle #1 returned to the roadway crossing over all travel lanes and departed the roadway left contacting an off road object with its back plane. Vehicle #1 reentered the roadway and was contacted by the front plane of Vehicle #2 on its right side plane. Vehicle #1 was contacted on the right side plane by Vehicle #3 's frontal plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling eastbound making a left turn out of a parking lot onto a a four lane, non-positively divided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling southbound on the same 4 lane roadway approaching the intersection. Vehicle 1's frontal plane contacted vehicle 2's frontal plane. V1 rotated clockwise, and V1 front contacted V2 right side.

V1 was traveling east using an exit ramp making a left turn to travel north. V2 crossed through an intersection and was traveling south on the intersecting three lane roadway. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 as V1 turned to its left.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane not physically divided roadway making a left turn. V2 was traveling north approaching the intersection. The front plane of V2 contacted the right side of V1. After the initial impact V1 rotated and departed the northwest corner of the roadway contacting a sign post with its right side.

V1 was traveling westbound attempting to pass through an intersection, V2 was traveling north approaching the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 in the center of the intersection.

V2 was traveling east in lane 1 down a 2 way non-divided entrance ramp to merge left onto a 2 lane divided roadway.  V1 was traveling in the same lane in the same direction. V2 was slowing and the front plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

V2 was traveling west in lane 2 of a 2 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling west on the same roadway in Lane 2 behind V2. As V2 slowed in it's travel lane, V1's frontal plane struck the rear plane of V2. The impact caused V2 to rotate in a counter clockwise direction and it's frontal plane then struck the side of a concrete bridge/guard rail before coming to final rest.

V1, V2, & V3 were traveling west in Lane 2 of a 2 lane divided roadway. V3 and V2 had stopped in their lane due to traffic when the frontal plane of V1 struck the back plane of V2. Due to the impact, V2's frontal plane then struck the rear plane of V3.

V1 was traveling north west on a two lane two way undivided road way, V2 was traveling south east the same road way. The front right corner of V1 contacted the front right corner of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the road way.

V2 was east bound on a two lane non divided roadway passing through an intersection. V1 was crossing through the intersection turning left to travel west bound. V1's trailer left side impacted V2's frontal plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound. V1 departed the lane on the left side and then departed the roadway on the left while rotating counter-clockwise and contacted the right side on a tree. V1 rolled on it's right side seven quarter turns and contacted three trees.

V1 was traveling north east on a two lane one way highway. V1 departed the left side of the road way contacting a bush or tree on the right side then striking a tree with the front plane. V1 came to final rest off the road way.

V1 was westbound on 5 lane roadway. The driver of V1 had a medical episode resulting in loss of control of V1. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted the guardrail face. V1 then rotated clockwise, 180 degrees, went through a parking lot, up a hill, and came to final rest after the front of V1 impacted the bucket of a tractor.

V1 was northbound in lane 2 of a 4-lane 2-way roadway. V2 was southbound in lane 1 of the same 4-lane roadway. V1 entered the intersection and started to turn left. V2 entered in the intersection at the same time. The right of V1 impacted the front of V2 (event 1). Then V1 rotated counter-clockwise as V2 rotated clockwise. The right of V1 impacted the left side of V2 (event 2). V1 came to final rest facing south on the intersecting roadway. V2 came to final rest facing west on the same intersecting roadway.

V1 was traveling north and V2 was east toward the same four-way intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. Subsequently, V2 departed the northeast quadrant of the intersection and impacted a steel pipe fence.

V1 was traveling northwest in the third lane on a five lane non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling southeast. V1 traveled into intersection turning left. V2 continued straight on the same intersection. The front of V2 impacted with the right side of V1. The impact forced V1 to rollover onto the left side, where it came to final rest. V2 came to final rest in the intersection facing southeast.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 4 lane physically divided roadway. V2 was parked on the right-hand shoulder. The roadway was wet and standing water was on the roadway. While traveling V1 began to yaw clockwise, almost 360 degrees, departed the roadway and the right side of V1 struck the back of V2. Both Vehicles were towed.
V1 was southbound on a two lane two way undivided road. V1 departed the right side of the roadway (west), impacting a tree with the frontal plane.

V1 was westbound on a two lane undivided roadway. A deer entered the path of V1 and V1 traveled to its right to avoid the deer. Upon departing the road V1 traveled up an embankment and overturned left side leading 2 quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on its top facing northwest.
Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2, a M/HT, were traveling northeast with Vehicle 2 ahead of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted the rear of Vehicle 2's trailer.

V1 was traveling southbound following a two-way, two lane road. The roadway was curved to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a pole and went on to impact a mailbox with the same plane. V1 came to final rest on right shoulder of the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a four lane divided roadway approaching an intersection controlled by traffic lights. A non-contact vehicle (NCV) traveling southbound in the fourth lane of a four lane divided roadway was waiting at the red left turn traffic light. The NCV decided to go straight instead departing the lane at right and entering the third and second lanes. V1 avoided collision with the NCV and departed the lane at right and departing the roadway at right. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a curb (Event 1). The frontal plane of V1 then contacted a warning sign (Event 2). Then the frontal plane of V1 contacted a traffic light pole (Event 3) where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway attempting to take a left at an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching a stop sign at the same intersection. V1 lost control and departed the lane at left and then the roadway at left. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the curb on the center median (Event 1). The frontal plane of V1 then contacted the frontal plane of V2 where V1 came to final rest.

This crash took place at a four way stop sign intersection. V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in a single lane roadway. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side plane of V2. V2 began to rotate clockwise and impacted a curb with its front right wheel. V2 then impacted a small concrete barrier before continuing forward and impacting tree with its frontal plane where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a 2 lane, 2 way, undivided roadway. V1 went off the right side of the roadway, returned to the roadway in a counterclockwise yaw,and went off the left side of the roadway striking an embankment with its undercarriage. V1 then began a right side leading 8 quarter turn roll, striking 2 gates in the course of the roll. V1 came to final rest on its wheels facing east.

V1 was traveling east on a six lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling north on a three lane, one way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  After the impact V2 continued north east and the front of V2 contacted a curb.  The front of V2 then contacted a sign post.

V1 was traveling eastbound on the opposite side in the fourth lane of the two-way, five lane road, toward oncoming traffic. As V1 was being pursued by a NCV, V1 departed the roadway to the left. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with a pole. V1 re-entered the road on the right and proceeded to travel in the southeast direction crossing all lanes of travel. The left front wheel of V1 made contact with a curb.
Vehicle #1 was driving east and made a left turn onto an intersecting road. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The front plane of V1 struck a tree.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed its lane to the left, then over-corrected and departed the road to the right. V1 steered right, then over corrected left, rotating clockwise and re-entering the road. V1 departed the road to the left. The back plane of V1 contacted a guardrail. V1 rotated sharply counter-clockwise and the right plane contacted the guardrail.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  V1 departed the road to the right, steered left then re-entered the road.  V1 steered right where it rolled left 4-quarter turns on the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and the front of V1 collided with a wooden utility pole. The collision with the pole caused V1 to rotate clockwise as it continued to travel off the roadway and down a dirt embankment. As V1 traveled down the embankment it overturned three quarter turns to the left about its longitudinal axis and rotated back onto its roof, before coming to final rest on its roof facing northeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, negotiating a right curve.  V1 lost control and began to rotate clockwise.  V1 departed the road to the left.  The left of V1 contacted 3 trees simultaneously.  V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise.  V1 rolled over to the right.  During the rollover the right of V2 contacted 2 tree simultaneously.  The top of V1 then contacted a tree interrupting V1's rollover.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east.  V1 lost control and departed the road to the left.  V1 rolled over 4 quarter-turns.

V1 was traveling north on the Interstate in lane 1 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the right and sideswiped a section of guardrail.  V1 was steered to the left and returned to the roadway briefly before departing the roadway on the left onto the dirt median where it rolled right coming to rest on its left side.

V1, V2, V3 and V4 were all traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway.  V2, V3, and V4 were stopped. The front of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V2 front plane contacted the back plane of V3 and V3 front plane contacted the rear of V4.

V2 and V3 were traveling northbound on a five-lane roadway approaching an intersection, V2 was in lane one and V3 was in lane two. V1 was traveling southbound attempting to turn left at the intersection and head eastbound. The front of V2 struck the front of V1 and the front of V3 struck the right side of V1. After impact V2 continued northeast off the roadway where it struck a pole.
V1 was north bound on a two way, 4 lane divided highway, when V1 impacted a bear with its frontal plane.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway exiting a left hand curve.  V1 departed their initial lane of travel over the center lane line and into the opposing lane of travel.  V1 continued traveling in the opposing lane of travel and departed the southern shoulder of the roadway.  V1 continued driving off of the roadway for a short distance before striking a tree with its frontal plane.  V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right hand side striking approximately one hundred feet of cable guide wire and a roadside sign with an unknown plane of impact. V1 continued to travel on the front lawn of a local business before striking a concrete parking barrier with its frontal plane. Afterwards V1 continued to travel across the lawn before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was negotiating a turn on an off-ramp in the first lane of a one lane, one-way, roadway turning eastbound. V2 was negotiating a turn on an off-ramp in the first lane of a one lane, one-way, roadway turning eastbound behind V1. V1 approached a yield sign and stopped for oncoming traffic before attempting to merge onto the roadway. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the rear of V1.

This intersection has stop signs for the north/south roadway. V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way undivided roadway. V1 passed through the intersection as V2 was traveling through the same intersection. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way divided roadway. V2 was a legally parked, not in transport vehicle facing southbound. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way roadway, approaching a three-leg intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two-lane,  two-way roadway, approaching the same intersection. The driver of V1 initiated a left turn as the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, one way roadway.  V2 was stopped on the same roadway ahead of V1.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two lane two way roadway traveling through an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was northbound on a two lane two way roadway traveling through the same intersection.  Vehicle 2 front end contacted the left side of vehicle 1 as both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane one way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane one way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the right lane of a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 made a left turn at the intersection, onto a two way, two lane, undivided roadway traveling eastbound. V2 was parked on the intersecting roadway on the south side facing eastbound. V3 was parked in front of V2. The frontal plane of V1 then made impact with the right plane of V2, and then the frontal plane of V1 made impact with the rear plane of V3.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with one lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in front of V1. V3 was traveling on the same roadway in front of V2. At the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 made impact with the rear plane of V2. This caused V2 to move forward and, the frontal plane of V2 made impact with the rear plane of V3.

Vehicle 1 was attempting to make a right hand turn on a 6-lane not physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling in the number three lane on the same roadway traveling north. Vehicle 1's left and Vehicle 2's front made contact with each other in the number three lane. Vehicle 2 then rolled 4 quarter turns, left side leading, and came to final rest on its wheels facing in a north-easterly direction.
V1 was traveling east in the right lane on a two way, four lane road. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a pole.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east, in the third of four lanes and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, in the fourth of four lanes. V1 changed lanes to the left to avoid a collision with another vehicle. The left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both drivers lost directional control, veered left and departed the roadway on the left side. The front of V2 contacted the concrete traffic barrier. The front of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane, one way, exit ramp in the number 2 lane. V1 departed the roadway to the left side and the front corner impacted a concrete barrier. V1 rotated clockwise after the impact and the left of V1 impacted a concrete barrier. V1 came to final rest blocking the number 1 and number 2 lanes, facing in a southeast direction.

V1 was traveling southbound in the #1 lane of a 4 lane highway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and traveled down into a ditch where the front of V1 impacted an uphill embankment leading to an over-crossing bridge.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east. Vehicle #2 was traveling west on the same traffic way. Vehicle #3 was stopped facing south west, waiting to turn west. V1 began to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 departed the road to the right and contacted a sign post on a curb-height median. V2 entered a different roadway and the front of V1 contacted the left of V3.
V1 was traveling east on a one way interchange joining two interstates.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 struck an embankment.

V1 was traveling west on an alley access road. V2 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway approaching the alley access. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 LR tire contacted a curb. The front of V1 contacted a row of shrubbery.

V1 was traveling north passing through an intersection using a jug handle attempting to head south. V3 was traveling westbound in the passing lane crossing over the same intersection. The front of V3 contacted the left side of V1. V1 and V2 began to rotate and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V3. After the impacts with V1, V3 continued moving forward and to its left and the front of V3 contacted the front of V2. V2 was traveling eastbound approaching the same intersection.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, one way highway. A non contact vehicle was also traveling north west on the same roadway. The non contact vehicle had an object detach from their undercarriage while traveling in front of V1. The undercarriage of V1 contacted the object on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was stopped at a stop sign and proceeded to make a left turn onto a two lane, non-positively divided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling southbound on the same two lane roadway approaching the intersection. Vehicle #1's right frontal plane contacted Vehicle #'2 left rear side plane.

Vehicle #1 was making a left turn from a two lane undivided roadway onto an intersecting two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle #1 frontal plane made contact with the frontal plane of Vehicle #2, which was traveling northbound. After contact, Vehicle #2 departed the roadway left and made contact with an off roadway object coming to final rest.
Vehicle #1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, non-positively divided roadway. Vehicle #1 departed the roadway contacting an off road structure with its frontal plane before coming to final rest.
V1 and V2 were westbound on a two lane, two way, non divided roadway, in an active work zone. V2 was at a stop as directed by road workers, when V1's frontal plane impacted V2's rear plane.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a two-lane, two-way roadway in the same lane. V2 slowed down to make a left turn onto an intersecting roadway. In the initial travel lane, the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling east bound on a 2 lane undivided roadway in lane one, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north bound on a 2 lane one way roadway approaching the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling west on a highway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and drove on the shoulder until V1 impacted the end of a guardrail with its front. V1 rotated clockwise and impacted the guardrail with its left side.

V1 was traveling south, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 started to rotate counter clockwise and V2 started to rotate clockwise. The back of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound in the same lane and on the same roadway. V2 was ahead of V1 as the vehicles approached a four-leg intersection. V2 slowed and then stopped in the roadway, attempting to make a left turn. V1's front contacted V2's rear.

V1 was headed in a southerly direction on a 3 lane roadway at an intersection. A non contact vehicle pulled out of an intersecting road from the left. V1 ran off of the roadway to the right and struck a guardrail with its front end.

V 1 was westbound in lane one on a three lane, two way roadway enter an intersection. V 2 was northbound in lane one on a three lane two way roadway entering the same intersection. The front of V 1 struck the right side of V 2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north and Vehicle #2 was legally parked, facing north, along the east curb. V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V2 was traveling west through an intersection (in lane 2 of a four lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway). V1 was making a right turn (from south to west) through the same intersection (in lane 1 of a five lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway). Just outside of the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the left lane of a two way roadway, with two lanes of travel in each direction. V1 then departed the lane on the right side, returned to the lane on the left side, crossed the two lanes of travel northbound, and then departed the roadway on the left side. The frontal plane of V1 made impact with a tree.

V1 was traveling northbound in the second lane of a two way roadway with five lanes of travel. V2 was traveling westbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with three lanes of travel. At the above intersection, the frontal plane of V2 made impact with the right plane of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway with traffic in opposite directions, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the road to the right onto a dirt roadside. The right side of V1 impacted a sign post. V1 entered a counter-clockwise yaw, then impacted a wood utility pole with the right plane. The impact to the pole was significantly aft of the V1 center of gravity and the impact redirected V1 into a rapid clockwise yaw. V1 tripped and rolled over to the left one quarter-turn and came to final rest on the left plane, straddling a narrow ditch.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  Vehicle #2 was traveling east on an intersecting roadway.  V1 turned left into V2's path and the front of V2 contacted the back of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, with a left curve.  V1 departed the right (west) side of the roadway and continued traveling until it struck an embankment with its undercarriage.  After striking the embankment the vehicle crossed the road to the left and continued traveling south through the ditch until coming to final rest heading south.

Vehicle #1 was heading west on a two-lane undivided road, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was heading north, on a two-lane road, approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection going straight, and the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north bound approaching the same intersection attempting to turn left. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling south in the first lane on a five lane physically divided roadway. V1 departed roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a pole on the east road side.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, not physically divided roadway, toward a T intersection. V1 traveled straight across the intersection striking a curb, mailbox, embankment and sign. V1 then came to final rest off the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of three on a divided highway without a positive barrier, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane one of two of a two-way street approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection as both vehicles proceeded through. V1 departed the left side of the road and crossed over the median where it came to final rest. V2 came to final rest heading south near the intersection.

V1 was traveling east in the number 1 lane on a 2 lane divided highway. V1 departed the roadway to the right traveling along the shoulder when the front of V1 struck a barbed wire fence post (event 1). V1 continued to travel along a ditch line and the front of V1 struck the side wall of the ditch line, sideswiping the side of the ditch line (event 2). The the front of V1 struck a culvert drain (event 3) and V1 then came to rest on the culvert.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two lane, non-marked roadway. V2 was legally parked facing north. V1 departed the roadway to the right, its right side contacting V2's left side.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound in the third of four lanes at the apex of a merge ramp. Vehicle 2 was eastbound in the second of the four lanes on the merge ramp. V1 attempted to change lanes to the right and the right of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 was redirected to the north and traveled across the eastbound travel lanes. The front of V2 contacted the concrete traffic barrier on the left roadside.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane 4 of a 4 lane roadway.  V2 was traveling southbound in lane 1 of a 4 lane roadway.  V3 was stopped and preparing to turn south from a gas station parking lot.  V1 turned left at the intersection and struck V2 on the left side plane with the frontal plane.  V2 then traveled and struck V3 on the left side plane with the frontal plane.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west bound on a two-lane roadway when it departed the road on the right side. V1 continued off road and the front plane contacted a fence.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling northeast on a 6 lane interstate all in the number 2 lane. V2 and V3 were stopped due to traffic and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of this collision pushed V2 forward where the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.

V1 was heading eastbound on a 5 lane highway traveling in the #4 lane. V2 was stopped facing west in the #4 lane of a 5 lane highway. V2 was in a previous crash. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was stopped on the right shoulder facing east on a two lane road. V2 was traveling westbound in the #1 lane of a 2 lane road. V1 entered the roadway and attempted a U-turn. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 continued to turn left and traveled up a private driveway and impacted the wall of a house where it came to final rest.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east and vehicle #2 was traveling south. Both vehicles entered an intersection, and the front plane of V2 struck the left plane of V1.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north. V1 departed the road to the left, and the front plane of V1 contacted a boulder.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west. Vehicle #2 was stopped, facing east in lane 3, a dedicated left turn lane, waiting to turn left. Vehicles #3 and #4 were stopped facing east in lane 2. V1 crossed over into the eastbound lanes, then attempted to swerve between V2 and V3. The right plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V3, then the front plane of V4.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, not physically divided roadway, in lane 1 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2, which was traveling east on the same roadway in lane 1 (of two lanes). V1 departed its lane on the left and sideswiped the left side of V2.

Vehicle One was traveling west on a two-way not physically divided roadway in the number two lane. Vehicle One lost control due to a blow-out of the left rear tire. The vehicle then departed the roadway on the right side and made contact with a traffic sign. This caused the vehicle to rotate counter-clockwise and a rollover was initiated by tripping over with a force that was applied to the wheels. The vehicle rolled primarily to the right 4 quarter turns and came to final rest off of the paved roadway on the right side.

V1 was traveling northbound in a single lane roadway marked for one way southbound travel only. V2 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V3 was legally parked north of the intersection facing north along the east curb. V1 and V2 both entered the intersection at the same time. The left side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise with the rear plane of V1 impacting the rear plane of V3. V1 came to rest facing southbound. As V2 rotated counterclockwise, the right rear tire impacted a curb before it came to final rest facing westbound.

V1 was traveling northbound on a one lane on-ramp entering the second lane of a two lane two-way divided trafficway. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way divided trafficway. V1 was merging onto the highway and lost control departing the second lane to the right. The right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2 as it entered the first lane (Event 1). V1 departed the roadway to the left.  The left side of V1 contacted the guardrail face (Event 2).   V1 then rotated counter-clockwise when the right side of V1 contacted the guardrail face (Event 3).  V2  then departed the roadway while rotating counter-clockwise. The right side of V2 then contacted the guardrail face (Event 4).  V1 and V2 came to final rest facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V1 departed the left side of the right lane, returned to the right lane, and then departed the roadway on the right side contacting V2 who was parked. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 causing V2 to rotate counter clockwise while V1 rotated clockwise; during this rotation the rear plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2.  V1 and V2 both came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound in lane one, while V3 and V4 were traveling in lane two northbound on a two lane one way roadway. V2, V3 and V4 were decelerating with traffic when V1's front contacted V2's back forcing V2 into lane two where the front of V2 contacted V4 causing it to rotated clockwise off the roadway where it came to final rest. V2 came to final rest in lane two. V1 continued to travel into lane two where the front of V1 contacted the right side of V3 causing V3 to rotate clockwise off the roadway where the front of V3 contacted the Right front tire of V1's tractor before coming to final rest off the roadway and V1 came to final rest partially off the roadway and partially blocking lane two.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south, on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, approaching a T intersection. V1 began to turn left at the intersection, but departed the end. The front plane of V1 contacted an embankment.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway, and Vehicle #2 was traveling west. V1 braked hard for slowing traffic, and departed the road to the right. V1 over-corrected to the left, returned the road, and entered the oncoming traffic lane. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2.

Vehicle # 1 was westbound on a three lane two way roadway.  Vehicle # 2 was westbound stopped on the same roadway spraying weeds for the city with rear caution lights activated.  Vehicle # 1 front end struck Vehicle # 2 back end.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two way undivided roadway.  V1 lost control on the wet roadway, began a counter-clockwise yaw and departed the road left, V1 contacted a mailbox with its right side.  V1 then continued forward where it overturned two quarter turns onto an embankment and came to rest back on its wheels.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-way undivided roadway approaching a 4-way intersection.  V2 was traveling south in lane one of a two-way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection.  The front end of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane undivided roadway.  V1 began a clockwise yaw on the wet roadway and departed the roadway to the right and its right side contacted a stand of small trees.

Vehicles 1,2,3 were traveling south on a non physically divided two way roadway approaching an intersection. All of the vehicles were merging into the left hand turn lane. V3 was slowing in the roadway to make a left turn. V2 subsequently slowed down as well. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3.

V1 was east bound, turning right on a two lane non divided dirt roadway. V1 lost control as it made the turn. V1 then left the roadway to the left where it impacted an implement of husbandry (Lamco Forage Wagon) with its frontal plane.
V1 was west bound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the travel lane. V1 came to final rest on the right side (north) of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east, making a left turn. V2 was traveling south on an intersecting roadway. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 spun clockwise and impacted a snow bank with its left side.

V1 was traveling east bound in lane two on a four lane, two way divided roadway. V1 contacted the undercarriage on a wheel that was in lane two. V1 departed the lane on the left side and then departed the roadway on the left side and contacted the front bumper on a pole.

V1, which was towing a trailer, was traveling north bound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north bound behind V1. V1 attempted to turn right and the right side V1 contacted the front bumper of V2. V1 then departed the roadway at the northeast intersection apex and the front of V1 contacted a stop sign. The front of V1 then contacted two fence posts.

V1 and V2 were northbound on a three lane divided interstate. V1 was in lane two and V2 was in lane one. V2 departed its initial lane of travel to the left.The front of V2 impacted with the right of V1.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane one of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction and approaching a four way intersection. V1 departed the roadway on the right side near the northwest apex and the front of V1 contacted a pole.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 traveled to its left, crossing the northbound travel lane, then departed the east road edge. The left side of V1 contacted a tree and continued down a slight embankment, where the right side contacted an unknown object. V1 came to final rest facing southbound off the east side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a four lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane two on the same roadway. V2 attempted to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling west in lane two of a two-way, four-lane roadway. The driver of V2 entered lane one and initiated a left, U-turn maneuver. The front of V1 contacted the left of V2.

V1 was northbound in traffic in the third of five lanes approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was northbound in the fifth lane slightly ahead of V1. V1 changed lanes to the left, passing through lane four and into lane five. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was westbound in the third of six lanes. Vehicle 2 was westbound in the same lane ahead of V1. Vehicle 3 was westbound in the same lane ahead of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. The front of V2 then contacted the back of V3.

V1 was eastbound on a 4 lane roadway in the second eastbound lane. V2 was westbound on a 4 lane roadway in the second westbound lane. V2 started to turn left across the eastbound travel lane. The front of V2 impacted the front of V1 (event 1). Then as V1 continued forward, the front of V2 impacted the left rear of V1 (event 2). V1 traveled right across the eastbound travel lanes and came to final rest on the shoulder facing east. V2 came to final rest at impact.

V1 was traveling west on a 4 lane divided roadway in lane 4 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway in lane 1. At the intersection V1 turned left and the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound approaching an intersection in the left turning lane on a two way undivided roadway with two lanes of travel and a left turning lane in the northbound direction, and two lanes of travel in the southward direction. V2 was traveling southbound in the middle lane on the intersecting two way roadway with two lanes of travel and a left turning lane in the southbound direction, and two lanes of travel in the northbound direction. As V1 turned to its left to travel westbound at the intersection V2 proceeded straight through the intersection. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the left lane of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. The driver of V1 was attempting to turn left at the intersection heading northbound. V2 was traveling in lane three of a physically divided roadway, with four westbound travel lanes and two eastbound travel lanes. At the intersection, the right side plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a curved, two lane, 2 way roadway, and slowed down to make a left turn. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. The front plane of V2 struck the rear plane of V1. V1 went off the right side of the roadway striking a culvert before coming to final rest off the roadway headed east. V2 departed the right side of the roadway and came to final rest east of V1 headed west.

V1 was traveling west on a two way two lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on the intersecting two way two lane undivided roadway. As V2 attempted to turn to its left at the intersection V1 proceeded straight through the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2, and V2 began to rotate counterclockwise. V2 then rolled five quarter turns and came to final rest off of the roadway in a ditch in the southeast intersection apex.

V1 was east bound in lane two on a two lane each direction, four lane roadway divided by a grass median. The front of V1 impacted a deer. V1 came to final rest on the south side of the roadway facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 2 lane 2 way roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling north on the same roadway. Vehicle 2 departed its lane and contacted the left side of Vehicle 1 with its front plane. Vehicle 1 continued south departing the roadway to the right (west) coming to final rest in the west ditch facing east. Vehicle 2 continued north, departing the roadway to the left (west) coming to final rest in the west ditch facing west.

V1 was traveling west on a 2 lane, 2 way, undivided roadway with a left turn lane, at a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. V1 attempted a left (south) turn at the intersection as V2 traveled straight through the intersection eastbound. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the intersection. V1 front contacted and came to final rest in the south east ditch facing east. V2 came to rest on the south east shoulder facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 3 was traveling northwest stopped at the same intersection. The right plane of Vehicle 1 was contacted by the front plane of Vehicle 2. Then, Vehicle 1's right plane contacted the front plane of Vehicle 3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest and Vehicle 2 was traveling southeast approaching Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 departed its travel lane to its left. Vehicle 1's left plane contacted Vehicle 2's left plane. Vehicle 1 departed the left road edge and went into a counter clockwise rotation and its right plane contacted the ground as it began to trip non horizontal. Then Vehicle 1's right plane contacted two utility pole guy wires and came to rest on its wheels.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling northwest approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1's right plane was contacted by Vehicle 2's front plane. Vehicle 1's right plane then side slapped with Vehicle 2's left plane.

V1 was traveling east on a non-physically divided 2 lane street.  V2 was traveling northbound on a non-physically divided 2 lane street.  While passing though the non controlled intersection, the right side of V1 made contact with the front of V2.  Both vehicles rotated together and the right side of V1 made contact with the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling in the opposite direction on the same road. V1 attempted to make a left turn onto a side road when the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on a 4 lane freeway in the #1 lane. V2 began to slow due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a 6-lane roadway in lane 1.  V1 traveled through an intersection and departed the road on the right side.  The front right tire of V1 impacted the curb as it departed the road.  The front left tire also impacted the curb.  The front right tire of V1 impacted a second curb separating the sidewalk from the grass.  The front of V1 then impacted a light pole.

V1 was traveling north on the Interstate in lane 5 (of 6 lanes). A non-contact vehicle was traveling north on the same roadway in lane 4 (of 6 lanes) when it began to change lanes to the left. V1 steered left, departed the left road edge rotating counter-clockwise and with its front plane, contacted a concrete barrier. V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise then contacted the concrete barrier with its end plane.

Both vehicles were traveling west on a five-lane physically divided roadway. V1 was traveling in lane 4 and V2 was traveling in lane 5.  V1 changed lanes to the left in front of V2. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V2 continued forward and its left side contacted the concrete barrier.  V1 rotated counter clockwise and impacted the concrete barrier with its front.

V1 was traveling southeast negotiating a left curve, approaching a light controlled 4 legged intersection in lane 1. V2 was traveling north approaching the same intersection in lane 2. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and impacted a utility pole (Event 1) with its frontal plane. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise as the left fender region impacted the utility pole guy wire (Event 2), before coming to rest, facing west.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane three on the intersecting four lane divided roadway. As both vehicles proceeded to travel straight through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. After impact V1 and V2 then traveled into the northeast intersection apex and the front of V1 contacted an embankment.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 of a 5 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling east in lane 2 of a 3 lane non-divided roadway and was turning left at a controlled intersection to head north on the 5 lane divided roadway. At the intersection, V1's frontal plane struck the left side plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a one way two lane roadway. V1 departed the south edge of the roadway and rolled four quarter turns left side leading before coming to final rest off the roadway on its wheels.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 2-lane, 2-way undivided roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right where the front of V1 contacted a fence (wrap around damage on right plane).  During off road travel, V1s LF tire contacted an unknown object causing a tear in the sidewall. V1 continued off road and the front of V1 contacted an embankment.
V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a sign and a guardrail end.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a highway entrance ramp V1 was negotiating a right curve when it departed the west road edge. The front of V1 then contacted a ditch on the west roadside and came to rest.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two way road with a descending grade. V1 departed the left side of the road and sideswiped its left plane on a tree. V1 continued on the left side of the road and sheared a telephone pole with its front plane causing it to rotate clockwise. The left side of V1 then impacted a guy wire where it came to rest.

V1 was traveling south in lane two of a level, two-lane divided road. V2 was traveling north in lane three of a three-lane of the same road.  V2 made a left turn and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 and V2 were west bound in the second lane on a 5 lane physically divided roadway. The front of V2 impacted with the rear of V1. V1 came to final rest in the third lane facing west. V2 came to final rest facing west in original lane.

V1 was negotiating a curve to the left, following two-way, two lane roadway. V1 lost control on black ice and departed the travel lane to the left. V1 reentered the original travel lane to the right. V1 then departed the roadway on the right. The LF tire of V1 impacted the curb. V1 flipped 1 quarter turn. The hood of V1 impacted a utility pole causing V1 to spin clockwise around the pole, impact a tree with its right side and land on all four tires.

V1 was facing north entering an intersection turning left from a 2 lane, two-way private driveway. V2 was going east on a 3 lane, two-way road, approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, approaching a T intersection on the through street. V2 was traveling west in the same lane, in front of V1. V2 was slowing, and beginning to make a right turn. V1 contacted V2 in the rear plane with its frontal plane. V3 was stopped at a stop sign on the intersecting 2 way, two lane, unmarked roadway headed south waiting to turn. After V2 was contacted in the rear plane by V1, V2 proceeded forward and to its left and contacted the left plane of V3 with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest west of the intersection headed west. V2 came to rest at the point of impact with V3 headed north west. V3 came to final rest at the point of impact with V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two lane divided interstate under construction.  V1 attempted to change lanes to the left over a painted median.  The front of V1 contacted an impact attenuator then rotated clockwise and the right side of V1 contacted a concrete barrier.
V1 was southbound negotiating a right curve on a two lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front impacted a fire hydrant. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact.

V1 was northbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the right (east) side of the roadway traveling up an embankment and overturning left side leading. V1 came to final rest on its roof facing northeast.

V1 & V2 were soutbound on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a 4 leg intersection. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 causing damage. Both vehicles came to final rest on the west side of the road facing south.
V2 was stopped heading west on a two lane, two way positively divided roadway.  V1 was traveling west on the same roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling east on seven lane two way roadway. V2 was traveling east on a seven lane two way roadway. V1 departed lane of travel to the left. V1 returned to the roadway, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling southeast on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was negotiating a curve heading southwest on a two lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  The left side of V1 then contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a 2-lane, 2-way, undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve.  V1 departed the roadway to the right where the right rear tire contacted loose rock causing a blowout.  V1 then rocked up onto its right wheels (curtain air bags deployed) but did not complete a quarter turn roll.  V1 came to rest on the east side of the roadway.
Vehicle #1 and vehicle #2 were both traveling south. V2 stopped at a red light, and the front plane of V1 struck the back plane of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north. Vehicle #2 was traveling south. V1 began to turn left at an intersection, and the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling east in lane 2 on a 5-lane, undivided, two-way roadway. V2 decelerated to stop at a red light. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north on the same trafficway.  V1 began to turn left and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning right; V2 entered the intersection going straight, and the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 2-lane, 2-way undivided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and became airborne and the undercarriage of V1 contacted a tree, V1 then rolled right while falling to the ground and the right side of V1 contacted a downed tree.  V1 continued to roll onto the roof where it came to final rest.

V1 and V2 were south bound in lane 1 of a two lane physically divided roadway, V1 behind V2. V2 was a plow truck equipped with a wing plow. V1 attempted to overtake V2 on the right. V1's frontal plane impacted the wing plow on the right plane of V2. V1 then left the roadway to the right, where it impacted the guard rail with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted the guard rail a second time with its right plane. V1 re-entered the roadway, rotated counter clockwise and impacted the front plane of V2 with the front plane of V1, before coming to final rest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two lane non-divided highway and departed the road to the right. V1 re-entered the road, crossed the southbound lane, departed the road to the left, yawed counter-clockwise, and impacted a large tree with the front plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection and Vehicle #2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 in the intersection. V2 departed the impact with V1 on a northeast trajectory and V2 departed the northeast corner of the intersection and sustained a frontal impact with a metal sign pole.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane, non divided highway. V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway. V1 turned left and the back left of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane roadway entering an intersection. V2 was traveling east on the intersecting two lane, two way roadway entering the same intersection. The front of V1 struck the left side of V2.
V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way roadway and V2 was traveling behind V1 on the same roadway. V1 attempted to make a U turn and travel east and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound negotiating a curve to the left on a five lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on a six lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane, two way roadway in the second lane approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  As V2 attempted to turn to its left at the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way undivided roadway. A deer crossed the the path of V1 striking the front end. V1 came to final rest on the roadway

V1 was traveling westbound on a one way, 4 lane roadway approaching a turning lane. V1 continued straight. V1's front wheels contacted a curb and then went off of the roadway and continued traveling westbound before reentering intersecting roadway. V2 and V3 were traveling in opposite directions on a 6 lane roadway. V2 was headed north and V3 was headed south. V1's front contacted V2's right side. V1 then continued and V1's front contacted the left side of V3. V1 then continued northbound.

V1 was traveling south in the number 2 lane of a 3-lane undivided roadway, turning left at an intersection.  V2 was traveling west in the number 2 lane of a 5-lane roadway, heading straight through the same intersection.  The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest facing toward the southwest corner in the intersection.
V1 and V2 were traveling south in lane two on a four lane two way roadway. V1 was behind V2. V2 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane one on a five lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in lane three of a two way five lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. At the above intersection, as V1 was making a left turn to travel southbound, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two way roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same two way roadway. As the vehicles were negotiating a curve, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V2 rotated counterclockwise and contacted a guardrail with the rear.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane 5 of an 5 lane divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest in lane 3 of a 7 lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 turned left at the intersection the front of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling NE on a 2 lane non divided roadway when it departed the right side of the road and ran up a slight embankment and struck a tree with its front plane, then it rolled onto its left side and came to rest in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V1 traveled into the westbound travel lane to avoid a stopped vehicle and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was southbound on a two lane two way non divided roadway, attempting to negotiate a curve to its left. V1 traveled across the northbound travel lane and departed the east road edge where the front of V1 contacted an embankment. V1 then rolled five quarter turns before coming to final rest on its right side in the roadway.

V1 was traveling north in lane 2 of a 2 lane undivided roadway entering a roundabout.  V2 was traveling east in lane 2 of a 2 lane undivided roadway and was traveling through the roundabout. V1 entered the roundabout and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After initial impact the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2 as the vehicles moved to final rest.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a 3 lane divided highway. V1 was traveling in lane 3 and V2 was traveling in lane one. V1 traveled west, crossing over all lanes of southbound travel and entering the west roadside. V1 then reentered the roadway and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V1. V1 was pushed into the west roadside and rotated back into lane one of southbound travel, facing north in lane one of southbound travel. The front of V2 then contacted the front of V1.

V1 was traveling north in lane two on a three lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east in lane two on a five lane two way roadway, approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded to travel straight through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was southbound on a two-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was eastbound on a two-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and came to final rest on the edge of the roadway. V2 continued forward going around V1 and came to final rest in front of V1 on the edge of the roadway.

V2 was northbound in the third lane of a seven lane two way divided roadway. V1 was behind V2 on the roadway. V2 and V1 both entered lane four of northbound travel and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V1. V1 came to final rest just north of point of impact. V2 traveled over the median to its left and came to rest.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane one of a 2 lane roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling eastbound in lane one of a three lane roadway approaching the same intersection.  V1 attempted to turn left at the intersection to travel westbound and was struck on the left side by the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east negotiating a slight left curve on a three lane roadway composed of a eastbound travel lane and a westbound travel lane separated by a two-way left turn lane. V2 was legally parked along the south curb of the roadway. V1 moved to its right and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling north, approaching an intersection on the same roadway.  V1 was in lane 1.  V2 was in lane 2.  V2 began to turn right and the right of V2's trailer contacted the left of V1.  V1 was forced off the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a snow bank.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.
V1 was traveling south in lane five on a five lane one way divided roadway behind V2, which was stopped in lane five. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 (of 2 lanes). V2 was traveling north in lane 2. While V2 was overtaking V1, V1 departed its lane to the left, and the right side of V2 sideswiped left side of V1. V2 rotated clockwise, and departed the roadway on the right, contacting an earthen embankment with its front and then its back. V2 then overturned (2 quarter turns, leading left) as it reentered the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound in lane 3 on a four lane one way divided roadway, with V1 traveling behind V2. V3 was disabled from a previous crash partially blocking lanes three and four, facing north. V2 braked and turned to the right to avoid a collision with V3. The front of V1 then contacted the back of V2. V1 then continued traveling north, and the front of V1 contacted the back of V3.
Vehicle one and vehicle two were both traveling north. The front plane of vehicle one struck the back plane of vehicle two.

Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 5 lane two-way physically divided roadway in the #4 lane. Vehicle 1 was traveling in the #3 lane and changed lanes prior to crash to pass another vehicle in front of Vehicle 1 in lane 4. Vehicle 1's front end and Vehicle 2's rear end made contact with each other.

Vehicle #2 was going eastbound on a four lane non-divided roadway slowing to a stop due to traffic. Vehicle #1 was going eastbound on the same roadway and contacted the back plane of Vehicle #2 with its frontal plane.

Vehicle #1 was going northbound on an exit ramp entering into a right hand curve, when Vehicle #1 departed its travel lane left, it then exited the roadway left, contacting a guardrail with the frontal plane. After contacting the guardrail, Vehicle #1 continued and re-entered the roadway to the right traversing the two lanes and departed the roadway to the right side, contacting a second guardrail, with the frontal plane, before coming to rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling west on the intersecting roadway. Vehicle 1 turned to its left and the front of Vehicle 1 impacted the front of Vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane roadway approaching a T-intersection. V1 traveled through the intersection striking the northern curb with its undercarriage and then its left and right front wheels.

V1 was at a stop traveling north attempting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling east on a two-lane two way divided roadway passing through the intersection when the front of V1 made impact with right plane of V2.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane roadway. The front plane of V2 struck a deer in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 2 lane divided interstate when it drove off the right side of the road and struck a stump with the RF tire (Event 1) and then undercarriage (Event 2), V1 continued easterly and impacted a tree with the right fender area right A-pillar (Event 3), before impacting another tree with the front bumper plane (Event 4) of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling east on a 2 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the left side of the road onto a grass median, then returned to the road, crossed 2 traffic lanes and then departed the right side of the road. V1 struck a guardrail with the front plane.  The RF tire of V1 struck a curb.  V1 continued east on the roadway and again departed the right side of the road and impacted an embankment with the front undercarriage.

V2 was traveling northwest on a 2 lane, two way roadway and was turning left to enter a private driveway. V1 was traveling northwest behind V2 on the same roadway and attempted to pass V2 on the left. As V1 attempted to pass V2,  V2's left side plane contacted the right side plane of V1.

V1 was traveling south in the #2 lane of a 5 lane undivided two way traffic way.  V2 was traveling north in the #3, left turn lane, attempting a left turn to head west.  V3 was stopped, facing east, awaiting the light in the #1 lane of the intersecting 3 lane undivided two way traffic way.  V1 front made contact with V2 front. V1 was deflected after impact.  The front of V1 impacted the front of V3.

V1 was traveling east in the second lane of a four lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west in the second lane of a four lane two-way undivided roadway. V1 was attempting to take a left at the intersection with traffic lights. V2 was attempting to continue straight through the same intersection with traffic lights. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling in the first lane of a two lane roadway heading eastbound. V2 was traveling in the first lane of a two lane roadway heading eastbound. V2 stopped at the intersection to take a left turn. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2. V2 crossed into the second lane on the left. V2 departed the roadway on the left. V2 struck a curb with the frontal plane causing damage to the left front tire. V2 then struck a tree with the frontal plane, where it came to final rest.
Vehicle one was traveling south approach an intersection. Vehicle two was traveling east approaching the same intersection. Vehicle ones's front plane contacted Vehicle two's left plane.

Vehicle one was traveling south approaching an intersection. Vehicle two was traveling north approaching the same intersection attempting a left turn. Vehicle ones front plane contacted vehicle twos front plane. Vehicle one rotated counter clockwise and departed the right road edge. Vehicle ones right plane contacted a sign then two light poles. The driver of vehicle one was fully ejected.

Vehicle 2 was northbound in lane one of seven. Vehicle 1 departed a parking lot and was southbound on the same roadway.  V1 initiated a left turn into another parking lot on the east side of the roadway. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling south on an interchange attempting to enter an interstate roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to its left and crossed over the westbound interstate lanes and the front of V1 struck a guard rail.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and returned to the roadway. V1 then began a counter-clockwise yaw and departed the roadway to the left. The front the V1 contacted a guardrail end. V1 then rolled 6 quarter turns to the right and came to final rest on the roof.

V1 was headed north on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a four lane, one way roadway approaching the same intersection.  In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.  The left side of V2 then contacted the right side of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west. Vehicle #2 was parked facing east. V1 lost control departed its lane to the left, and the left plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2. V1 departed the road, and the front plane of V1 contacted a curb.

V1 was making a left turn from a parking lot onto a two lane two way undivided roadway to travel northbound.  V2 was northbound on the intersecting two lane two way undivided roadway. As V1 turned across the roadway the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the northbound travel lane.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way street. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 struck the rear of V2 that was parked along the right curb. V2 then struck V3 that was parked in front of it.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way snow covered road. V1 encountered a slick area and lost control sliding to the left across the southbound lane. V1 went off the road into a snow berm, rolling onto its left side.

Vehicles #1, #2 and #3 were traveling east.  Vehicles #1 and #2 stopped at an intersection.  The front of V3 contacted the back of V2.  This impact pushed V2 forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of V1.

V1 was traveling east on a three-lane, two-way road that curved left before passing through a five-leg intersection. V2 was traveling south on the two-lane, two-way intersecting road passing through the same intersection.
