V2 continued southeast onto a raised median and impacted a sign pole with its front and came to rest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on the intersecting two lane two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V2 attempted to turn to its left and travel east V1 proceeded straight through the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane undivided roadway. A non-contacted vehicle, pulling a trailer was traveling east on the same roadway.   The trailer crossed into the southbound travel lane, into the path of V1. The front of V1 contacted the left side of the trailer.

V1 was traveling westbound on a four-lane, two-direction roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was stopped at a traffic light on a two-lane, one-way roadway at the same intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.

Vehicle #2 was traveling south, on a divided highway, and Vehicle #1 was traveling east, in a crossover, after exiting a private drive. The front of V2 impacted the left plane of V1. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise in the roadway and the front left bumper contacted the left back of V2 before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling east bound on a non divided two lane roadway. As V1 rounded a corner to the right  a deer entered the roadway. V1 attempted to avoid impacting the animal., in doing so V1 lost control. V1 left the roadway to the left. V1's frontal plane impacted an embankment, and a fence post with it left plane. V1 then rolled 1 quarter turn where it impacted a tree with its right plane, before coming to final rest on its right side.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided highway when V1 encountered ice on the roadway. V1 yawed clockwise and departed the lane and roadway to the right. V1 climbed an embankment and rolled 2 quarter turns coming to rest on it's top. V1 was towed.
V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 departed the right side of the road onto a sidewalk and the front of V1 contacted a fire hydrant.

V1 was passing through a four-way intersection traveling southeast on a three-lane, two-way road. V2 was passing through the same intersection traveling southwest. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 as both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection.

V1, V2, and V3 were westbound on a five lane divided interstate roadway. V2 was slowing for V3 stopped ahead. V1 drifted into lane 1 and the front of V1 collided with the rear of V2 (event 1). V1 then moved into Lane 2. The front of V2 then impacted with the rear of V3 (event 2).

V1 was southbound on a 5 lane physically divided interstate in the far right lane. As lane five turned into an exit ramp V1 attempted to change lanes to its left to remain on the main roadway. V1 entered a painted gore area and the front of V1 impacted a sign. V1 then returned to the exit ramp lane and came to rest.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane non divided roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V1 departed its lane of travel to the left and into V2's lane of travel. V1's frontal plane impacted V2's frontal plane. V1 rotated counter clockwise, coming to final rest off the roadway to the right. V2 continued in a northern directions, where it impacted the guardrail before coming to final rest. As a result of the impact V1 had a minor engine fire.

V1 and V2 were traveling northwest on a three lane one way roadway, negotiating a right curve while approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling in lane 2, V2 was traveling in lane 3. V1 was eastbound on a two lane, non-divided roadway traversing a curve to the left, when the vehicle departed the roadway to the right. V1 impacted a caution sign with its frontal plane. V1 continued forward, where it impacted a tree with its right plane, which caused the passenger side front fender, and front passenger door to be torn from the vehicle. V1 continued forward where it impacted a second tree with its frontal plane. The second impact caused V1 to rotate clockwise where it impacted a third tree with its left plane before coming to final rest.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound on a two-lane roadway. V2 stopped and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane undivided roadway with traffic in in opposite directions. The north side of the roadway is intersected by an undivided two lane north/south roadway with traffic in opposite directions. West of the intersection the eastbound travel lanes are comprised of a dedicated left turn lane, an eastbound lane, and a dedicated right turn lane. East of the intersection the eastbound travel lanes are comprised of a an acceleration lane merging into the eastbound lane and the continuation of the dedicated right turn lane. Westbound travel through the intersection consists of a single lane. V1 was traveling east in lane one (dedicated right turn lane). V1 departed the right side of the roadway and the front of V1 contacted a tree with simultaneous contact to the top and left side of V1 and various limbs and branches. After colliding with the tree V1 continued to travel east while rotating in a clockwise direction. In the course of its travel and rotation the front of V1 contacted a mile marker sign and the left side of V1 contacted a utility pole. The collision with the utility pole accentuated V1's clockwise rotation and begin overturning to the left about its longitudinal axis. As V1 continued to move east it overturned 4 quarter turns and rotated approximately 180 degrees further to a position of final rest facing northwest straddling southern shoulder of the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was southbound on a four lane divided roadway in lane one negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway on the west side and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail face.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a stop sign. V2 was stopped at the stop sign and had been traveling westbound on the same two roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2 at the stop sign. V1 reversed and then moved forward twice, both times contacting the rear of V2 with the front of V1.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were all traveling southeast on a 4 lane interstate in the number 1 lane. V4 was traveling behind V1. V1 was traveling behind V2. V2 was traveling behind V3. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2, pushing V2 left into the number 2 lane. The momentum from V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted the rear of V3. V4 veered left and the right of V4 impacted the left of V1.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way interchange approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east in lane one on the four lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  As V1 attempted to turn left the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane two way roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a snow bank.

V1 was traveling south toward a four-way intersection and V2 was traveling north toward the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and V1 initiated a left turn. The right of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was westbound on a four-lane two-way undivided roadway in lane one.  V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a curb then a light pole.  V1 then rolled left across the embankment.
V1 was southbound on a 3 lane, 2 way undivided roadway.  V1 traveled off the roadway, to the right, and the front of V1 contacted a guard rail end and a sign post.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on the westbound portion of a four lane two way divided roadway with left turn lanes, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one on the intersecting three lane two way roadway. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 in the intersection.  V2 began to rotate clockwise and departed the road to the left.  The right side of V2 contacted a light pole.

V4, V2 and V3 were stopped in traffic traveling eastbound on a four lane not physically divided two way traffic roadway. V1 was traveling east on the same roadway. V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 front plane contacted the rear of V3, and V3 front plane contacted the rear of V4.
V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a four-lane roadway; V1 was traveling behind V2. V2 was stopped in traffic awaiting a left turn when the front of V1 struck the back of V2.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side where the front plane struck a utility pole.

V1 was legally parked facing east on the left side of a two way two lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V2 left the roadway on the right hand side. The front left side of V2 contacted the front left side of V1. V1 came to final rest on the roadway and V2 came to final rest off the roadway to the right.

V1 was traveling west entering a two way two lane undivided road. V1 was traveling north on the same roadway. V1 crossed the path of V2. The front plane of V2 contacted the left side of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest off the roadway on the west side of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on a one- way, two lane roadway. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 departed the roadway to the right and rolled 7 quarter turns. During the rollover, the bottom plane of V1 impacted a tree.  V1 came to final rest on its right side with the undercarriage against the tree.

V1 was traveling north following a two-lane, one-way road. V1 lost control and departed its original travel lane to the right. V1 then departed the roadway on the right. The front of V1 made contact with a guardrail. V1 rolled a total of 8 quarter turns. V1 landed on all four tires on the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane 1 on a two-lane, two-way roadway.  V2 was traveling northeast in lane 1 on the same roadway.  A non contact vehicle reversed out of a driveway on the north side of the road in front of V1 causing V1 to steer left to avoid a crash and travel over the left lane into the oncoming lane of traffic. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2 in the northeast travel lane. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest facing south across both lanes of traffic.  V2 came to rest facing north in its original lane.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane roadway. V2 was northbound on a two lane roadway. V1 and V2 entered into the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted with the left of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non divided traffic way in the process of making a left hand turn in the intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a two lane non divided traffic way approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 struck the front half of the left side of V2.  V1 and V2 rotated together causing a side slap.

Vehicle one was traveling northeast negotiating a left curve. Vehicle one departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted a utility pole. Vehicle one rotated clockwise and the left plane contacted a mail box. Vehicle continued and the left plane contacted a gas meter.

V1 was traveling northbound and departed the roadway to the right. V1 went into a clockwise rotation and tripped and rolled left five quarter turns. V1 contacted two trees and a utility pole in an interrupted roll before coming to final rest.

V1 was stopped at an intersection headed north. V2 was traveling east on the intersecting roadway. V1 entered the road way to travel north and the front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of Vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the road on the right side. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the curb. V1 then continued and the frontal plane impacted a utility pole where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling east in the first lane of a two lane divided trafficway. V1 lost control and departed the lane at right and then the roadway at right. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the shrubbery/brush (Event 1). Then the right side of V1 contacted a tree (Event 2).

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a two lane two way undivided traffic way.  V1 departed the east road edge and the front of V1 contacted a pole. V1 then began to rotate counterclockwise and the front of V1 contacted a fire hydrant. V1 then rolled 4 quarter turns left side leading, coming to rest in the northbound travel lane.

V1 was traveling east on the Interstate in lane 3 (of four lanes) and was overtaking V2, which was traveling east in lane 2.  V1 was moved from lane 3 to lane 2 and the front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2.

V1 was traveling west and the driver initiated a left turn, at a four-leg intersection.  V2 was traveling south through the same intersection.  In the intersection, the front end of V1 came into contact with the left side of V2.  V2 then continued in a southwesterly direction, departed the roadway on the right, and its front end came into contact with a pole and a fence.

V1 was eastbound on a three lane divided interstate.  V1 steered to the right in an avoidance of an animal that entered onto the roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of the vehicle impacted an interstate exit sign (event 1). V1 continued down the embankment and entered into a line shrubberies and the right side impacted (event 2) with a tree where it came to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound on the southbound side of the two lane freeway. V1 departed the east side of the roadway to the median. V1 drove off of a bridge that was under construction over the road below.  The left side mirror of V1 impacted the bridge as V1 left the roadway, and an unknown plane of V1 impacted a concrete pillar that was under construction.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound and approaching an intersection to turn left. Vehicle 2 was westbound and approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling north approaching a T-intersection on a three lane undivided roadway composed of one lane of southbound traffic, one lane of northbound traffic, and one northbound dedicated left turn lane. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and the front of V1 collided with a traffic sign. V1 continued to travel north off the roadway, subsequently the front of V1 struck a metal mile-marker sign and then a pole supporting a pedestrian crosswalk control box. After striking the control box V1 continued north, returning to the roadway and traveling with a northeast arcing trajectory through the intersection. V1 ultimately continued its northeast trajectory and struck a raised concrete curb at the northeast corner of the intersection. After striking the curb V1 came to final rest straddling the concrete curb and a downward sloping grass covered area east of the curb.

V1, V2 and V3 were all traveling westbound in lane two of a one-way roadway with three lanes of travel. V1 was behind V2 and V2 was behind V3. The frontal of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way undivided roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling northbound on the same roadway. V1 traveled to its left and entered the northbound travel lane. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V1 was originally heading north and turning west at an intersection. V2 was going straight and heading east through the intersection. V2's front contacted V1's left side.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in the number four left turn lane approaching an intersection to make left turn. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in the number 3 lane approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1's front end and Vehicle 2's left side made contact with each other. Vehicle 2 spun counter-clockwise to face in a southerly direction at final rest. Vehicle 1 final rest was in the opposite direction facing north.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way undivided roadway traveling through a right curve. V1 departed the north road edge and traveled onto the sidewalk. V1 then began to yaw counterclockwise and reentered the roadway, crossing over the west and eastbound travel lanes. V1 then departed the south road edge and rolled four quarter turns. V1 then came to rest on its wheels facing southeast.

V1 was westbound on a three lane, two way undivided roadway.  V2 was eastbound on the same roadway. V1 traveled to its left and entered the eastbound travel lane and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the south road edge and the front of V1 contacted a tree.
V1 was traveling north when it lost control and departed the road to the left. The rear plane of V1 contacted a large shrub.  V1 spun counterclockwise and the left plane contacted another shrub.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was parked facing north on the right side of the roadway. V1 lost control on the icy road and departed the travel lane to its right. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a three lane, two way roadway entering a five-legged light controlled intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane one on a three lane, two way roadway entering the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a five lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a five lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection attempting to turn left.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  V2 then departed the roadway to the southwest and the front of V2 contacted a steel light pole.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right to avoid contacting a deer in the road. V1 proceeded off the roadway and contacted an embankment with its frontal plane.

V1 was north bound on a two way two lane non divided roadway, when the vehicle lost control and slid off the road to the left. V1 impacted a traffic delineator with its frontal plane. It then impacted an embankment with its frontal plane. It then rotated counter clockwise, before coming to final rest in the south bound lane.

V1 was traveling northwest on a 4 lane interstate in the number 2 lane. V1 crossed over the lane lines to the right and departed the roadway. As V1 departed the roadway the front of V1 contacted a guardrail face. V1 came to rest blocking the number 2 and 3 lanes.

V1 was traveling in the number 2 lane of a 2 lane interchange. V1 was negotiating a curve on the interchange from one freeway to another. V1 lost control of the vehicle and departed the roadway on the right side. V1 impacted the curb on the right edge of the road. V1 traveled into a grassy median between two interchanges and rolled over coming to final rest on its roof.

V1 was traveling north on an undivided two lane roadway with traffic in opposite directions. As V1 was negotiating an uphill right hand curve it departed the right side of the roadway onto a down sloping dirt/grass embankment. V1 traveled along the embankment and began to yaw in a clockwise rotation. The left side of V1 contacted two used utility poles that were incorporated into the structure of a barbed wire fence and overturned four quarter turns to the left about its longitudinal axis coming to final rest on its wheels off the roadway facing northeast.
V1 and V2 were traveling southwest in the number 3 lane of a 7 lane road. Both vehicles were slowing due to traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a dark but lighted two-lane, two-way road. V1 stopped to make a left turn. The front of V2 impacted the rear of V1. V2 came to final rest on the road and V1 came to rest on the right side of the road.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V2 was eastbound on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer in the roadway. V1 then entered the eastbound travel lane and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was southbound on a two lane undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V1 departed the right side (south) of the roadway in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 then overturned 4 quarter turns right side leading. V1 came to final rest on the wheels off the roadway facing north.

V1 was eastbound in the first lane on a two-lane roadway. V2 was eastbound in the second lane of a two-lane roadway. V1 attempted to take an exit ramp and lost control due to the roadway being wet. V1 veered left and the left front of V1 collided with the right rear of V2. Then V1 veered right and the left rear of V1 collided with the right rear of V2 (event 2). V1 came to final rest on the south side of the roadway facing east. V2 came to final rest in front of V1 on the south side of the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a five lane, two-way roadway, with a two-way left turn lane.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side, while rotating clockwise, striking a curb with the left side wheels.  V1 continued traveling off the roadway, striking a street sign post with the left side.  V1 then rolled onto its top.

V1, V2 and V3 were traveling east on a five lane divided roadway in lane 2, with V2 directly behind V3, and V1 directly behind V2. V3 and V2 stopped for traffic and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V2 moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the back of V3.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed its lane to the left to avoid striking a deer in the road. V1 then departed the left side of the roadway impacting a culvert with the front. V1 continued to travel east and the right side of V1 contacted a ditch.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. V2 stopped and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 began a clockwise yaw and departed the east road edge. The front of V1 contacted an embankment with snow.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on a four lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a six lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a six lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 turned left at the intersection. The front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 in the intersection.

V1 was headed north in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was slightly ahead of V1 headed north in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 stopped as a non-contact vehicle ahead in the same lane was attempting to take a left turn onto a roadway at left. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a three lane one way divided roadway. V1 traveled to its left and crossed the remaining two lanes of westbound travel. V1 then departed the south road edge and the The right side of V1 impacted a guardrail end. V1 then rotated clockwise and the front of V1 impacted the guardrail end. V1 rotated clockwise along the west roadside and the driver was ejected from the vehicle.

V1 parallel parked facing north on the east roadside.  V2 was traveling northbound in the same single lane, one way roadway. As V1 was pulling out of the parking space into the single lane, one way roadway to head northbound,the frontal plane of V2 impacted the left side plane of V1.

Vehicle #1 was traveling North, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the road to the left and entered a depressed, grassy median. V1 began to rotate and the front plane of V1 contacted two boulders. V1 rolled over four quarter turns to the right.

V1 was traveling north and V 2 was traveling south on the same two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 traveled to its left and entered the southbound travel lane and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

Vehicle 1, 2, and 3 were traveling west in the #5 lane on a two way physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1's front end and Vehicle 2's back made contact with each other. After the initial contact between those two vehicles, Vehicle 2's front end and Vehicle 3's back end made contact with each other.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a two way undivided traffic way.  V1 moved to its right, exiting the west road edge. The front of V1 contacted a tree and V1 continued to travel south off the west road edge where the front of V1 contacted a second tree.

V1 was traveling southeast in the third lane and V2 was traveling northwest in the second lane on a five way non-physically divided roadway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection, V1 began left turn. The front of V1 impacted with the front of V2. V2 came to final rest facing northwest in the first lane. V1 came to final rest facing north in the intersection.

V2 was traveling south in the second lane on a three lane physically divided highway. V1 was traveling south in the first lane. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest in the left shoulder facing south.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a two lane two way undivided roadway negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the road to the right, then traveled back across both the west and eastbound travel lanes. V1 departed the north road edge and the left side of V1 contacted a tree and the front of V1 contacted an embankment.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling in a westerly direction in the #1 lane on a five lane roadway. Vehicle 2 stopped for the traffic ahead. Vehicle 1's front contacted the rear of V2 at a slow speed.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction and a left turn lane, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on the intersecting two-way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two lane, not physically divided State Route and was approaching V2 and V3, which were traveling west on the same roadway (with V2 ahead of V3).  V1 departed its lane to the left, sideswiped V2 and then contacted a temporary concrete traffic barrier along the north edge of the road.  The front end of V1 then contacted the front end of V3.

V1 and V2 were traveling north in lane two on a four-lane, physically divided roadway.  V1 was behind V2.  The front of V1 contacted and became entangled with the back of V2's trailer.  V1 was dragged as V2 pulled to the shoulder, and V1 caught fire.

V1 was traveling north on the Interstate in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the left and struck a paddle marker. V1 returned to the roadway and began to rotate clockwise. V1 then departed the roadway on the right and overturned (10 quarter turns, leading left) when its front left and back left wheels/tires struck a curb along the road edge. V1 was traveling westbound in the left lane on a two way roadway with three lanes of travel westbound and two lanes of travel eastbound. V2 was traveling eastbound in the left lane on a two way roadway with three lanes of travel in each direction. As V1 turned to its left the frontal of V2 made contacted with the right of V1.
V1 was traveling south on a four lane, two way positively divided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 struck a concrete barrier.
V1 and V2 were both eastbound on a two-lane neighborhood street. V2 was stopped ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was southbound on a two-lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the east edge of the roadway and the RF wheel of V1 contacted a curb. V1 continued to travel south and the front of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 returned to the southbound travel lane then departed the east road edge a second time. The RF wheel of V1 contacted the curb and the front of V1 contacted a mailbox.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching a four way intersection.  V2 was traveling southbound on the intersecting two lane undivided  roadway approaching the same intersection.  V1 and V2 proceeded straight through the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a four lane two way divided roadway in lane one. V1 traveled to its left, crossing lane two of westbound travel and the departing the west road edge. V1 continued to rotate counterclockwise, returning to the westbound travel lanes and coming to rest in lane one of southbound travel.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of 2 lanes.  V2 and V3 were traveling west in lane 1 of 2 lanes, with V3 directly behind V2.  V1 departed its lane to the left, and the front end of V1 contacted the front end of V2.  V1 then entered a counterclockwise rotation, and the left side of V1 contacted the front end of V3.  V2 entered a counter-clockwise rotation, and its undercarriage contacted a concrete jersey barrier.

V1 was traveling south in lane one on a five-lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 had been stopped in lane one at the intersection, and had just begun to move forward when the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north on an intersecting roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west.  V1 lost control and departed the road to the left.  The front of V1 contacted a snow bank.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane two of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction attempting to turn left heading northbound.  V2 was traveling westbound in lane one of the same roadway going straight.  At the intersection of the above roadways, the frontal plane of V2 contacted the right side plane of V1.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two way undivided roadway with one lane of travel and a turning lane in each direction. V2 was parked in a parking lane on the west side of the roadway facing southbound. Vehicle 2 was stopped at an intersection in the fourth of four lanes facing west. Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound in the same lane approaching V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was southbound in the third of three lanes. Vehicle 2 was southbound ahead of V1 in the same lane. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2. V1 then crossed over and through the first and second lanes and departed the roadway on the right side. The front of V1 contacted a concrete traffic barrier.

V1 was westbound in lane one of a four lane, two way road. V1 lost control on the icy road, leaving the roadway on the left over a sidewalk (via a drive-way cut-out) and impacting a cinder-block edging. (Cinder-block was one course tall, 20 cm)

V1 was northbound on a two lane two way road. V1 lost control on the ice and snow covered roadway. V1 rotated counterclockwise and departed the roadway on the left side. V1 rolled 5 quarter turns coming to rest on it right side in the southbound ditch.

V1 was northbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 began to rotate clockwise and departed the east road edge. The front of V1 contacted a snow bank. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted a snow bank.

V1 was traveling south in lane 2 of a two-lane physically divided roadway. V2 was in lane 1, to the right of V1. V1 attempted to change lanes to the right at an exit ramp interchange. V1, V2, and V3 were traveling westbound in lane two on a three-lane, one-way divided highway. V2 and V3 were stopped in traffic. The front of V3 contacted the rear of V1. V1 moved forward and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane two-way roadway attempting to make a left turn into a business parking lot. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.
V1 was traveling south on a two-way unmarked roadway when it departed the roadway on the left side. As a result, the front plane struck a tree where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling east in lane 2 of a 4 lane divided roadway stopped at a 4 way intersection.  V2 was traveling behind V1 in the same travel lane approaching the same intersection.  The front end of V2 contacted the rear end of V1.  Both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided two way roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V2 continued to travel off the roadway where V2's left side contacted the trailer unit of V1 before coming to final rest off the roadway.

V1,3,4,5 were all traveling north on a 2-lane divided highway in lane 2.  A non-contact motorcycle struck a deer running across the roadway coming to rest in lane 1 ahead of V4.  V4 stopped.  V3 stopped behind V4.  V2 contacted the back of V3 pushing V3 into V4.  V1 contacted the back of V2 pushing V2 into the back of V3 again.  A minor engine compartment fire then occurred in V1.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane non-divided highway, behind V2. V2 was attempting to stop for a non-contact vehicle making a turn. The front plane of V1 collided with the rear plane of V2. V2 was north bound on a two way two lane non divided roadway, when V1 attempted to back out of a parking lot onto the same roadway. The back of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the northbound travel lane.
V1 was traveling south on a four lane two way roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. The left side of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a five lane two way divided roadway in lane three, approaching an intersection.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west on the same roadway in lane three, a left turn only lane. As V2 turned left at the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling west on the same roadway. V2 began to rotate clockwise and traveled into the eastbound travel lane where the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a four lane, non-positively divided roadway, when it encountered icy road conditions, resulting in Vehicle 1 losing control. Vehicle #1 was going westbound on a seven lane concrete median divided roadway making a left turn at an intersection. Both Vehicles #1 and #4 then came to final rest.

V2 was parked on the east shoulder on a six lane, positively divided roadway facing south. V1 was traveling south in lane three on the same roadway. V1 moved to its left and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 then rotated counter clockwise contacting a concrete barrier with its front and continuing to rotate counter clockwise, contacting the barrier with its right side.

V2 was traveling east in lane one on a four lane, two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling west in lane two on the same roadway, attempting to make a left turn at the intersection. As V1 turned to its left the front of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the intersection.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway and V3 was following behind V2. The left front wheel of V2 became disconnected from the vehicle and landed in the eastbound travel lane. The front of V3 then contacted the disconnected wheel from V2.

V1 was traveling northeast negotiating a left curve on a two way undivided two lane roadway. V1 lost control and departed the road way on the right side of the roadway. V1 contacted a bush from the front, then V1 started to rotate clockwise and began to roll. V1 rolled 7 quarter turns before coming to rest on it's left side after contacting a house with it's left side.

V1 was traveling south in lane four on a seven lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane three, approaching the intersection. V1 was traveling southwest on a two-lane, two-way undivided roadway negotiating a curve to its left. V1 departed the right road edge and the front of V1 contacted a pole.

V1 was southbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 traveled to its left and entered the northbound travel lane. V2 came to rest blocking the number 3 and number 4 lane. V3 came to rest facing south in the number 5 lane. V4 came to rest facing south in the number 4 lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in lane 2 on a three-lane two-way roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2, 3, and 4 were stopped at the intersection with V2 behind V3 and V3 behind V4. V1 was traveling northbound approaching an intersection to turn left. V2 was eastbound and approaching the same intersection. V1 then rotated counterclockwise and the right side of V1 contacted an unattached trailer.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane undivided two way roadway. V1 departed the roadway to its right and the front of V1 contacted a building on the west side of the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way undivided roadway negotiating a curve to its right. V1 failed to negotiate the curve, traveled across the southbound travel lane and departed the west road edge. The front of V1 then contacted a utility pole, a sign and a bush at the beginning of a stand of brush/bushes. V1 continued to travel north off the roadside through the stand of multiple bushes and the left side of V1 contacted a tree. V1 continued forward through the bushes and the right side of V1 contacted a tree.
V1 was traveling east. V2 was parked facing east along the south curb. V1 departed its lane to the right, and the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

V1 was traveling north toward a four-way intersection. V2, V3, and V4 were all southbound approaching the same intersection. V1 was traveling east in lane two on a two way divided roadway. V1 traveled across lane one of eastbound travel and departed the south road edge. V1 rotated counter-clockwise in the soft median and then rolled over 3 quarter turns and came to rest on the driver side of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way undivided roadway and departed the road to the right into a grass and dirt shoulder. V1 departed the road to the left into a grass and dirt roadside, then tripped and rolled over to the right 8 quarter-turns. The right front seat occupant was completely ejected during the rollover event.

Vehicle one was traveling eastbound at an intersection attempting a left turn. Vehicle two was traveling westbound attempting to pass through the same intersection. Vehicle one's right plane was contacted by Vehicle two's front plane.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 steered to its right to avoid an animal in the roadway. Vehicle one departed the west road edge and the front of V1 contacted a tree.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 departed the lane on the left side and departed the south road edge. The front of V1 contacted three small trees and a fence. V1 continued west off the road edge and the front of V1 contacted six small trees.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a three lane roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one on a three lane two way roadway  approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded to travel straight through the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling North in lane two of a divided roadway with two northbound lanes, V1 behind V2.  V2 was stopped in the lane and the left plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. V1 departed its lane to the right and then the roadway to the right where its front plane contacted a guardrail face.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching a T intersection. V1 traveled straight through the T intersection until tipping over into a east west trajectory ravine. V1 rolled two quarter turns coming to final rest in the bottom of the ravine on its roof.

V1 was traveling east in lane one on a four-lane two way roadway. V1 attempted to pass a vehicle in lane one of eastbound travel by entering lane two of eastbound travel. V1 then began to rotate counterclockwise and traveled across the westbound travel lanes. V1 departed the north road edge and the right side of V1 contacted a tree.

V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a four-lane two way undivided roadway. V1 was in lane two and V2 was in lane one. V2 was traveling east on a two lane on way roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling south on the intersecting two lane two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on the intersecting two lane two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded to travel straight through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling North on a 2 lane divided highway in the number 2 lane when V1 lost control on the icy road. V1 departed the east road edge and the front of V1 contacted one cable barrier post and came to rest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way non divided road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on the intersecting two lane two way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded to travel straight the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 in the intersection. As the vehicles rotated to rest the right side of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 and V2 both exited the northwest roadway apex and came to rest.
V1 and V2 were traveling west in lane one on a five lane two way undivided roadway with V2 ahead of V1. V2 was proceeding forward from a stop and the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling west in lane two on a two lane roadway. V2, a tractor truck with a trailer,  was stopped on the roadway in lane two of westbound travel. The front of V1 impacted the rear of the trailer of V2.

V1 was traveling north on an undivided two lane road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on an undivided two lane road approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was making a left hand turn out of a driveway. V2 was traveling west in lane one on a 4 lane, 2-way undivided roadway. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 as it attempted to turn. After impact V1 traveled south, crossing all travel lanes and departed the south road edge. The front of V1 then contacted a tree.

V1 was traveling south in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway with a shared center turn lane. V1 traveled to its right and departed the west road edge. The RF tire contacted a curb and V1 continued to travel south off the west road edge and the front of V1 contacted a pole.

V1 was traveling south on 4 lane roadway with a divided median in lane 3. V1 was negotiating a right curve, departed the lane and roadway to the left in to the median. V1 began to rotate clockwise and impacted a light pole with the left side of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane one as the roadway widened from a two lane roadway to a four lane divided roadway with a grass median. V1 departed the roadway to the left, and front of V1 drove over a drainage culvert.
V1 was turning left out of a driveway. V2 was headed west bound on two- way, 6 lane roadway V2 was in lane 2.  V2's front contacted V1's left side.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on the intersecting two lane two way undivided roadway. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane two on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling westbound in lane one on the same roadway. As V1 was making a left turn into a private parking lot, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway.  V2 was traveling west in the left hand turn lane on the 5 lane non-physically divided roadway.  The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection as V1 turned left.
V1 was traveling south on a 4 lane divided highway, behind V2. V2 slowed to turn right into a parking lot, and the front of V1 contacted the rear of the trailer V2 was towing behind it.
V1 was traveling in the north on a two lane two way undivided roadway negotiating a curve to its left. V1 departed the east road edge and the front of V1 impacted a landscape boulder.

V1 was traveling northbound in the left turn lane of a two-way roadway with two lanes of travel and a left turn lane in each direction.  V2 was traveling southbound in lane one of the same roadway, approaching the intersection. As V1 turned to its left at the intersection V2 proceeded straight through the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. As the vehicles rotated toward the southwest intersection apex the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V1 exited the southwest apex and the front of V1 contacted a utility pole support cable, sign pole and utility pole.

V1 was traveling northwest in lane one on a two lane divided roadway. V1 traveled to its left, crossing lane two of eastbound travel and departed the left road edge. The front of V1 contacted a traffic barrier.
V1 was traveling eastbound in lane one of a two lane roadway. While negotiating left curve, V1 departed roadway and the frontal plane struck a tree.
V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway, negotiating a curve to its left. V1 began to rotate clockwise and departed the east road edge. The left side of V1 contacted a pole.

V1 and V2 were traveling northeast on a 5 lane physically divided highway. V1 was traveling in the #2 lane and V2 was traveling in the #3 lane. V1 departed from its original travel lane on the left side. The front left corner of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 then traveled across an on ramp lane and off the road on the right side. The front of V1 impacted a tree where V1 came to rest. V2 steered to the right and came to rest on the shoulder.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way undivided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the east (right) side contacting a utility pole with its front, before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and contacted a utility pole with its front end.  The vehicle continued to travel northeast until it came to a final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a three lane divided roadway. V2 was also traveling south on the same roadway in lane two. Wet and snowy weather conditions were present for both vehicles. V1 lost control on the wet roadway and departed its lane to the left and entered lane two while yawing in a counter clockwise direction. V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling north on the same roadway ahead of V1. V1 was traveling northbound in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted an impact attenuator.
V1 was traveling west on a four lane two way roadway. V2 was traveling west on the same four lane two way roadway in front of V2. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a three lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.  V1 then rotated counterclockwise and departed the roadway to the left.

V1 was intially headed east bound and was turning right into a southerly direction. V2 was initially headed west and had just turned left onto the same roadway and was headed south. V1's front contacted V2's right side.

V1 was stopped in traffic, going south on a two way, two lane road in the left lane. V2 was traveling in the left lane on the same roadway, behind V1. V2 rolled backwards impacting the front of V3 with its rear. V1 did not stop and continued on after impact.
V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 lost control and departed the right road edge. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and contacted a sign post with the left plane.  V1 continued and rolled, left side leading, five quarter turns.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two way two lane roadway. Vehicle 1 traveled off the right side of roadway and onto the northbound shoulder. Vehicle 1 traveled back onto the roadway, over corrected and began rotating clockwise. Vehicle 1 departed the right side of roadway a second time and the front V1 stuck an embankment. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise and rolled two quarter turns to the left coming to rest on its top facing east in a ditch adjacent to the embankment.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a one way two lane roadway. V1 traveled to its right and contacted a guardrail on the southern shoulder of the roadway with an unknown plane. V1 then proceeded to travel north across two travel lanes before striking the guardrail on the north side of the travel lane with their front left and then front plane.

V1 was approaching an intersection, traveling northbound in the left lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was approaching same intersection, traveling southbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. As V1 was making a left turn at the above intersection, the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the left plane of V2. V1 then proceeded to depart roadway on the left side and impacted a sign pole with its frontal plane. V2 proceeded to depart the roadway on the right side. The frontal plane of V2 made impact with a tree before coming to final rest. V1 then continued to travel in the southwest direction and the frontal plane of V1 made impact with shrubbery before coming to final rest on private property facing southwest.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-way, seven lane, median divided roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was headed eastbound, stopped in the left turn lane, at the same intersection,.  As V1 turned right at the intersection, the front of V1 made contact with the front of V2.

V1 was traveling west through the right hand curve of a two-way, not physically divided roadway, and was in lane 1 (of two lanes), approaching V2, which was traveling east through the left hand curve of the same roadway, in lane 1 (of two lanes).  V1 departed its lane on the left and its front end came into contact with the front end of V2.  V1 then overturned (4 quarter turns, leading left). V1 then experienced a major fire and V2 a minor fire.

V1 was traveling east on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane 1 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the right. V1 contacted an earthen embankment and overturned (8 quarter turns, leading left). During the rollover, Occupant 2 was totally ejected from V1.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane three on a three-lane highway at a point where the roadway divides into separate roadways, one continuing north and the other diverting eastbound. V1 traveled across all three lanes at the gore point of this interchange and departed the ride side of the roadway while  engaged in counterclockwise yaw. Vehicle 1 initiated a four-quarter turn rollover sequence (Event1), before its right fender region impacted a metal light pole (Event 2). Vehicle 1 continued to rotate counterclockwise as its right door impacted and sheared a second metal light pole (Event 3). Vehicle 1 rotated another 90 degrees CCW, before coming to rest, upright and facing southerly. The driver was ejected, likely during the initial rollover sequence.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a three lane undivided roadway in lane one approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east in lane two approaching the same intersection. As V1 proceeded straight through the intersection V2 turned to its left to travel north. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling north on a 3 lane divided roadway. Slush was on the roadway. V1 began to yaw clockwise, exited the roadway to the right and the left side of V1 contacted a pole.
Vehicle 1 was traveling Eastbound in lane 2 on an interstate when Vehicle 1's front impacted a deer. V1 continued East and pulled off on the right shoulder of the road before coming to a stop.
Vehicle #1 was traveling eastbound on a eight lane median divided roadway. Vehicle #2 was stopped within its lane and its rear plane was contacted by the frontal plane of Vehicle #1.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two-way unmarked roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side while attempting to avoid an animal in the roadway. The front of V1 then struck a utility pole and rotated one quarter turn clockwise. V1 came to final rest facing west in the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the same two lane roadway. Vehicle #2's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #1's right side plane as Vehicle #1 was making a left turn at the intersection. After contact Vehicle #1 rotated clockwise and contacted a guard rail with its left plane.
V1 and V2 were both in Lane 2 of the same 3 lane roadway, heading in a northerly direction. V2's front contacted V1's rear.

V1 was traveling south in the first lane on a two-way, non-physically divided roadway. V1 departed roadway to the right and impacted the front of vehicle with a guardrail face (event 1). V1 rotated clockwise until rolling over, left side leading (event 2), and proceeded to complete two more quarter turns striking a fence during the roll (event 3). V1 then went into an end over end rollover, falling over the edge of an over pass landing on the roof/ left A-pillar. V1 then rolled over onto it's wheels and proceeded to slide down the hill. V1 came to final rest along the roadside facing west.
V1 was traveling north on a 2 lane roadway when the front of V1 impacted a deer crossing the road.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, non divided bidirectional roadway, when it departed the roadway to the right. V1 impacted a traffic delineator with its right side. V1 was traveling south in the left lane, on a one way, two lane road. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left. V1 continued on to depart the roadway to the left. V1 went down an embankment and started to roll with its right side leading. V1 rolled a total of 6 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its roof.

V1 was traveling north in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway entering a four-legged, uncontrolled intersection. V2 was traveling east in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway entering the same intersection. In the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the right side plane of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound on a single lane ramp to merge onto the roadway eastbound. V1 departed the roadway on the right, at the top of the ramp. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the guardrail face. V1 came to final rest facing northwest.

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way, roadway around a curve to its left. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a rock barrier. V1 continued froward and impacted a small bush and then a tree with it's frontal plane, where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way, undivided roadway. V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 departed the left road edge then rolled to the right contacting a boulder with its top plane, and tree with its undercarriage.  V1 rolled three quarter turns coming to final rest on its left side.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, with a left curve. V1 went off the right side of the roadway with its right wheels. V1 then steered back onto the roadway and then proceeded to travel off the right side of the roadway again striking an embankment with its frontal plane and undercarriage.

V1 was traveling south on a curved left, two-lane, non-divided bidirectional roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway directly behind V2. V2 and V3 were also traveling east on the same roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast when it departed its travel lane to the left. Vehicle 1 then departed the roadway to the left into the median. Vehicle 1's LF wheel contacted a culvert.

V1 was eastbound in lane of a five-lane, undivided roadway.  V1 passed through the intersection then departed the right road edge and the front of V1 impacted a utility pole. V1 was southbound in the first lane on a five lane physically divided roadway. V1 departed roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted with a utility pole. V1 came to final rest at point of impact facing south.

V1 was traveling south on a two way non-physically divided roadway.  V2 was traveling north on the same roadway.  V2 departed the lane to the left.  The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. Vehicle #1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V2 rotated sharply counter-clockwise and rolled over two quarter turns to the right.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane two roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 as V1 attempted to turn left.
V1 was traveling south on a three lane, two way roadway.  V2 was traveling north on the same three lane two way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the initial travel lane to the left, then departed the left side of the roadway in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 was traveling east in the fourth lane of a six lane, physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in the third lane on a seven lane, physically divided roadway with a concrete median. V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  An animal entered the roadway from the east side of the roadway contacting the frontal plane of V1.  V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right impacting a curb with its right front tire. V1 continued over the curb, impacting a utility pole with it's frontal plane.

V#1 was traveling south on a 2 lane roadway. V#2 was traveling north on the same roadway. V#1's frontal plane contacted V#2's frontal plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling westbound on a two lane roadway. Vehicle #1 departed the roadway to the right. Vehicle #1's frontal plane contacted a tree. As a result of this impact, V1 began to roll over on its left side, completing 4 quarter turns, coming to final rest on its tires.

Vehicle #2 then left the crash scene.

Vehicle #1 was traveling eastbound in the westbound lanes of a six lane median divided roadway. Vehicle #1 departed the roadway on the right and traveled through a grass median. V1 was traveling eastbound on two- way roadway crossing through an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a two-way unmarked roadway passing through the intersection. V1 and V2 were traveling on an on-ramp heading westbound. The right side of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 then continued toward the left departing the roadway and contacting a guardrail.
V1 was traveling northbound negotiating a left curve on a two-lane roadway, V2 was traveling southbound. The front on V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the left lane line leaving the north side of the road way. V1 contacted four trees with an unknown plane before coming to final rest off the roadway.

V2 was traveling south in lane 2 of a 2 lane divided roadway and had nearly stopped in the roadway due to traffic .V1 was traveling south in lane 1 of the same roadway and had moved to lane 2 when it's frontal plane struck the rear plane of V2.

V1, V2, & V3 were in transport, west bound in lane 1 of a 2-lane roadway. V2 was stopped in traffic, V1 was decelerating behind V2. The front plane of V3 impacted the back plane of V1. The front plane of V1 then impacted the back plane of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway and was approaching the intersection of another two lane, two way roadway. V1 was traveling westbound on a one-way roadway with on-street parking. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2, which was parked along the south curb. Vehicle #3 was traveling north on a two-lane, undivided roadway. Vehicle's # 1 & 2 were traveling south on the same roadway. Vehicle #3's frontal plane struck Vehicle #1's frontal plane (Event 1). Vehicle #1 was traveling on an entrance/exit ramp. V#1 departed the roadway on the left, striking the head of a guardrail with the left side.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound in lane two. V1 departed the roadway on the left side then re-entered the roadway on the left side. V1 then departed the lane on the right side and departed the roadway on the right side and contacted the front bumper on a pole and two trees.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two-lane road curved left roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a tree. V3 was stopped facing southeast on a two way, two lane roadway. V3 was attempting to turn left into a private driveway. V1 was traveling north, in lane four, on a six lane, median divided roadway, intending to turn left. V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a four lane, two way roadway.  V2 was traveling west in the second lane of the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway. Due to poor road conditions (snow/ice) V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 contacted an embankment. V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway, passing through a T intersection. V1 struck a deer with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the south west corner of the intersection headed south.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane roadway. While attempted to pass another vehicle V1 departed the roadway on the left side where the front plane contacted a large tree.

V2 was traveling north on a four lane physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling west on the intersecting non-divided two lane roadway approaching the intersection when the front plane of V1 made contact with the right side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east, in the second of four lanes and Vehicle 2 was traveling west, in the first lane. V1 departed its lane of travel on the left side, crossed through the adjacent lane and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a one way roadway with four lanes of travel. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in the same direction, in the first lane. As V1 attempted to merge into the first lane, the frontal plane of V1 made impact with the left side plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was westbound approaching an intersection to pass through in the number 1 lane on a two-way not physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was approaching the same intersection traveling north. Vehicle 1's front end and Vehicle 2's right side made contact with each other in the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 lost control and ran off the right side of the roadway.  Vehicle 1 started to rotate counter clockwise. V1 was traveling west on a two way, five lane, undivided roadway, proceeding straight through a four leg intersection. V1 steered right to avoid an oncoming vehicle and struck a curb with its left front wheel. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact headed north west..

V1 was traveling westbound on a 4 lane, non-positively divided, roadway. Vehicle's #2 & #3 were traveling eastbound on the same roadway. Vehicles #1, #2, and #3 were going eastbound on a eleven lane positively divided roadway in lane one. Vehicle #1 contacted the back plane of Vehicle #2 with its frontal plane. V1 and V2 were both traveling south on a major highway. V2 was traveling in the lane to the right of V1. V1 changed lanes to the right. The front of V1 impacted the back of the trailer of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane roadway with a divider to the left of the roadway between the east and westbound traffic. V1 departed the roadway to the left and entered a grassy median. The front of V1 impacted the concrete base of a light pole located on the median.

V1 was stopped in the second lane of travel facing northwest on a two way, 4 lane road, attempting to turn left. V2 was behind V1, also stopped, facing northwest in the second lane of travel.  V3, traveling in the second lane, going northwest, behind V2, impacted the back of V2 with its frontal plane. The front of V2 then impacted the rear of V1.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road, passing through an intersection. V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road, passing through the same intersection. V1 was traveling west following a two way, two lane road. V1 was originally traveling in the left lane, negotiating a right curve in the road. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left. V1 was traveling southwest on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a right hand curve. Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way roadway negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1 departed the right road edge and the front plane contacted two mailboxes. Vehicle 1 continued off road and the right plane contacted a house. Vehicle 1 then contacted a tree with its front plane.

V1 was eastbound on lane one of a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. While attempting to negotiate a right hand curve, V1 departed the right side of the roadway in a clockwise yaw. V1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a "Y" intersection. V1 traveled into the center area between the roadways. V1 was traveling north following a two-way, three lane road in the second lane of travel. V2 was traveling in front of V1 on the same roadway and same travel lane. V2 stopped in traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling south in lane one of a three lane roadway. V2 was traveling east in lane two of a four lane intersecting roadway. V1 and V2 both entered the intersection where the right plane of V1 impacted with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling north east in the #1 lane of a two lane road. V2 was traveling north west in the #1 lane of a two lane road. V1 was westbound on two-lane, two-way road divided by a left turn lane. V1 departed the roadway right side striking the corner face of a guardrail. V1 was traveling North on a two-lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the right road edge and the front of V1 contacted a guardrail end. V1 continued forward striking down 23 folding guardrail posts. While rotating the front of V1 contacted  the face of the guardrail continuing to rotate a total of 180 coming to final rest facing South on the bridge. V1 was traveling north on a two lane non divided road driving towards a T-Intersection. V1 continued straight through the intersection and departed the north road edge. The undercarriage of V1 contacted a ditch as it drove into a grassy area and came to rest.

V1 was traveling westbound in the right lane of a two way roadway.  V1 departed its original travel lane on the left and continued to crossover and depart the roadway on the left side. V1's right side wheels/tires came into contact with a curb, and its front end came into contact with a light pole.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound in the number one lane on two-way, not physically divided roadway when the vehicle lost control negotiating a curve left. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right, went up an embankment, contacted a bush with its front while going airborne, and proceeded down into a ditch. The vehicle rotated counterclockwise and rolled primary to the right 6 quarter turns coming to final rest on its roof. V1 caught fire.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in the number one lane on two-way, not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was approaching the same intersection traveling north and attempting to make a left hand turn. Vehicle 1's left side contact Vehicle 2's front in the intersection. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right on the southwest corner. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with fence on the side of the roadway. Then, vehicle 2 right side made contact with a fire hydrant and came to final rest.

V1 was westbound on a non divided, two lane, bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. It then returned to the roadway, rotating clockwise and departed the roadway to the left, where it rolled left side leading, completing 6 quarter turns. During the rollover, V1 impacted a  small tree (left plane),  a second tree with its top plane (bed side) and a third tree with it's right plane before coming to final rest on its roof.
V1 was traveling south on a one-way, one-lane roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the left side and contacted the left side of V1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two lane undivided roadway making a left turn onto an intersecting roadway. Vehicle 1's right side plane was contacted by the frontal plane of Vehicle 2, which was traveling eastbound on the same roadway. After contact was made, Vehicle 1 continued to travel, rotating clockwise onto the intersecting roadway and contacting Vehicle 3. Vehicle 3 was parked. Vehicle 1's left side plane contacted the rear of Vehicle 3.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane roadway approaching a T-shaped intersection controlled by a stop sign. V1 continued north across the intersection where it departed the roadway on the north side. The front of V1 then contacted two trees where it came to final rest.

V1 and V2 was traveling northwest on a four lane divided roadway. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2 (Event 1). V2 departed the right side of the roadway and the right side plane impacted a guardrail (Event 2). V1 initiated a clockwise rotation with its left side leading. V1 departed the roadway to the left and initiated a left side leading rollover sequence (Event 3). V1 completed two quarter turns before coming to final rest on its top facing a northwest position. V2 was redirected back onto the roadway and the vehicle traversed the center median and the southeast travel lanes before its frontal plane impacted the guardrail (Event 4).

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane roadway passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling west approaching the same intersection. V2 front plane contacted V1 right plane. After initial impact with V2, V1 continued northwest and overturned on its right plane on roadside.

V4 was traveling south in lane No. 2 of an undivided four-lane trafficway and approaching a three-leg intersection. V1 was turning north from the west leg of the intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side plane of V4 (Event 1). Vehicle #4 continued south while rotating clockwise and the left side of V4 impacted with the front of V2 (Event 2). V2 was stopped at the south-leg of the intersection, facing north. The impact thrust V2 rearward (south) as its right side plane impacted the front of V3 which was traveling northbound in lane No. 1. The right side of V2 was secondarily contacted by the left side of V3 in a sideslap type impact (Event 4). V2 subsequently rolled in reverse across both south lanes coming to rest near the curb facing east.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two lane interstate. V2 began to slow down. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest close to point of impact.
V1 was traveling south on a five lane roadway behind V2. V2 stopped and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest close to point of impact

Vehicle #1 was traveling northbound on a two lane roadway attempting to traverse (cross) a four-leg intersection and proceed northerly. Vehicle #2 was traveling westbound on a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection.   Vehicle #1's right side was impacted by V2s frontal plane.

V1 was northwest on a three lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway traveling though an intersection. V2 was southeast on a two lane non divided, bidirectional roadway traveling through the same intersection, attempting to turn right. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2.
V1 was west bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, when a deer entered its path. V1 impacted the deer with its frontal plane.

V1 was traveling on the southbound on ramp when V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted the ground (Event 1). Then V1 entered the southbound roadway (3 lane physically divided roadway) and crossed all southbound lanes exiting the roadway to the left. V1 then continued to travel along the shoulder between south and northbound lanes. V1 then traveled off the edge of roadway whilst making contact (Event 2). V1 then continued traveling down the side of the overpass and its back end scraped against the bridge (Event 3) landing on the roadway below Event 4). V1 then continued to drive eastbound on a new roadway (4 lane non physically divided with 2 way turn lane). V1 departed and re-entered the roadway several times before coming to rest.
V1 was traveling southbound on a 2 lane roadway when the front of V1 contacted a dog running across the roadway. V1 was towed.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane divided trafficway. V1 braked to avoid a collision with V2. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 continued after the collision towards the northwest where the front of V1 impacted a guardrail face. After the collision with V1, V2 started to rotate clockwise and departed the roadway to the right where the front of V2 impacted a chain link fence. V2 continued to rotate and the left side contacted the fence.

V1 was heading south in the #1 lane of a 5 lane divided highway. V2 was heading south in the #2 lane of a 5 lane divided highway. V1 changed lanes to the left into the #2 lane behind V2. V2 began to stop while V1 attempted to change lanes to the left into the #3 lane. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. After impact V1 was stuck to the back of V2.

V2 was passing through an intersection while traveling west on a two-lane, two way road. V1 was passing through the same intersection while traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V2 came to rest on the right side of the road west of the intersection. V1 came to rest just off the right side of the road north of the intersection.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 was stopped behind a non-involved vehicle that was stopped and waiting to make a left turn. V2 was traveling west on the same two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front left corner of V2 struck the right rear corner of V1 causing damage to both. V1 came to final rest headed west in its initial travel lane. V2 came to rest headed west on the right road edge.

V1 was traveling westbound crossing through an intersection in the #1 lane of a 2 lane roadway. V2 was traveling north through an intersection in the #3 lane of a 3 lane roadway. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway to the left where the left rear tire impacted a curb.
V1 was traveling southbound in the number 2 lane of a 2 lane interstate. A deer entered the roadway to the left side. The left side of V1 impacted the deer. V1 came to rest in the center median.

V1 was traveling northbound in the #1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the #1 lane of a 3 lane roadway. V1 turned left in the intersection to head west. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 traveling north on a three lane undivided roadway. V2 was traveling west on a five lane divided roadway. V1 entered into the intersection to make a left turn. V2 entered the same intersection to cross through the intersection. The left of V1 impacted with the front of V2. V1 came to final rest facing a northeast direction close to impact. V2 came to final rest facing west close to impact.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted a deer.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a three lane one way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound approaching an intersection to turn left. Both vehicles entered the intersection and V1 contacted the front bumper on the front bumper of V2.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two-lane, two-way roadway entering a sign controlled intersection. V2 was traveling southwest on a three lane, divided roadway entering the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 contact the right plane of V1. After the initial impact, both v1 and v2 departed the roadway before coming to rest.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two lane, two way roadway. Vehicle 1 drove through some slush, and lost control. V1 departed the roadway to the left, and the front plane of V1 contacted an embankment. Vehicle 1's front plane then contacted a fence, and rolled-over four quarter turns to the right.

V1 and V2 were traveling south on an icy, unmarked, two-lane, two-way road with a significant downhill grade. V2 was attempting to make a right turn into a driveway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.
