V1 was east bound on a narrow two lane bidirectional roadway, negotiating a curve to the right. V2, a fully loaded log truck, was making a right hand, K-type turn onto the same roadway from a field road. While V2 was backing up across the roadway. V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling west in lane three on a three lane divided roadway approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one on the three lane undivided intersecting roadway. As V1 attempted to turn to its left and travel south V2 proceeded straight through the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a two-way, two lane road. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left and went on to depart the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a guardrail face on the left roadside. V1 returned to the road and departed the roadway on the right before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane non-divided roadway. V1 came to a curve to the right in the roadway. V1 exited the roadway off the left side, going over a slight embankment, hitting a road sign with the front right, and causing the sign to also hit the top of V1. V1 then proceeded to an area with trees, hitting several smaller trees with the left side of the vehicle, before hitting a larger tree with the front of the vehicle, and coming to rest.

V1 was traveling south one a one-way on-ramp negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway and the RF and RR tires impacted a curb. The front of V1 then impacted a bush and an embankment. V1 rolled left 3-quarter turns coming to final rest on its right side facing an easterly direction on the roadway.

Vehicle one was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way, divided roadway without a positive barrier in the number 1 lane. Vehicle one departed the lane to the left, returned to the lane, and then departed the roadway to the right. Vehicle one struck two palm trees on the right side of the roadway and came to final rest against a metal fence that caused no damage.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the left lane line, then departed the left road edge. V1 contacted a small tree with its frontal plane as it began to travel down a slope. The front of V1 then contacted a stream culvert. V1 then rolled to the left one quarter turn and the A pillars of V1 contacted a tree.

V1 and V2 were heading east on a 5 lane roadway. V1 slowed for traffic ahead. V2 began to change lanes. The rear of V1 impacted with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest close to point of impact.
V1 and V2 were traveling south in the #3 lane of a 4 lane divided highway. V2 slowed due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the number 4 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane roadway. V1 made a left turn across the path of V2. V2 attempted to steer to the right to avoid the collision. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counter clockwise where the right rear of V1 impacted the left front of V2. V1 continued its momentum westbound where the front of V1 impacted a curb. V1 continued along the sidewalk before coming to rest partially on the roadway. V2 came to rest in the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest.  Vehicle #2 was traveling southeast on the same trafficway.  V2 began to turn left at an intersection and the right of V2 contacted the front of V1.  V2 rotated counterclockwise and the right of V2 contacted the left of V1.

V1 was traveling southwest, following a two way, two lane road in the left lane of travel. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left, continuing on to depart the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a sign. V1 continued traveling off roadway. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V2 was legally parked. After impact, V2 spun clockwise impacting the right side of V3 with its frontal plane. V3 was legally parked. V1 reentered the roadway on the right, crossed the second travel lane and continued to depart the roadway to the right. V1 reentered the roadway on the left into the first lane of travel. V1 departed its travel lane to the left. V1 then returned to its travel lane impacting the back of V4 with its frontal plane. V4 was legally parked. The impact to V4 caused the front of V4 to impact the back of V5. V5 was legally parked. V1 rotated clockwise facing southeast. V1 continued on to depart the roadway to the left, impacting a light pole with its frontal plane.

V1 was traveling east in the first lane, on a two way, non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in the first lane on a two way, non-physically divided roadway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection. The front of V1 impacted with the left side of V2 (event 1). V2 continued north, V1 rotated counter clockwise, The right side of V1 impacted with the left side of V2 (event 2). V1 and V2 came to final rest facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. This caused V2 to rotate clockwise and its left rear wheel struck a curb. V2 then impacted a metal railing with its left side, coming to rest off of the roadway facing east.
V1, V2, and V3 were traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road with V3 leading and V1 trailing. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The front of V2 then impacted the back of V3.
V1 was backing south down a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 was parked legally behind V1 facing north along the east curb.  The back of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way roadway.  V1 departed the road to the left and the right side of V1 contacted a mailbox post.  V1 steered right, returned to the road and rotated clockwise as it crossed both lanes to the right.  V1 departed the roadway to the right with its left side leading then tripped and rolled left through a ditch.  As V1 rolled, the top contacted a large tree trunk.  V1 continued to roll left completing 4-quarter turns and came to rest on its wheels.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway negotiating a curve to the left.  V1 departed the roadway to the right then returned to the roadway and departed the roadway to the left in a counter-clockwise yaw.  The right side of V1 then struck two trees and came to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was attempting a left hand turn to travel south at an intersection. Vehicle 2 was also attempting a left hand turn at the same intersection. Vehicle 1's left side and Vehicle 2's front made contact with each other.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling in the number 1 lane on a 5-lane physically divided two-way roadway. Vehicle 1 lost control of the vehicle for unknown reasons and departed her lane to the right making contact with the jersey barrier with the vehicle front end. Vehicle 1 continued its clockwise rotation contacted the jersey barrier a second time with the left side of the vehicle. Then Vehicle 1's left and Vehicle 2's front made contact with each other.

Vehicle #1 was stopped at an intersection facing north.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west on an intersecting roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated counterclockwise and V2 rotated clockwise.  The right of V1 contacted the left of V2.

V1, V2 and V3 were all  traveling east on a two-lane exit ramp. V2 and V3 were stopped ahead of V1. V1 impacted the back of V2 (event 1). Subsequently, the front of V2 impacted the back of V3 (event 2).

V1 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a four lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a four lane two-way undivided roadway behind V1. V1 braked to avoid stopped traffic ahead. The frontal plane of V2 contacted the rear plane of V1.

V1 was traveling south departing a parking lot and began to turn right on the roadway. V2 was traveling west in lane 1 of a two lane divided roadway. The front plane of V2 impacted the left side plane of V1 as V1 entered the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in a parking lot. V1 made a left turn to go eastbound on a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling eastbound in the right lane of the same roadway. The right side plane of V1 made impact with the frontal plane of V2.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling South. V2 stopped in traffic and the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

Vehicles #1, #2, and #3 were traveling east, approaching an intersection. V3 stopped for traffic. V2 slowed for traffic. The front of V1 contacted the left plane of V2, and V1's RF wheel got pinched between V2's LR wheel and the wheel well, causing V1 to "pop up" onto its left tires at a roughly 20 degree tilt. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V3. V1 rode up over the bed of V3 and rolled over four quarter turns to the left.
Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two lane two way roadway.  Vehicle 2 was eastbound on the same roadway.  Vehicle 1 left front side struck vehicle 2 right back end.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 struck a deer with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the south side of the road facing east.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a stop sign. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 attempted to turn left to head eastbound. V1 continued straight through the intersection and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the left side of V2 (Event 1.) V1 continued straight and the frontal plane of V1 contacted a sign (Event 2). The frontal plane of V1 then contacted a rock (Event 3). V1 continued forward and the frontal plane of V1 contacted a tree (Event 4) while coming to final rest.

Vehicle 2 was coming down off an overpass heading eastbound. Vehicle 1 was traveling behind vehicle 2. Vehicle 2 applied their brakes and the front of vehicle 1 made contact with the rear of vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 was towed from the scene.
V1 was traveling north in lane 1 of a a two-lane, two-way road. V2 was legally parked facing the same direction. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a westbound one way street. V1 traveled across an intersecting road with four lanes, making an end departure with its front wheels impacting a curb. The front of V1 then impacted a non-breakaway pole, a fence, and a tree before coming to final rest.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane one of a two-lane two-way roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north in lane two of a three-lane two-way intersecting roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise, departed the road to the right and the left of V1 contacted a sign post.

V1 was traveling southbound in the fourth lane of a four lane, one- way roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the same lane, ahead of V1. A pedestrian was attempting to cross the roadway. V2 stopped to allow pedestrian to cross. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was stopped facing eastbound at a T intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on the intersecting 5 lane non divided roadway. As V1 attempted to make the left hand turn the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V2 then began to yaw clockwise and tripped over V2 wheels and tires on the paved roadway. V2 overturned 4 quarter turns and came to rest on its wheels.
V1 was west bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, when a deer entered the roadway. V1 impacted the animal with it's frontal plane.

V1 entered a driveway to a parking lot traveling northbound from an unknown direction of travel on a four-lane, not physically divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a picket fence, crossed an alley, where the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2 which was parked in a private parking space facing north. V1 came to final rest facing north at the point of impact with V2.

V1 was traveling east, in the second lane, on a two way non- physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in the first lane. V1 departed lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 then departed roadway and impacted the left front tire of vehicle with the curb. V1 came to final rest on the sidewalk facing east. V2 came to final rest facing north straddling the east and west bound lanes.

V1 and V2 were northbound on a three lane interstate when V1 slowed abruptly.  The front of V2 impacted with the rear of V1.  A trailer being towed by V2 separated and impacted the rear of V2. V1 came to final rest facing northbound close to the point of impact.  V2 came to final rest facing northwest near point of impact.  V2 then experienced a post-crash fire.

V1, V2, and V3 were northbound on a 3 lane interstate roadway. V2 decelerated for traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2 (event 1). The front of V3 impacted with the rear of V1 (event 2). All vehicles came to final rest near point of impact.

V1 was traveling west bound on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway in the number 2 lane crossing through the intersection.  V2 was traveling east bound on 6 lane non-physically divided roadway in the left turn lane.  V2 was making a left turn when the front of V1 made contact with the front of V2.  Both vehicles were disabled and required towing.

V1 was making a left hand turn through an intersection and was traveling from north to west on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane 2 (of four lanes). V2 was traveling south through the same intersection on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane 2 (of four lanes). V3 was stopped at the entrance to the same intersection and was facing east on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane 2 (of four lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V2 contacted the right side of V1. The front end of V1 then contacted the front end of V3.
V1 was traveling east on a four lane two-way roadway. V1 departed the right side roadway, and the front plane of V1 struck a utility pole before it came to final rest.

V1 was negotiating a curve, traveling east on a two way, two lane road. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left and went onto depart the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 impacted a utility pole. V1 began a counterclockwise yaw and contacted a mailbox post and then a street sign with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off the left side of the road.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southbound in lane one. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and contacted the front on a sign.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection in lane one.  V2 was traveling northwest on the same roadway approaching the same intersection in lane 1 in front of V1. V1 entered into the southbound lane as V2 was turning left.  The front plane of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  After the initial impact V1 continued toward the western road edge contacting the face of a guardrail with its left plane.  V2 came to final rest on the roadway and V1 came to final rest against the face of the guardrail.

V1 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way road approaching a sharp curve to the right.  V1 departed the left side of the road and impacted its left front wheel on a curb. V1 then impacted a tree with it's front causing it to rotate clockwise.  The left side of V1 impacted the rear of V2 which was parked in a parking lot on the left side of the road.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two-lane, two-way road passing through an intersection.  V2 was traveling northeast on a two-lane, two-way road passing through the same intersection.  The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2

V1 was traveling south and turning left out of a driveway onto a two-way, four lane road.  V2 was traveling west in lane 2 on the two-way, four lane road.  The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was following V2, traveling north on a two-way, two lane roadway. V2 stopped on roadway in anticipation of turning left. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 went on to depart the roadway to the right.The front of V1 made impact with a tree before coming to final rest.

V1 was eastbound on a four lane roadway divided by a grass median. While attempting to negotiate a left hand curve V1 lost control and departed the right side (south) of the roadway in a counter clockwise yaw. The undercarriage of V1 impacted the ground causing damage. V1 then traveled up an embankment striking a tree with the left side causing damage. Upon impact rotated clockwise coming to final rest facing north.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 came upon another vehicle in its initial travel lane traveling at a lower speed. V1 steered to the left to avoid hitting the NCV, departing the north side of the road. V1 then traveled down an embankment striking  three trees with the right plane, front plane, and left plane. V1 came to final rest at the point of impact facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west approaching an intersection attempting to turn left. Vehicle 2 was traveling northwest approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1 was towing a utility trailer. Vehicle 1's utility trailer was contacted on the left plane by the front plane of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 left the scene.

V1 was westbound on a six lane two way roadway. V2 was eastbound on a six lane two way roadway. V2 was approaching the intersection preparing to make a left turn.  V1 was approaching the same intersection going straight.The front of V2 impacted the front of V1.  V1 came to final rest facing eastbound. V2 came to final rest facing northbound.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and then re-entered the roadway on the right side. V1 then departed the lane on the left side and the roadway on the left.  V1 re-entered the roadway on the left side and the vehicle rolled, left side leading, two quarter turns.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in the number one lane on a one-way, two-lane not physically divided roadway. Vehicle Two, a semi-truck, was also traveling in the number one lane traveling in the same direction. Vehicle One's front and Vehicle 2s back made contact with each other. Vehicle One then departed the roadway to the left and contacted a tree with its front bumper before coming to rest.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two lane, two way roadway. Vehicle 2 was northbound on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 departed its lane to the left, and the front end of V1 struck the front end of vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling northwest in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right where the front of V1 impacted a utility pole. After the initial impact V1 rotated clockwise and the left side of V1 impacted a guide wire anchor. V2 continued rotating clockwise and came to rest facing southwest between both points of impact.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the road to the left and began to rotate clockwise. The left plane of V1 contacted a fiberglass road edge reflector, then a utility pole and its guy wire.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were both traveling south on a four lane, positively divided roadway.  V1 was in lane two and V2 was in lane three. V1 changed lanes to its left and entered lane three of southbound travel.  V1's frontal plane then contacted V2's rear plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two lane median divided roadway, making a left turn within the intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north on the same roadway and entered the intersection. Vehicle #1 frontal plane was contacted by Vehicle #2's frontal plane.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The driver of V1 initiated a left turn sequence as the frontal plane of V2 impacted the front plane of V1 at an obtuse angle impact. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling west in lane three of a seven lane non divided roadway. V2 stopped and V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was stopped at a stop sign facing south in lane one of a 2 lane non-divided roadway. V2 was westbound in lane 1 of a 5 lane non-divided roadway. V1 continued forward and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 2 lane divided roadway when the vehicle departed the right side of the roadway and struck the end of a guardrail with the frontal plane of the vehicle. The undercarriage of the vehicle then contacted the guardrail debris with its undercarriage.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 5 lane two way non physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a 3 lane two way non physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 entered the intersection. Vehicle 1 also entered the intersection. The front of V1 made contact to the right front side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a 2 lane non physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a 2 lane non physically divided roadway. The front of vehicle 1 made contact with the right rear of vehicle 2.
Vehicle #1, Vehicle #2, and Vehicle #3 were traveling east bound in lane 1 of a 2 way trafficway. V1 contacted its front on the back of V2. V2 contacted its front on the back of V3.

V1 was heading north on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway. V2 was heading north on the same roadway. V2 crossed the right lane line and V2 right side contacted V1 on the front left panel. V1 rolled to the right contacting a guardrail with the top plane, then rolled back to the left coming to final rest on its wheels on the road way. V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, one way highway. V1 started to skid clockwise longitudinally crossing the left lane line, contacting a guardrail with the left side. V1 then contacted the same guardrail with the left front panel. V1 reentered the road way crossing two lanes then contacting the right side on a guardrail. V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A moose entered V1's travel lane from the left and made contact with the front and continued down the left plane of V1. V1 remained on the roadway and came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling on a one way roadway in an easterly direction. V2 stopped for traffic and V1's front contacted V2's back.
V1 was traveling westbound on a major highway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted a bridge pillar. V1 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing southeast.

V1 was traveling east on the exit ramp of a major highway. V1 was pushed by a police car, due to possible car trouble. Upon entering the service road of the highway, V1 became disengaged from the police car and started to drive on its own again. The driver of V1 could not gain control of the vehicle or stop it and decided to steer V1 off the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted the breakaway pole of a traffic sign. The breakaway pole then contacted the top of V1 as V1 continued to drive off road. The front of V1 then impacted the pole of a traffic signal with its front.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane undivided road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound approaching the same intersection. V1 attempted to cross the intersection to turn left. In the intersection the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V1 rotated clockwise, V2 continued straight. The right side of V2 then sideswiped the right side of V1.
V1 was traveling southbound on a 5 lane divided roadway in the number 4 lane. V2 was stopped due to traffic on a 5 lane divided roadway in the number 4 lane. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling east in the #1 lane of a 4 lane roadway. V2 and V3 began to slow down due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward and the front of V2 impacted the back of V3.
V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 struck an embankment.

V1 has traveling north on a three lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a three lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 in the intersection. V2 began a counter-clockwise yaw and contacted a light pole in the north east corner of the intersection with it's right side.
V1 was traveling northeast in the sixth lane on a nine lane, two way roadway.  V2 was stopped ahead of V1 facing northeast.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V2 was traveling north in lane 1 of a three lane non-divided roadway, passing through an intersection. V1 was traveling south in lane 2 of the same roadway and turned left at the intersection. The front plane of V2 impacted the right plane of V1.
V1 attempted to make a left turn from a private drive. V2 was traveling northbound on a 2 lane roadway approaching V1. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two-way roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on a two lane, two-way roadway, approaching the same intersection.  The front of V2 made contact with the left side of V1. V1 rotated counter-clockwise, coming to final rest, off the roadway, facing southeast.  V2 came to final rest on the roadway facing east.

V1 was traveling southbound on a three lane undivided roadway approaching an four-intersection. V2 was traveling northbound on a three-lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 initiated a left turn at the intersection as the frontal plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2. V2 was deflected towards the southwest intersection quadrant where it rolled one-quarter (1/4) turn onto its left side plane.

V1 was traveling east in lane 2 on a 5-lane roadway.  V2 was traveling east in lane 1 on the same roadway.  V3 was traveling west in lane 2 on the same roadway when it traveled left across the center turn lane and its front plane contacted the right side of V1.  V3 continued across the eastbound lanes to the left and its front plane contacted the left side of V2.  V3 then departed the left road edge and contacted a shallow brick wall with its front plane.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a four-lane, divided roadway. The driver of Vehicle #1 was in the left turn lane and initiated a left turn, to proceed westerly. Vehicle #2 was traveling west in the center through travel-lane on the three-lane divided roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection as Vehicle #1s frontal plane impacted Vehicle #2s frontal plane.

V1 was traveling west in lane one on a three-lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection under road construction.  V2 was traveling east in the left turn lane on the same roadway approaching the intersection.  As V2 turned left at the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on the intersecting single lane roadway. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a five lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a five lane, one way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way physically divided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway to the left contacting a concrete barrier with its front plane. The left side of V1 then contacted the concrete barrier again.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling north on a five lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.  V1 then rotated clockwise and the left rear tire of V1 contacted a curb.  V2 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V2 contacted a steel utility pole.  Both vehicles came to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north around a left curve. The right front tire experienced a blow out.  V1 departed the road to the right and the right plane of V1 contacted a tree. The front plane of V1 contacted two trees, then the right side contacted a tree, then the front plane contacted a final tree.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northeast. V1 almost departed the road to the right, overcorrected and began rotating counter-clockwise. V1 tripped over six quarter turns to the right and came to rest atop a boulder.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling eastbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, the left side plane of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling east.  V2 stopped, intending to turn left.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast on a one way two lane roadway in lane one. Vehicle 1 departed the road to the right, striking a curb, then a tree with its front plane. Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise, and rolled two quarter turns to the left

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection going straight; V2 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane one of a one way highway with four lanes of travel. V1 then departed lane one on the left side, and continued to depart lane two and lane three on the left side. V1 then departed the roadway on the left side and the frontal plane of V1 made contact with a concrete traffic barrier.

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 on a 5 lane two way traffic way.  V1 departed the roadway to right impacting a tree with the front plane.  V1 returned to and crossed the roadway to the left then departed the left road and contacted a curb with its left front wheel. The vehicle crossed the sidewalk and impacted a retaining wall with the front plane.
Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound. Driver of V1 attempted to make a left turn. Vehicle 1 traveled off of the left side of the roadway and made contact with a barbed wire fence.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling north on a four lane interstate. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2 (event 1). V2 spun counter clockwise and the rear of V2 impacted with the right of V3 (event 2).  V1 departed the road and contacted the concrete barrier wall with the right side (event 3).
V1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a mailbox and then a utility pole. V1 came to final rest at point of impact.

V1 was traveling west on a 2 lane undivided roadway. V1 steered right to avoid another vehicle and departed the roadway to the right impacting a ditch with its undercarriage. V1 reentered the roadway to the left and came to final rest in the original lane of travel facing west.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two-lane, two-way, non-divided highway negotiating a right curve in the roadway. V2 was traveling northeast on the same two- lane, two- way, non-divided highway negotiating the left curve. V2 slightly traveled into the opposing lane as V1 and V2 simultaneously entered a 90 degree turn in the roadway, traveling in opposite directions. The left side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a major highway in lane four of four. Due to traffic V1 slowed and the front of V2 impacted the back of V1.
V1 and V2 were both traveling south on a major highway. V1 decelerated and came to a stop in its lane. The front of V2 impacted the back of V1.

V1 was traveling southbound approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling northbound approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V2 attempted to turn left. During the intersection the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 and V2 were both headed east bound on a 4 lane one way roadway. V1 was in lane 2, turning left. V2 was in lane 1, also turning left. V1's right side contacted V2's left side as both vehicles turned left at the intersection.

V1 was traveling north on a straight roadway, approaching an intersection. At the intersection V1 turned right. V1 departed the roadway to the left and impacted the north curb of the westbound lanes with both left side wheels.

V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V2 turned left into the northbound lanes. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 started to rotate clockwise and departed the road to the right. The right front wheel of V2 impacted a curb. V2 continued to drive off the road and entered a steep concrete embankment. V2 impacted a small tree and a wooden fence at the top of the embankment with its undercarriage. V2 rolled over, left side leading, 2 quarter turns, falling back onto the roadway.

V1 was traveling in lane two of a four lane two way divided by a painted median roadway. V1 attempted to change lanes to the right however there was a vehicle in the lane. V1 attempted to go back into lane two when it lost control and exited the roadway on the left. V1 then entered lane two of the opposing traffic lanes before attempting to travel back into its original lane. However V1 over corrected and begun to spin clockwise back into the original traffic way before exited the roadway to the right in yaw. The back left of V1 contacted a utility pole coming to final rest against the pole.

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway from the right hand side of the roadway and struck the front plane of V1. After contact with the deer, V1 continued southbound and departed the roadway on the lefthand side where the front plane struck a small tree.
V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two lane roadway. V2 was stopped in road waiting to make a left turn. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V2 was westbound on a 4 lane, two-way roadway.  V1 was eastbound on the same roadway, attempting to turn left.  V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time and the front plane of V2 struck the front plane of V1.

V1 was traveling southwest in the second lane on a three lane non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling southeast in the first lane on a two lane non-physically divided roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection, and the front of V2 impacted with the right of V1. V2 rotated clockwise and came to final rest facing southwest. V1 departed roadway to the left and contacted a utility box. V1 then fled the scene.
V1 and V2 were traveling east in the first lane on a two way non-physically divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest in original lane facing east.

V1 was eastbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway. V2 was northbound on a two-lane undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 then traveled counterclockwise and departed roadway and proceeded to roll over 3 quarter turns. While rolling, the left side contacted a rock and then a post. V2 came to final rest on its left side. V1 came to final rest facing northeast off the roadway.
V1 was traveling east in lane 2 of a 5 lane non-divided, two way roadway. A deer entered the roadway front the north road edge and the deer contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling east on a channelized lane. V2 was also traveling east on a roadway that connects to the channelized lane. V1 merged left into the traffic and its left side impacted the right side of V2.
V1 was south bound in lane 2 of a four lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left, where it impacted a cable barrier with its frontal, left and top plane.

V1 was negotiating a curve, traveling north on a two-way, two lane roadway. V1 departed its original travel lane to the left. V1 then returned to its original travel lane and continued on to depart the roadway on the right. The front of V1 impacted a tree (event 1)  and spun clockwise impacting another tree with its left plane (event 2). V1 began to roll (event 3) and its top contacted a third tree (event 4). V1 came to final rest facing the road on all four tires.

V2, V3, and V4 were legally parked facing northeast on the side of a 2 lane, two way roadway. V1 was traveling southwest in lane 1 of the same 2 lane, two way roadway when it's front plane contacted the front planes of V2, V3, and V4 before coming to final rest behind all of the vehicles.

V1 was traveling westbound on a 3 lane roadway and V2 and V3 were traveling eastbound on the same roadway. V1 traveled over the lane lines to the left and V1's front contacted V2's front. V1 then rotated clockwise and V1's left contacted a guard rail.  V3's front contacted V2's back.

V1 was southbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway then returned to the roadway crossing the left lane and departing the left side of the roadway in a counter clockwise rotation. V1 traveled down an embankment striking a utility marker with the right side plane, then hit a culvert with the right rear wheel causing damage initiating the roll. V1 then struck a stop sign and road sign with the right side plane before overturning right side leading 4 quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on the southeast side of the roadway facing northeast.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound in lane one approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north bound in lane one approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in lane two entering a four-legged, light controlled intersection attempting to turn left. Vehicle #2 was traveling south in lane one entering the same intersection. In the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 continued west and the right side contacted the front of V2 again.

V1 was traveling southbound backing down a single lane roadway. V2 and V3 were parked legally on the left side of the roadway facing north. V1 departed the roadway at left and the rear plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2 (Event 1). V1 then pushed V2 while re-entering the roadway at right. V2 was pushed off the roadway at right and came to final rest. V1 proceeded forward and backed again departing the roadway at left. The rear plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V3 (Event 2). V1 proceeded to go forward again to re-enter roadway at right but was hooked onto V3 and entered final rest.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway.  V1 attempted a 'U' turn ahead of V2 and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  V2 then departed the roadway to the left and the left side of V2 struck a utility pole.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway. V2 was traveling east on the same two lane two roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was heading south in the #1 lane of a 2 lane road attempting to turn left and head east. V2 was traveling west in the #1 lane of a 5 lane roadway. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. After the first impact an unknown part of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. As V1 was negotiating a curve in the roadway, it departed its original travel lane on the left and continued on to depart the roadway on the left side. The frontal plane of V1 made contact with a sign post and then continued forward and made contact with a cement pillar.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane two of a divided highway with three lanes of travel and an entrance ramp lane. V2 was traveling westbound entering the same roadway on the entrance ramp. V1 attempted to merge onto entrance ramp and the right side plane of V1 made contact with the left side plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east in lane 5 on a 9-lane roadway.  V1 turned left at the intersection and departed the road to the right.  The front plane of V1 contacted the concrete base of a utility pole, then a concrete wall.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two way, four lane roadway with a two way turn lane.  Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right.  Vehicle 1's front plane struck a basalt column.  Vehicle 1 rolled eight quarter turns coming to rest facing southeast on the westbound shoulder.  The driver was ejected out of the right side window during the rollover.
Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest.  Vehicle #2 was traveling southeast on the same trafficway.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east, negotiating a left curve.  V1 departed the road to the right.  The front of V1 contacted a sign post.  The front of V1 then contacted a tree.  V1 began to rotate clockwise.  The front of V1 contacted another tree and the left of V1 contacted 6 trees.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 (of two lanes) on a two-way, not physically divided roadway.  After two back-to-back roadway departures and returns (all on the right side), V1 overturned on the roadway (4 quarter turns, leading right).

V1, V2 and V3 were traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 2 (of five lanes), with V1 directly behind V2 and V2 directly behind V3. V2 and V3 were slowed to a stop in response to traffic ahead. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2, pushing V2 forward where the front end of V2 contacted the back end of V3.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 (of three lanes) on a two-way, not physically divided roadway (with two-way left turn lane) and was approaching V2, which was legally parked, facing south along the west curb edge of the same roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right, and its front end contacted the back end of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in the number 3 on a two-way not physically divided roadway attempting to make a left hand turn to head east. Vehicle 2 was traveling north in the number 2 lane approaching the same intersection that Vehicle 1 was turning. Vehicle 1's right side made contact with Vehicle 2's front end. Vehicle 2 departed the roadway to the right and made contact with a traffic signal on the northeast corner of the intersection.

V1 was traveling southwest on a two-way, three-lane road. V2 was legally parked on the right side of the road facing the same direction. V1 departed the right side of the road and traveled over a section of sidewalk that extended into the road, then entered the parking lanes on the right side of the roadway.  The front plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway and V2 was traveling east on the same roadway when the front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. V1 came to final rest on the roadway, and V2 came to final rest partially off the roadway.

V2 was traveling northwest in lane 3 of a 7 lane, two way, non-divided roadway. V1 was traveling southeast in lane 4 of the same roadway, and was turning left onto a two way private driveway. V3 was traveling west in lane 1 of the 2 lane private driveway, and had stopped to exit the driveway. V2's frontal plane contacted the right side plane of V1. Due to the impact, V1's left side plane then contacted the left side plane of V3 before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane two way roadway with a sharp right-hand curve. V1 traveled into the on coming traffic lane before traveling off the roadway on the left side where the front struck a tree.  V1  continued to travel in a  counterclockwise rotation where V1 began a right side rollover for one quarter turn where V1's top impacted a tree and came to final rest against the tree on its right side.

V1 was towing a 2 axle horse trailer and traveling north in lane 1 of a 2 lane non-divided roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in lane 1 on the same roadway. V1 was traveling on the right edge of the roadway and the front plane of the right side mirror impacted a sign, then trailer's right side tires dropped off the right edge of pavement and impacted a ditch embankment pulling the rear of V1 to the right. V1 then departed lane 1 to the left and the front plane of V1 impacted the front plane of V2

V1 was traveling north in lane 2 of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 4 of the 4 lane divided roadway and was turning left to proceed east on a two lane divided roadway. At the intersection, V2's front plane contacted the left side plane of V1, Due to the impact, V1 rotated in a counter clockwise direction and departed the roadway on the right side. The vehicle came to final rest in westward facing position and was located partially on a side walk, and partially in lane 1 of a 3 lane divided roadway.

V2 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 3 lane, two-way roadway and had stopped behind traffic at a traffic signal. V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of the same roadway behind V2, when its frontal plane contacted the back plane of V2.

V1 was eastbound on a five-lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 and V3 were westbound on the same five-lane roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 began to make a left turn in the intersection. V1 entered into the intersection at the same time V2 was making their left turn. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 (event 1). V2 rotated counter-clockwise to travel northbound across the westbound lanes, over a median, and the front of V2 impacted the left side of V3 (event 2). V2 and V3 came to final rest at their point of impact. V1 went off the roadway to the right, traveled down a decline, and came to final rest at the bottom of the decline.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling north bound approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west bound. V1 departed the roadway on the right. V1 re-entered the roadway from the right and departed the lane on the left and departed the roadway on the left. V1 contacted the front bumper on a tree.
V1 was south bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 deprted its lane of travel to the left, left the roadway to the left, and the front of V1 impacted a guardrail.

V1 was traveling east, in the first lane, on a four lane non-physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on the intersecting three lane, one way road.  Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V1 came to final rest in the intersection facing east. V2 came to final rest in the intersection facing north.
V1 and V2 were southbound in the first lane on a 3 lane physically divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest facing south in their original lane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southbound attempting to negotiate a right curve on a two lane roadway. Vehicle 1 failed to negotiate the curve and departed the roadway to the left. The driver then reentered the roadway and departed the right side of the roadway, yawing clockwise. Vehicle 1's front then made contact with an embankment.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a three lane, non-divided roadway entering a light controlled four-legged intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane two entering the same light controlled intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. After the initial impact, V1s left side and V2s right side contacted each other. V2 then departed the southeast apex of the roadway and the front of V2 contacted a barrier.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway as a deer approached V1 from the western road edge.  V1 departed the right side of the roadway (east) before striking a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling southbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, the right plane of V1 made impact with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling northbound on a one way roadway with a single lane of travel. V3 was parked facing westbound on the north side of the roadway. At the intersection, the front plane of V1 made impact with the left side plane of V2. V2 then rotated counter clockwise and the back plane of V2 then impacted the frontal plane of V3.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A deer crossed the roadway in front of V1. V1 struck the deer with its frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway heading east.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the right side of southbound travel lane (west). V1 overturned four quarter turns.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest and departed its travel lane to the left. Vehicle 1 then departed the left road edge into a ditch where the front plane contacted a culvert.

Vehicle 2 and Vehicle 3 were stopped due to traffic. Vehicle 1 approached the stopped traffic and the front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the rear plane of Vehicle 2. The front plane of Vehicle 2 then contacted the rear plane of Vehicle 3.
Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling southwest approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's left plane.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southeast in lane 1 of a 3 lane roadway.  V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a portable road sign.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane 3 of a 3 lane roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west in lane 2 of a 4 lane roadway.  V1 began to turn left at an intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 then began to rotate clockwise where the right wheels struck the curb causing damage. V1 continued to strike a utility pole with the right side of its back plane, V1 continued to rotate and struck the same pole with the left side of its back plane.

V1 traveling eastbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling southbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the left side plane of V1. After the impact, V2 continued to travel in the southwest direction and departed the roadway on the right side. The frontal plane of V2 made contact with a fence.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling northbound in lane two of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, the left side plane of V1 made impact with the frontal plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling east on a two-way physically divided roadway in the number 3 lane. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with Vehicle 2's rear end, then Vehicle 2 lost control and departed the roadway to the right where the front of Vehicle 2 contacted a traffic barrier. Vehicle 1 came to final rest facing west. Vehicle 2 came to final rest facing east.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two-way, four-lane roadway negotiating a left curve.  Vehicle 1 departed the road to the right.  Vehicle 1 returned to the road, then over-corrected and departed the road to the right a second time, beginning to rotate clockwise.  Vehicle 1 tripped and rolled four quarter turns along the embankment on the north side of the road coming to rest partially on the road on its wheels. The driver of V1 was ejected during the roll.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way roadway. V2 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 was attempting to crossover the intersection. The right side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise with the frontal plane impacting a curb. V2 rotated clockwise in the roadway before coming to rest. V1 continued and impacted a curb/barrier with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest in front of shrubs.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a three lane two way non physically divided roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling west on a 2 lane one way non physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1 entered the intersection, Vehicle 2 entered the intersection. Vehicle 1's front made contact with the left side of V2.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were all traveling northeast in the #4 lane of a 4 lane divided highway. V3 and V4 were stopped due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V3. V3 was pushed forward where the front of V3 impacted the back of V4. The front of V2 then impacted the back of V1. V1 was pushed forward where the front of V1 impacted the back of V3 again.

V1 was traveling southwest in the #1 lane on a 2 lane roadway that was a bridged interchange to a highway. V1 departed the roadway on the right and the front of V1 impacted a concrete bridge wall/barrier. V1 re-entered the roadway on the right, crossed both lanes of traffic to the left, and departed the roadway on the left. The front of V1 impacted a concrete bridge wall/barrier.

V1 was traveling northeast in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southeast in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane divided roadway approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a three lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a four lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 in the intersection. V2 departed the roadway to the north and the left side of V2 contacted a utility pole.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane, two way median divided roadway.  V1 swerved to the left to avoid a deer and V1 departed the roadway and rolled one quarter turn.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway on its driver's side.

V1 entered a one-way, westbound Interstate exit ramp, and traveled east in lane 1 (of two lanes). V2 was traveling west on the same roadway, and was in lane 2. V1 was moved into lane 2, and the front end of V1 contacted the front end of V2.

Vehicle 1, 2 and 3 were traveling south on a two-way not physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1 was in the number 4 lane. Vehicle 2 was in the number 3 lane. Vehicle 3 was in the number 1 lane. Vehicle 1's right side made contact with Vehicle 2's left side. Vehicle 2 lost control after impact, the vehicle then impacted the center median then crossed all lanes on traffic to the right. Vehicle 2's right made contact with a jersey barrier closes to lane 1 and rolled back into traffic. Vehicle 1's front end made contact with Vehicle 2's right side.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in the #2 lane on a two way, not physically divided roadway with a continuous left hand turn lane. Vehicle 2 was exiting a private drive attempting to make a left hand turn to head north. Vehicle 1's left side and Vehicle 2's front end made contact with each other. Final rest for both vehicles were in the general area of the initial impact facing the original path of travel.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way, not physically divided roadway in lane 1 (of four lanes) and was approaching V2, which was legally parked along the east curb of the road. The front of V1 then contacted the rear of V2.
V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed south side of the roadway contacting and embankment with an unknown plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) and was approaching V2, which was ahead in lane 1 at a lower steady speed.  V1 entered lane 1 to the rear of V2, and in response to the impending contact between the front end of V1 and the back end of V2's rearmost trailer, V1 was turned to the right (departing the roadway onto the shoulder).  Control over V1 was lost in this maneuver, and V1 returned to lane 1, where its left side and back end came into contact with the right side of V2's rearmost trailer.  V1 then departed the road on the right, and its front end came into contact with a fence.

V1 was traveling south around a left curve. V1 departed the road to the right and the front plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 rotated sharply counter-clockwise and turned over three quarter turns to the right.
V1 and V2 were traveling east in lane 1 of a 4 lane, two-way roadway. V2 had stopped for traffic when the frontal plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

V1 was west on a two lane roadway negotiating a right curve. V2 was east on a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 exited its lane of travel to the left. The front of V1 impacted with the front of V2. V2 was slightly redirected to the right. V2 exited its lane of travel to the the right where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling south on a three lane roadway in lane 2.  V2 was traveling north on the same roadway in lane 2.  V1 continued into the intersection, attempting to turn left direction.  The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.  Both V1 and V2 remained on the roadway at final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a two way non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.  V1 came to final rest at impact facing north.  V2 came to final rest in original lane facing south.

V1 was eastbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway and V2 was northbound on the intersecting two-lane, undivided roadway. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. V2 rotated clockwise, and came to final rest facing northeast.  V1 continued traveling and left scene.

V1 was traveling up an incline in lane one of a five-lane, two way divided trafficway. V1 then merged into lane three and proceeded to take a left turn. V2 was traveling south on the same trafficway in lane one. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1 causing V2 to rotate clockwise. V1 was then struck a curb with its LF tire and a sign post while yawing laterally to the left coming to rest on a median.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest negotiating a right curve. The driver lost control of the vehicle and departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. Vehicle 1 traveled down an embankment and rolled four quarter turns.
Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling southeast with Vehicle 2 ahead of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's rear plane.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling southwest approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 3 was traveling northeast approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1's left plane was contacted by Vehicle 2's front plane. Vehicles 1 and 2 then side slapped with V1's left plane contacting V2's right plane. V2 then departed it's travel lane to the left crossing over the center median. V2's front plane contacted V3's front plane. V3 departed the right road edge and its front plane contacted shrubbery.
Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling east on a two-way, physically divided roadway in the number 3 lane. Traffic began to slow when Vehicle 1's front end made contact Vehicle 2's rear.

This intersection is controlled by stop signs in the eastbound & westbound roadways. V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching a stop sign at the same intersection. V2 attempted to turn left to head northbound. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2.
V2 was traveling south in lane two of a four lane one way road. V1 was traveling in the same lane behind V2. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V2 and V3 were stopped in traffic for construction traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road. V1 was traveling east on the same road. V1 departed its lane left and its front impacted the front of V2. The rear of V2 then impacted the front of V3.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west in lane 1 of a 2 way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east turning left at an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling west crossing the same intersection. Vehicle 1's right plane was contacted by Vehicle 2's front plane within the intersection.  After impact, V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to rest in the northwest corner of the intersection and V2 came to rest in the north end of the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest when it departed the left road edge. The front of Vehicle 1 struck a metal pole (mailbox) and continued traveling off the roadway. The front of Vehicle 1 then struck a tree, riding up the trunk of the tree, and coming to final rest. The left front tire of Vehicle 1 was separated from the vehicle as a result of the impact.
Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two-way, two-lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was southbound in the same lane, stopped for traffic. The front of vehicle 1 contacted the back of Vehicle 2.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two way, two lane roadway, stopped on the right side of the road. Vehicle 2 was westbound on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 started a U-turn across the westbound lane. Vehicle 2's front plane struck the left side of vehicle 1. Vehicle 1's LEFT side struck Vehicle 2's RIGHT side.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 and V3 were southbound on the same roadway. V1 crossed the center line impacting the left side of V2's trailer with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 continued forward in the southbound lane impacting the front of V3 with the frontal plane causing damage. Upon impact, V1 spun counter clockwise into the northbound lane coming to final rest facing west. After impact, V3 departed the right side of the roadway traveling down an embankment coming to final rest facing south. V2 was able to pull to the side of the southbound lane facing south.

V1 was eastbound in lane one of a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a 4-leg intersection. V1 crossed through the intersection in a clockwise yaw departing the southeast corner of the intersection. The undercarriage of V1 impacted a ditch causing damage. V1 came to final rest off the southeast corner of the intersection facing south.

V1 was traveling westbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel and a left turning lane in the westbound direction, and two lanes of travel in the eastbound direction. V2 was traveling eastbound in the left turning lane attempting to make a left turn to go northbound on the same roadway. At the above intersection, the frontal plane of V1 made impact with the right side plane of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 stopped for traffic and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a  two-lane road negotiating a curve to the left.  V1 traveled across the northbound lane and departed the left side of the roadway. V1 began to yaw in a clockwise rotation on the dirt shoulder. The left side of V1 struck a 36 cm wooden utility pole. V1 then spun counter-clockwise and rolled right 4 quarter turns coming to rest facing south on its wheels.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two lane, two-way roadway, negotiating a curve to the left.  V1 departed the roadway on the right side, continued traveling off the roadway, coming to final rest when the front of V1 made contact with a tree.
V1 was facing east stopped in a crossover.  V2 was to the right of V1 turning left when the left side of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, physically divided roadway.  V1, while negotiating a left hand curve in the roadway, departed its initial travel lane over the left lane line, and then departed the left side of the roadway (southern side) striking the face of a guardrail with its frontal plane.  V1 then rolled onto its right side on the guardrail then rotated counter-clockwise and rolled back onto its wheels then onto its left side coming to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  A deer entered the roadway from the southern road edge contacting the frontal plane of V1.  V1 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane undivided roadway.  V2 was backing southbound into a private driveway, partially in the eastbound lane, facing north. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 came to final rest at impact, facing north.  V1 rotated clockwise, and came to final rest facing southwest between the first and second lanes.

V1 was traveling east in the first lane on a two-way non-physically divided roadway. V1 departed roadway to the right. The front right tire of V1 impacted with the curb (event 1). V1 continued traveling east until impacting the front of vehicle with a tree (event 2) and coming to final rest in front of the tree facing east in the first lane.

V1 was traveling westbound approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound approaching the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. After impact V1 departed the north road edge and the front of V1 contacted a curb.

V2 & V3 were stopped at a signal controlled intersection while traveling west on a 5 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling south on an intersecting 4 lane interchange ramp and turned left (east) at the signal controlled intersection. The front plane of V1 impacted the front plane of V2, causing the back plane of V2 to impact the front plane of V3.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right hand side and made contact with a utility pole with the right plane. V1's final rest was 100 feet past the utility pole off the roadway.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. While attempting to negotiate a left hand curve V1 lost control departing the right side (south) of the roadway. Impacting a tree with the right plane causing damage (event 1) then impacted another tree with the frontal plane (event 2). V1 continued forward impacting another tree with the left plane (event 3) finally impacting a another tree (event 4) with the left plane causing damage. Upon impact with the final tree V1 rotated counterclockwise coming to final rest facing northeast.

V1 was headed west on a four lane, physically divided, two way roadway, pulling a trailer. V1 was in the left lane of the two westbound lanes. The trailer V1 was pulling began whipping from side to side and V1 went off the left side of the roadway and then came back onto the roadway. As V1 came back onto the roadway it entered into a clockwise yaw. The trailer V1 was towing and V1 jackknifed as the trailer passed V1. The trailer, proceeding west but now heading east, began to roll, left side leading. As the trailer rolled it caused V1, now behind the trailer, proceeding west but heading east, to roll. V1 came unattached from the trailer sometime during the roll sequence, and rolled left side leading, 7 quarter turns, while traveling down a ditch and then up an embankment. Upon rolling onto the embankment V1 rolled back one quarter turn, right side leading, coming to final rest on its left side facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling southwest approaching the same intersection. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's left plane as both vehicles traveled straight through the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast negotiating a left curve on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 departed its travel lane to the left, then departed the left road edge. The front of V1 then contacted a tree. Vehicle 1 contacted two additional trees before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling west on a two-way, two lane road approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south-east approaching same intersection, on a two-way, two lane road. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 departed the northeast shoulder of the roadway, driving along a roadside embankment. V1 contacted a reflector post with its frontal plane, then continued traveling and struck a brick encased mailbox with its frontal plane. As a result, the top of V1 came into contact with brick debris from the previous impact with the brick mailbox. V1 continued along the roadside embankment, before coming to final rest off of the roadway.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway approaching a "T" intersection. V1 departed the roadway to the east of the intersection. The front of V1 contacted an embankment and a guy wire.

V1 was eastbound on a three-lane roadway approaching the intersection. V2 was southbound approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped at the intersection facing northbound. V1 and V2 entered into the intersection at the same time. The left-front of V1 impacted the right-front of V2 (event 1). V1 then rotated clockwise at the same time V2 rotated counter-clockwise. The left side of V1 then impacted the right side of V2 (event 2). The right side of V2 then impacted the front of V3 (event 3) at which time V2 came to final rest. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V3 (event 4) at which time V1 came to final rest. V3 never moved from where it was stopped and final rest was at point of impact for both events 3 and 4.

V1 was traveling on a 4 lane non physically divided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on a 3 lane non physically divided roadway towards the same intersection. V3 was stopped at the intersection facing northbound. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2. Both V1 and V2 collided with the left side of V3. V1 and V2 were towed V3 was not.

V1 was traveling North on a 3 lane non divided roadway. V1 attempted to cross railroad tracks while the railroad crossing barricades were down while a train was approaching. The rear of the train car contacted the front/right of V1 pushing V1 west along the train tracks. V1 came to rest beside the railroad tracks.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two-way undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of a trailer (Event 1) parked on the roadside.  V1 then rotated clockwise and tripped over 2 quarter turns to the left (Event 2).

V1, V2, and V3 were northbound on a three-lane, interstate highway. V1 was traveling in the center lane (lane no. 2). V2 was in the left lane (lane no. 3).  V3 was in the right lane (lane no.1).  V1 departed its travel lane to the left and its left side plane sideswiped the right side plane of V2 (Event 1). Vehicle 1 was traveling east approaching an intersection attempting to make a left turn to travel north. Vehicle 2 was traveling west approaching the same intersection. The front plane of Vehicle 1 contacted the left plane of Vehicle 2 within the intersection.

V1 was west bound, on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, approaching a four way intersection. V2 was north bound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway, approaching the same four way intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time, where the left plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2. V2 came to final rest in the intersection. V1 continued westward, where it left the roadway to the right and rolled 4 quarter turns before coming to final rest on it wheels, partially in the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 5 lane road traveling through an intersection.  V2 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 3 lane road traveling through the same intersection.  The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.  V2 rotated clockwise then rolled left 4 quarter turns beginning on the road and continuing off the right road edge down an embankment where it contacted a barb wire fence before coming to rest on its wheels.

V1 was traveling west in the second travel lane of a two-way, four lane road. V2 was traveling east on the same road in the first travel lane. V1 made a left turn. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1 causing V1 to spin clockwise before coming to final rest on a side street.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling west in the first travel lane of a five lane, two-way road. V2 was traveling behind V3, and were slowing in traffic as they approached an intersection. V1, traveling behind V2, impacted the back of V2. The front of V2 went on to impact the the back of V3
V1 was traveling east on a four lane, two way median divided roadway.  The front of V1 contacted a deer.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane two-way roadway when it departed the right side of the road and its front impacted a pole. V1 then rolled 2-quarter turns and contacted a light pole on the south side of the roadway with its front.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway approaching a 'T' intersection.  V1 crossed through the intersection and the front of V1 contacted a sign post.  The front of V1 then contacted an embankment.

V1, V2,and V3 were traveling south on a two lane interchange on-ramp to an interstate with V3 in the lead.  V3 was stopped.  V2 was decelerating and V1 had stopped but started in the road when the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.  The front of V2 then impacted the rear of  V3.  All vehicles came to rest in the area of impact.
V1 and V2 were northbound on a seven lane undivided roadway.  V1 stopped for a traffic light.  The front of V2 impacted with the rear of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest close to point of impact.

V1 was traveling northwest in the number 1 lane of a 6 lane interstate, in the on-ramp for the interstate. V1 departed the road to the right side where the front of V1 impacted a concrete footing. V1 continued forward and began rotating clockwise where the left side of V1 impacted a tree. After the impact with the tree V1 came to final rest with its left side against the tree and the car caught fire.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound in the number 3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling behind V2. V2 began decelerating due to the traffic signal at the intersection that both vehicles were approaching. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2, pushing V2 to the other side of the intersection.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling southeast in the #2 lane of a 2 lane divided highway. V2 was decelerating due to traffic. V3 came to a stop due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V2 was pushed forward from the first impact and the front of V2 impacted the back of V3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection going straight; V2 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south, departing a private drive and Vehicle 2 was traveling west, approaching the same private drive. V1 entered the roadway turning left. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, one way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on a four lane, two way median divided roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  V1 then departed the roadway and the right front wheel of V1 contacted a curb.

V1 was heading north on a four lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was heading west on a three lane one way roadway approaching the same intersection. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane one way roadway. V2 was traveling east on a two lane one way roadway. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling east in the first lane of a two lane two-way roadway. V1 departed the lane on its left and then departed the roadway on the left side. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a granite block. V1 then rolled over, one quarter turn, onto the left side where its top contacted another granite block. V1 experienced a fire in the engine compartment after the rollover.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection going straight; V2 entered the intersection turning left. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

Vehicle One was traveling east on a two-way not physically divided roadway approaching an intersection in the number one lane preparing to make a left hand turn to head north. Vehicle Two was traveling south in the number two lane on two-way not physically divided roadway with a continuous left hand turn lane approaching the same intersection. Vehicle One's left and Vehicle Two's front made contact with each other in the middle of the intersection. Both vehicles came to final rest in approximately the same location.

V1 was traveling south east in the #3 lane of a 3 lane physically divided road. V2 and V3 were attempting to turn left to head north.
