Vehicle 1 was traveling north in the fourth lane of four lanes.Vehicle 2 was traveling north in the third of four lanes.Vehicle 3 was traveling north in the second of four lanes. V1 departed its lane on the right side. The right side of V1 contacted the left side of V2. The right side of V1 then contacted the left side of V3.

V1, V2, & V3 were traveling north on a 4 lane divided highway. At a signal controlled intersection, as V2 & V3 were departing on a green signal the front plane of V1 impacted the back plane of V2. The front plane of V2 then impacted the back plane of V3.

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two way roadway when the vehicle departed the right side of the road and struck several large rocks with the front right tire/wheel. The vehicle then struck an embankment with the frontal plane, traveled across the embankment, and rolled over 1/4 turn onto its left side plane. The vehicle then rotated in a counter clockwise direction and struck an embankment with the back plane. The vehicle then traveled backwards up the embankment and rolled over 1/4 turn onto its left side plane before coming to final rest back on the roadway.

V1 was headed west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, and was slowing down. V2 was headed west on the same roadway and in the same lane as V1. The frontal plane of V2 struck the rear plane of V1. Both vehicles came to rest headed west in their initial travel lane.

V1 was headed east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, through a four leg intersection. V2 was headed south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, through the same four leg intersection. The frontal plane of V1 struck the right side plane of V2. V2 rotated clockwise, and the right side of V1 contacted the right side of V2, in a side slap manner. V1 came to rest off the southeast corner of the roadway headed southeast. V2 came to rest heading north, on the shoulder of the northbound lane, south of the intersection.

V1 was traveling northbound on a one-lane, divided roadway (painted  flush center median) approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. The driver of V2 initiated a left turn at the intersection as the frontal plane of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 traveled off the right side of roadway after impact, striking a small post, and coming to final rest in a ditch.
V1 was turning left from a private drive to a 3 lane partially physically divided roadway when the front of V1 struck a sign situated on a traffic median. V1 was towed.

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane roadway when V1 departed the roadway to the right, then over corrected to the left and exited the roadway, the over corrected to the right, the V2 began to yaw clockwise, then V1 exited the roadway to the left, tripped and rolled 4 quarter turns landing on its wheels.

V1, V2, and V3 were all southbound in the same lane of a two-lane divided roadway. V3 and V2 were ahead of V1. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2 (event 1). Subsequently, the front of V2 impacted the back of V3 (event 2).

V1 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 1 (of two lanes), when it departed the roadway on the right, ascended an earthen embankment and overturned (8 quarter turns, leading left).

Vehicle #1 was traveling north approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling east on the intersecting roadway.  Both vehicles entered the intersection and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.

Vehicle 2 was traveling south on a six lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway in the number 2 lane approaching an intersection. Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a seven lane, two-way, not physically divided roadway in the number 2 lane approaching the same intersection. Both vehicles proceeded through the intersection going straight. Vehicle 1's right side made contact with Vehicle 2's left side. Then, Vehicle 2's left side made contact with Vehicle 1's right side. Vehicle 2 continued through the intersection, making contact with the front, to a curb followed by a pole on the southeast corner of the intersection, before coming to final rest against the pole facing south. Vehicle 1 came to final rest on the west side of the intersection in the eastbound travel lanes facing south.
V1 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 3 (of three lanes) when it departed the roadway on the left and its front end contacted a sign post.

Vehicle #1 was westbound on a two lane undivided roadway making a left turn to travel southbound onto an intersecting two lane undivided roadway. Vehicle #2 was traveling northbound on a three lane undivided roadway and entered into the intersection, contacting its frontal plane with the left side plane of Vehicle #1. Vehicle #1 then rotated counter-clockwise and contacted its left side plane with the left side plane of Vehicle #2.

V1 was traveling west on a two way roadway passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a two way roadway approaching the same intersection. V2 front plane contacted the right plane of V1.
V1 and V2 were traveling northbound on a one-way roadway. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a one-lane divided traffic way, V2 was stopped in traffic. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

Vehicles 2 & 3 were stopped west bound, in lane 1 of a 2 lane non-divided roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling west in lane 1 of the same roadway. The front plane of V1 impacted the back plane of V2. The front plane of V2 then impacted the back plane of V3.
Vehicle #1 was traveling SW, entered an intersection, and made a left turn. V1 departed its lane to the right and the front end contacted a utility pole.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two-lane undivided roadway and was approaching a three-leg intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling southbound approaching the same intersection and initiated a left turn to proceed eastbound. The front of Vehicle 1 impacted the right side of Vehicle 2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest negotiating right curve. Vehicle 1 departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. The driver steered right and reentered the roadway and its original travel lane. The driver over corrected and Vehicle 1 went into a counter clockwise rotation. Vehicle 1 then departed the travel lane to the left and departed the left road edge into a tree line. Vehicle 1 contacted a tree then tripped and rolled 1/4 turn onto the right plane contacting a tree.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southwest negotiating a right curve. Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1 lost traction on the wet roadway surface and initiated a counter-clockwise yaw. Vehicle 1 departed its traveling lane to the left. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's front plane.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided, roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway in a clockwise yaw impacting a ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. Upon impact with the ditch V1 overturned left side leading rolling one quarter turn coming to final rest on its left side facing north.

V1 was east bound on a four lane, two way, physically divided roadway. V1 went off the right side of the roadway, passing through a ditch and striking a barbwire fence. V1 proceeded through the fence, up a hill, striking 2 small trees with its frontal plan, and then a larger tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest heading southeast at point of impact four.

V1 and V2 were negotiating a right-hand curve northbound on a 2 lane road approaching a transitional split. V1 continued northbound into the number 2 lane and V2 started heading eastbound in the number 1 lane. V1 departed the roadway to the right side and the front impact a traffic attenuator. After the collision V1 continued easterly while rotating counter-clockwise into the number 1 lane where the rear of V1 impacted a bridge rail. After the collision the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling southeast in the #4 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was stopped, facing northwest, in the #4 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway waiting to turn left. V1 departed the roadway and drove over a small center median and entered the left turn lane that V2 was stopped in. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west, exiting a parking lot. V1 turned right onto a two way two lane roadway. Vehicle 2 was northbound on that roadway. The front of vehicle 2 struck vehicle 1.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number one lane of the interchange, while V2 was traveling in the number two lane of adjacent highway to V1's interchange roadway. V3 was traveling in the number one lane next to V2 in the adjacent highway to V1. V1 left the roadway on the right side and entered the adjacent roadway where V2 and V3 were traveling. V1 contacted V2, then continued to travel into V3's lane where it contacted V3 before leaving the roadway on the right and making contact with the jersey barrier before re-entering the roadway and coming to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south attempting to make a left hand turn within the intersection while Vehicle 2 was traveling northbound crossing into the same intersection. The front of V1 contacted the front of V2 within the intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east in the second of three lanes, approaching an intersection. Vehicle 2 was stopped facing east in the first lane, prior to the same intersection. V1 departed it's lane of travel on the right side and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2. V1 crossed through the first lane and then departed the roadway on the right side. V1 was traveling south on a two-way, four lane non physically divided roadway in lane 2.  V2 was traveling north, making a U-turn.  The front of V1 came into contact with the right side of V2.

V2 was traveling east on a two-way, five lane, not physically divided roadway (with two-way left turn lane) and was in lane 1.  V1 was stopped/parked facing south on the shoulder along the south edge of the road.  V1 backed onto the roadway in a northerly direction, and then began to travel forward/east in lane 1 ahead of V2.  V2 steered into lane 2.  V1 departed its lane to the left, and its left side was contacted by the front of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound in lane two. Vehicle #2 was parked in lane two facing east bound. V1's front bumper contacted the back bumper of V2.
V1 was traveling west in lane 2 of a 2 lane positive barrier divided interstate. The front plane of V1 impacted a deer.
V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway.  The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the right side (north) of the roadway facing west.

V1 was traveling southbound on a 2 lane divided highway in the #2 lane. V1 began to yaw counter-clockwise, departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 struck a cable guardrail. V1 continued to yaw and the right side of V1 contacted the same cable guardrail. V1 continued to yaw counter clockwise, now facing northbound, when the rear of V1 struck the same cable guardrail. V1 then came to rest on the shoulder and was towed.

V2 was traveling west on a 4-lane two way non-physically divided roadway. V1 was traveling north on a 4-lane two-way divided roadway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2 (Event 1). The impact caused both V1 and V2 to rotate and the right side of V1 contact the left side of V2 (Event 2). V2 then traveled north and the front of V2 contacted a sign in the median area (Event 3).

V1 was traveling North on a two way two lane roadway approaching a private drive behind a non-contact vehicle. V2 was pulling out of a private driveway turning left to travel south on the same roadway as V1. The non-contact vehicle stopped in the roadway and V1 went around the non-contact vehicle on the left and the front of V2 contacted the right of V2.

V1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1. V2 rotated counter clockwise and V1 rotated clockwise. Both vehicles impacted each other in a side slap impact. V2 continued to move southeast and departed the roadway to the east. The left front tire of V2 impacted a raised curb and an iron fence in front of private property.

V1 was traveling north exiting a private drive. V1 attempted  turning left at the intersection. V2 was traveling west approaching the intersection. During the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection. V1 turned left at the intersection, entering the southbound lanes of traffic. V1 departed the roadway to the right and impacted the raised west curb of the southbound lanes with its right front wheel. V1 continued to drive off road and impacted two small trees with its front and its right rear wheel. One of the trees broke off and fell on the roof of V1.

V1 was eastbound on a curved two-lane road. V2, V3, V4 and V5 were all westbound on the same roadway. V1 entered the westbound lane and its front impacted the left side of V2 (event 1). V1 continued east and its front impacted the left side of V3 (event 2). V3 departed the roadway and its right side stuck a mailbox (event 3). V1 resumed traveling eastbound in the westbound lane when its front collided with the front of V4 (event 4). Subsequently, the front of V5 struck the back of V4 (event 5).

V1 was westbound on a three lane undivided roadway preparing to turn left. V2 was northbound on a five lane undivided roadway going straight. The front of V2 contacted the left of V1. V1 was redirected to the right and V2 was redirected to the left. The left of V1 contacted the right of V2.

V1 was traveling west on an eight lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was stopped ahead of V1 on the same roadway facing west waiting to turn left onto an intersecting roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane two way roadway. V2 was traveling on the same two lane two way roadway ahead of V1. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2.

V1 was negotiating a slight curve to the left while traveling on a two-way, two-lane road. V1 departed the right side of the road and impacted the ground with it's undercarriage.  The front of V1 then impacted a telephone pole and rotated clockwise causing it to overturn one quarter turn onto it's left side where it came to rest in the road.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a four lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling west in the second lane of a three lane, two-way roadway. V2 was attempting to take a left turn to travel south/west onto the ramp. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the frontal plane of V2. V2 rotated counterclockwise and traveled across the roadway. V2 impacted a curb with the frontal plane and then impacted a sign with its frontal plane before coming to final rest. V1 continued to travel eastbound.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The front of V1 impacted a mailbox. V1 then impacted a utility pole with its front and came to final rest.

V1 was headed westbound in the second lane of a three lane divided roadway. V2 was headed westbound in the second lane of a three lane divided roadway ahead of V1. V2 was towing a trailer. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the back of V2's trailer (Event 1). V1 departed the lane and then the roadway contacting the curb (Event 2). V1 then rolled over to the right (Event 2). During the rollover the frontal plane of V1 contacted a sign (Event 3). V1 then came to final rest on its top plane.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east in the second of four eastbound travel lanes. Vehicle 2 was traveling east in the same lane ahead of V1. V2 slowed to a stop and the front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in the same direction in front of V1. After crossing the intersection, V2 stopped in traffic. The frontal plane of V1 made impact with the rear plane plane of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in the left turning lane of a two way roadway with three lanes of travel in the northbound direction and two lanes of travel in the southbound direction. V2 was traveling southbound in the right lane of the same roadway. As V1 was making a left turn at an intersection, the right plane of V1 made impact with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 1 lane on an undivided 4 lane road. V1 attempted to negotiate a right hand turn and V1 departed the roadway to the left side where the front of V1 impacted a utility pole guy wire. V1 traveled up the guide wire and started rotating left about the longitudinal axis. While V1 was rotating onto its left side on the guy wire, the left side of V1 impacted a tree. After the impact with the tree V1 continued to move westerly and rotating clockwise where the vehicle rolled onto its roof. V1 continued to rotate clockwise while on its roof where the left of V1 impacted a mailbox. The rotational force continued from the mailbox impact and the mailbox and left side of V1 impacted a stop sign. The vehicle came to rest facing northbound on its roof.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a 4 lane highway. V1 was traveling in the #2 lane and V2 was traveling in the #3 lane. V1 changed lanes to the left where the left rear of V1 impacted the right front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise  and departed the roadway on the left. The right side of V1 impacted a concrete traffic barrier.
Vehicle #2 was parked facing south on the right side of the road. Vehicle #1 was traveling south on the same roadway. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south.  Vehicle #2 was traveling north on the same roadway.  V1 began to turn left into a parking lot and the front of V1 contacted the left of V2.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling east in lane three on an undivided two-way roadway with a two way left turn lane, approaching a four way intersection. V1 was behind V2 and V2 was behind V3. V2 and V3 were stopped in traffic. The front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V2 moved forward and the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were travelling southbound on a single lane exit ramp. Vehicle #1's frontal plane contacted the back plane of Vehicle #2

V1 was traveling west on a two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south on a one-way roadway passing through an intersection. V1 front contacted the left of V2.  After initial impact with V1, V2 spun onto a curb and struck a stop sign with it's back plane.
V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a two way, two-lane, undivided roadway. V2 was slowing for traffic when the front plane of V1 struck the rear plane of V2.
V1 was traveling westbound on a divided three-lane roadway. V2 was making a right hand turn out of a business parking lot intending to travel westbound. The front of V2 contacted the rear of V1.

V2 was traveling NW in lane 2 of a 5 lane non divided roadway. V1 was turning left to exit a private driveway to proceed SW on the same roadway. Near the intersection of the driveway, the front plane of V2 impacted the left plane of V1.

V1 was traveling north on a 2 lane, two way roadway when the vehicle departed the right side of the roadway. V1 returned back to the roadway and departed the left side of the roadway striking an embankment and guardrail with the frontal plane of the vehicle. The vehicle then traveled up an embankment and struck a tree with the frontal plane, and then traveled down the embankment and struck the edge of the roadway with the right side plane of the vehicle. The vehicle then rolled over 4 quarter turns before coming to final rest back on the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northbound on a five-lane, divided trafficway. Vehicle #1 then departed the initial travel lane to the left, contacting the concrete raised, curbed center median with its undercarriage (Event 1) and left front wheel (Event 2). Vehicle #1 entered into the southbound lanes and departed the roadway left side, contacting an  electrical utility box (Event 3) and then a metal post (Event 4) with its front. Vehicle #1 rotated slightly, in a clockwise fashion and contacted another wooden gate post with a metal backed post (Event 5) on its left side plane. The metal horizontal gate bar impacted the left B-pillar and impacted the left window glazing (Event 6), before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling north on a 2 lane divided highway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway and traveled north on the grass median before impacting a dirt embankment with the front. V1 then continued, back to the right and impacted the left shoulder (ground) with the undercarriage before returning to the roadway and then departing the right side of the roadway and impacting a tree with the front plane.

V1 was traveling north in lane 1 of a 2 lane, 2 way non-divided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the road and impacted a sign post with the front plane (EV1), a fence with the front plane of the body (EV2) and the RF tire/wheel (EV3), also causing damage along the top and right side plane, and then a tree with the front plane (EV4) and the LF tire/wheel (EV5), before coming to final rest in a pasture.

V1 was traveling east on an interstate (physically divided with positive barrier) in lane 4 (of 5 lanes) and was approaching V2, which was disabled and stopped facing a easterly direction in the same lane. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2, and V2 then traveled in a northerly direction where its front end contacted a guardrail.

V1 was traveling west on an Interstate (physically divided - median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the left and its front end came into contact with a guard rail.
V1 was traveling east on a five lane two way roadway divided by a grass median. V1 departed the roadway to the left into the grass median. The front of V1 contacted a culvert.

V1 was traveling north in lane three of a five lane 2two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane one on the same roadway. In the intersection V1 began a right turn to change roadways. The unknown plane of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a four lane two way roadway entering a T intersection with an east west intersecting roadway. V1 departed the north side of roadway where it vaulted over an embankment edge and contacted the ground with its front plane.  V1 continued forward where its front contacted a berm causing V1 to roll left 2-quarter turns. V1 came to rest on its roof facing east.
V1 and V2 were traveling in the #3 lane of a 4 lane highway. V2 began to slow down due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound on a 5 lane road, entering a 2-way left turn lane. V1 negotiated a left turn onto a 2 lane road entering the number 1 lane. V1 departed the road to the right side and the front of V1 impacted the left of V2. V1 continued forward where the front of V1 impacted the rear of V3.

V1 was traveling north east on a two way road in the #1 lane. V1 departed the lane to the left and steered back to the right and departed the road on the right hand side. V1 traveled down into a ditch where the front of V1 impacted the ditch embankment. V1 continued forward and the front of V1 impacted a large bush where it came to final rest.

V1 was crossing through intersection traveling northeast on a two lane, two way road. V2 was crossing through same intersection traveling west on a two way, two lane road. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side, impacting the guardrail face with its frontal plane. V1 rotated and the front plane impacted the guardrail face a second time. V1 bounced off of the guardrail and began to roll. V1 made eight quarter turns, coming to rest on its tires facing west.

V1 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a three lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a three lane divided roadway ahead of V1. V1 attempted to change lane of travel to the first lane on its right. The right side plane of V1 contacted the left side plane of V2 (Event 1). V2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway at right. The frontal plane of V2 contacted a guardrail face (Event 2). V2 continued rotating clockwise and the left side of V2 contacted the guardrail face (Event 3). V2 re-entered the roadway at left and entered the first, second and third lanes at left and came to final rest in the third lane facing westbound.

This intersection is controlled by stop signs in the east/west bound roadway. V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling south in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V1 traveled through the intersection with its frontal plane impacting the left side plane of V2, as V2 was traveling through the same intersection.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. V2 entered the intersection turning left; V1 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. After the impact, V1 rotated clockwise and V2 counter clockwise. V1 impacted the right side of V2 with its left side in a side slap impact.

V1 was traveling east approaching an intersection in lane 1. V2 was traveling south approaching the same intersection in lane 1. V3 was stopped at the intersection traveling north in lane 3. During the intersection the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. V1 rotated clockwise, V2 rotated counter clockwise, the left side of V1 and right side of V2 side slapped. V2 continued to the southeast and crossed over the median, the front of V2 impacted the left side of V3.

V1 was traveling west, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 started to rotate counter clockwise and rolled over right side leading, 2 quarter turns.

V1 was northbound on a two-lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 impacted an embankment with the lower front-right bumper corner then came to final rest in the weeds just beyond the point of impact.
V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the eastern road edge and contacted an embankment with its frontal plane.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.
V1 was traveling east on a winding two-lane, two-way road that inclined steadily. V2 was traveling west on the same road going down the incline.  The front of V2 impacted the front of V1.

V1 was traveling east in a parking lot driveway. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in lane two on a five lane two way roadway. V1 entered the roadway and began to turn left and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.
Vehicle #1 was traveling  on a two lane, non-positively divided roadway. Vehicle #2 was legally parked on the same roadway. Vehicle #1's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #2's rear plane.

Vehicle #1 was travelling westbound on six lane grass median divided roadway entering the intersection. Vehicle #2 was travelling southbound on a five lane median divided roadway entering the intersection. The front plane of Vehicle #2 contacted the right side plane of Vehicle #1.

V1 was accelerating north from a traffic signal controlled intersection in lane 2 of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling north in the same lane. The front plane of V2 impacted the back plane of V1.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two way roadway and was negotiating a left curve in the road. V1 then departed the roadway on the right side, returned back to the roadway, and then  departed the roadway on the left side. V1 then struck 3 trees with the frontal plane of the vehicle before coming to final rest.

V2 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway. V1 was traveling east on the same roadway and was turning left onto another two lane, two way roadway. At the intersection, V2's frontal plane contacted the right side plane of V1.
V2 was traveling west on a two lane roadway. V1 was traveling on the same road attempting to make a U - turn to travel east. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling eastbound on a four-lane roadway, V3 was traveling westbound. V2 was stopped in the road when the front plane of V1 struck the rear of V2. After initial contact, V2 continued eastbound where the front plane of V1 struck the front plane of V3. V3 then continued westbound departing the roadway on the right side where the back plane struck a sign post then a utility pole.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway, when V1 departed the roadway on the left side and contacted a sign post with the front.  V1 continued forward and contacted a tree with the left side.

V1 was westbound on a two-lane roadway. V2 was eastbound on the same two-lane roadway. V1 began to make a left turn onto an intersecting roadway. The right-front corner of V1 impacted the front of V2 (event 1). V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest in the roadway facing southeast. V2 departed the roadway to the right, the front of V2 impacted a traffic sign (event 2), and then the front of V2 impacted a business sign (event 3) where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road passing through an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way road passing through the same intersection.  The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling east through an intersection in lane one of a two-lane, two-way road.  V2 was traveling north through the same intersection in lane two of three of a five-lane, two-way divided road. The front of V2 impacted the right of V1 causing V1 to rotate clockwise.  The left side of V1 impacted a curb causing it to roll one quarter turn onto it's left side and then impacted a fire hydrant.
V1 and V2 were traveling southbound in the number 1 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was slowing due to traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling northbound on a 4 lane interstate in the number 4 lane. V2 and V3 began to decelerate due to traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of this collision pushed the front of V2 into the back of V3.

V1 was traveling northeast in lane 3 of a 5 lane roadway traveling through an intersection.  V2 was traveling northwest in lane 3 of a 4 lane roadway turning left in an intersection to head southwest.  The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling west on a four lane, two way median divided roadway pulling a trailer.  The trailer became detached from the hitch in the bed of V1 and flipped over damaging the left bed rail of V1.

V2 was traveling east in lane 1 on a four lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V3 was stopped facing northbound on a two lane, two way roadway at the same intersection.  V1 was traveling west in lane 3 on a five lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.  The left side of V1 then contacted the front of V3.

V1 and V2 were west bound on a two lane non divided bidirectional roadway. V3 was east bound on the same roadway.  V1's frontal plane impacted the rear plane of V2. V1's right plane then impacted V2's left plane. V1 then crossed into the east bound lane, where it's frontal plane impacted the frontal plane of V3. V1 then left the roadway to the left, rotating clockwise and rolling 1 quarter turn coming to final rest on it's left side. V3 left the roadway to the right, where it rotated clockwise and impacted a tree with it's rear plane before coming to final rest. At some point in the sequence, the engine compartment of V1 caught fire.

V1 was traveling on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway stopped at a stop sign at an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided road way approaching the same intersection and stop sign. The front plane of V2 contacted the rear plane of V1. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.  V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on a two way non-physically divided roadway. A deer entered the road and the front of vehicle 1 struck the deer in the roadway. Vehicle 1 was able to pull off of the roadway. Vehicle 1 was towed from the scene.

V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V2 attempted to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a 3 lane road in lane 1, approaching a 3 leg intersection. V2 was traveling north on a 3 lane road in lane 2 approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V2 attempted to turn left. In the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V2 then rotated clockwise, and the right side of V1 then impacted the back of V2. V2 continued rotating clockwise and departed the roadway southeast of the intersection.
V1 was traveling north on an undivided two lane road. V2 was parked on the roadside facing north. V1 departed its lane to the right and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

Vehicle #1 was travelling eastbound on a six lane non-positively median divided roadway making a left turn within the intersection. Vehicle #2 was travelling westbound on the same roadway in an opposite direction. Vehicle #1 frontal plane contacted the left side plane of Vehicle #2.

V1 was traveling southwest in lane 2 of a 2 lane divided roadway. V2 was turning left at the exit of a private driveway to proceed northeast on a 2 lane divided roadway. At the driveway intersection, V1's frontal plane contacted the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was northbound on a two-lane interstate. V1 departed its initial lane of travel to the left. V1 returned to its initial lane of travel to the left. V1 continued in a northern direction, then departed its travel lane roadway to the left. V1 traversed the grass median and entered the southbound roadway. The front of V1 impacted the left of V2 (event 1). V1 continued southbound in the northbound lanes as the left of V1 impacted with the left of V3 (event 2). V1 then came to an uncontrolled final rest a short distance from point of impact. V2 rotated 360 degrees then the front impacted with a guardrail face (Event 3) where V2 came to final rest. V3 was redirected to the right where the front impacted the guardrail end (event 4) where V3 came to final rest.

V1 and V2 were southbound on a  four lane interstate. Both vehicles took an off exit ramp on the right. The front of V1 impact with the rear of V2 (Event 1). V2 was redirected  to the left.  The left of V2 collided with the a guardrail face (Event 2). V2 was redirected to the left where is came to final rest in a patch of grass. V1 was redirected to the right where the front of collided with the embankment (Event 3).  The rear of V1 was propelled upward as the vehicle rotated counter clock wise.  The right rear tire came to final rest on rear top of V2 (Event 4).

V1 was traveling north approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was traveling west approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded through the intersection the intersection the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a undivided 4 lane road way in lane 2. V2 stopped in the lane waiting for the opposite direction traffic to clear to turn left into a private drive. V1 was traveling behind V2 and the front of V1 impacted the back of V2. V1 then departed the roadway to the right coming to rest off the roadway. V2 rotated counter clockwise and came to rest facing south in lane 4.

V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.
V1 was south bound on a 4 lane physically divided bidirectional roadway in the number one lane, when a deer entered the roadway from the left. V1's frontal plane impacted the deer.

V1 was traveling west on a two way two lane undivided bridge. V1 slid on ice crossing over the eastbound lane and striking the south side of the bridge. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway. V1 struck the front plane of V2 with its frontal plane just as V2 reached the west end of the bridge. Following the impact with V2, V1 spun clockwise with the rear of the vehicle lifting up and came to final rest heading north with its rear plane landing on top of the south guardrail just west of the bridge. V2 came to final rest on the center line heading north east.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V2 was stopped, headed north, in the south bound lane. V1 struck the frontal plane of V2 with its front plane. V1 came to final rest headed south on the west side of the roadway. V2 came to final rest at the point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was going southbound entering into an intersection, Vehicle 2 was going eastbound entering into the same intersection. Vehicle 2's frontal plane struck the right side plane of Vehicle 1. After this contact, Vehicle 1 rotated clockwise striking a parked vehicle, Vehicle 3. Vehicle 1's left frontal plane made contact with the left rear plane of Vehicle 3 before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a six lane positively divided highway. V1 departed the east road edge and the front of V1 contacted a guard rail. After contacting the guard rail V1 re-entered the highway and traveled across all northbound travel lanes and departed the west road edge. The front of V1 then contacted a concrete barrier. There was a secondary contact with the concrete barrier to the left side back plane of V1.  After contact with the concrete barrier V1 re-entered the northbound travel lanes and the front of V1 contacted the left side trailer of V2, which was traveling north in lane two.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way roadway. As V1 was negotiating a curve to its right it departed the east road edge. The front of V1 contacted a ditch embankment. V1 continued to travel north in the ditch and the front of V1 contacted a steel drainage pipe outlet. The right side of V1 then impacted the ditch wall.
V2 is a delivery vehicle and stopped at a roadside box on a 2 way non divided roadway. V1 was traveling in the same direction and the front plane of V1 impacted the back plane of V2.

V1 was traveling in lane 2 of a 2 lane divided roadway when the vehicle departed the left side of the roadway. The vehicle then struck a tree with the left side plane of the vehicle and rotated in a counter clockwise direction.  The undercarriage of the vehicle impacted the ground before coming to final rest.
Vehicle #1 was traveling southwest. V1 departed the roadway and contacted the left front wheel on a curb.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way roadway entering a four-legged light controlled intersection. . V2 was traveling north on a two-lane, two-way roadway entering the same intersection. V1's front contacted V2's right side in the intersection. V2 then traveled northwest and contacted a curb with its front tires, departed the roadway and contacted a pole with its front before coming to final rest.

V1 and V2 were both traveling west on a two-lane, two way road. V1 departed its travel lane to the left, attempting to pass V2. V2 was a medium/heavy truck, making a left turn. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.  V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a small shrub. V1 began to rotate clockwise and impacted a stump with its left side. V1 continued to rotate clockwise and came to final rest facing north off the roadway.

Vehicle was traveling north in lane 1 of a 2 lane non divided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the road and impacted a roadside marker with the front plane. V1 continued and impacted a culvert pipe with the front plane and undercarriage, then the embankment with the front and right side plane.  V1 then rolled over, right side leading and impacted 2 fence posts and the ground with the left plane, before coming to final rest on its wheels.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a curve to the left. V2 was traveling west on the same roadway also negotiating the same roadway curve to the right.  V1's front plane contacted the front plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching a four way intersection. V2 was traveling south approaching the same intersection. In the intersection, the front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, not physically divided, dry roadway, preparing to turn left at the intersection. V2 was eastbound on a two lane, not physically divided, dry roadway. V1 proceeded to turn left when impact occurred. The front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. Upon impact, V1 rotated clockwise, where V1's right side again impacted the frontal plane of V2. V2 pushed V1 off the roadway, where the left side of V1 impacted a guardrail before coming to final rest.

V1 was stopped on the side of a 5 lane non divided roadway, waiting to make a u-turn. V2 had just negotiated a left turn out of a private drive and was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane. V1 attempted to make a u-turn and the front of V1 contacted the right of V2.
V1 was stopped at an intersection facing westbound. V2 was traveling northbound on a two lane divided roadway. V1 made a left turn, and the front of V2 contacted the left of V1.
