V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V1 departed the roadway at right. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a cluster of mailboxes (Event 1). V1 continued through entering an intersecting roadway at right, crossing both lanes and departing the roadway at left. The frontal plane contacted a bush (Event 2). Then the front undercarriage contacted cinder block & cement stairs (Event 3) on final rest.

V1 was eastbound on a 4 lane divided highway with two lanes in each direction. V1 was in lane 1 approaching an exit lane to a truck weigh station. V1 driver stated the sun was in her eyes causing a sight issue. V1 drifted to the right following a fog line. When the driver realized she was not on her lane she said her vehicle struck the face of a guardrail that separated the travel lane from the weigh station exit.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane 2 of a 5-lane undivided two way roadway, V2 was traveling southbound in lane 1 of the same roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the left where the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a three lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same roadway. The front of V1 struck the front of V2 causing damage to both vehicles. V1 came to rest headed east in the southbound lane near the point of impact. V2 came to rest headed south east in the northbound lane near the point of impact.
Vehicle #1 was traveling NW and vehicle #2 was traveling SE. V2 turned left at an intersection, and the front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2.

Crash took place at an intersection controlled by traffic lights. V1 was stopped in the second lane of a five lane, two-way roadway heading northbound. V2 was stopped ahead of V1 in the second lane of a five lane, two-way roadway heading northbound. V1 started in the road once the traffic light changed. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south, exiting a private drive and Vehicle 2 was traveling west, approaching the same drive. V1 entered the roadway turning left. The left side of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling south in the first lane on a two way non-physically divided roadway. V1 departed lane, then roadway to the left. V1 then traveled through bushes and shrubs impacting the front of vehicle with shrubbery (event 1). V1 then overturned onto the left side (event 2), where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection, V1 attempted to turn left. Within the intersection, the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.

V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling east in lane 2 of a 4 lane, two-way roadway. V2 and V3 had stopped in the roadway for traffic when the frontal plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2. Due to the impact, the frontal plane of V2 then contacted the back plane of V3.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a curve.  V2 was traveling north on the same roadway exiting a right curve in the roadway and about to enter the same roadway curve as V1.  The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.  V1 came to final rest on the roadway facing east.  V2 departed the road on the right, and the right side of V2 contacted an embankment.

V1 was traveling south on on two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed their initial travel lane over the left lane line and then departed the left (east) roadside.  The front plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2 who was legally parked on the roadside.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling westbound. Vehicle #2 was traveling westbound behind V1 on a two lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the lane on the right side and re-entered the roadway on the right side attempting to make a u-turn. The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1 as it turned across the roadway to travel east.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 on a 4 lane non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 4 lane non-physically divided roadway.  V3 was at a stop light facing north in lane 1 on a 3 lane non-physically divided roadway.  V1 entered the intersection attempting a left turn. The front of V2 impacted the right of V1.  V1 then rotated clockwise and the left of V1 impacted the front of V3 and came to final rest facing southwest in the intersection. V3 came to final rest in original position. V2 came to final rest in the intersection facing east.
V1 and V2 were northbound in the left lane of a four-lane, divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling west in in lane 1 of the same roadway. While negotiating a curve in the roadway, the frontal plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was westbound on a four lane, two way, undivided roadway with a left and right turn lane approaching a four leg intersection. V2 was northbound on a three lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped at the same intersection heading south. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2 in the intersection. Upon impact V2 spun clockwise impacting V3 with the left plane and overturning left side leading. V2 came to final rest on the driver's side facing east. V1 came to final rest off the north west side of the intersection facing northwest. V3 came to final rest at the point of impact of V2 and V3.

V1 was traveling north in lane one on a seven lane two way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south in lane four on the same roadway approaching the intersection. As V2 turned to its left to travel west at the intersection V1 proceeded straight through the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.
V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way undivided roadway. While negotiating a right curve, V1 departed the road to the left and the front of V1 contacted a tree.

V1 was southbound on a curved two-lane divided highway. V1 departed the left side (east) of the roadway and its front impacted vegetation (event 1). Subsequently, V1 rolled over and came to rest on its right side (event 2).

V1 was traveling south in the second lane of a three-lane, two-way road, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north in the second lane of a three-lane, two-way road approaching same intersection. V2 was turning left. The front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 forward of the front axle.  V2 rotated counterclockwise and the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1 adjacent to the rear axle.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west, in the first of three lanes approaching an exit. The driver of V1 departed the roadway on the right side attempting to exit. The front of V1 contacted an impact attenuator. Vehicle 1 continued forward and departed the right road edge and its front plane contacted a concrete traffic barrier.
V1 was traveling south west on a two lane two way roadway. The front of V1 contacted a deer.

V1 was traveling north on a five lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a four lane, two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling east on a two way two lane roadway. V1 attempted a U-turn and departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a culvert off the roadway.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. An animal ran into the path of the V1. V1 steered left, departing the first lane on the left and entering the second lane. V1 then departed the roadway on the left. V1 struck a curb with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted a tree with its frontal plane. V1 continued and impacted another tree with its frontal plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a three lane divided roadway. V1 had stopped for traffic on the roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the same lane as V1. The frontal plane of V2 impacted the rear plane of V1.
V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway. V1 departed the lane at right and then the roadway at right. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a utility pole.

V1 was traveling west bound on a major highway. V2 was unoccupied and parked on the right shoulder. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2, the tire and rim fell off of V1 and bounced back into the highway. V1 continued and the front right impacted a curb. V3 and V4 were traveling west bound on the same highway, V3 impacted the tire and wheel with it's undercarriage. V4 then impacted the tire with it's undercarriage.

Vehicle 1,2, and 3 were traveling northbound on a two-way not physically divided roadway in the number two lane. Vehicle 2 and 3 were stopped at the intersection. Vehicle 1's front and Vehicle 2's rear made contact with each other. Then, Vehicle 2's front and Vehicle 3's rear made contact with each other.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left; V2 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling east on divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) that serves as an entrance to a not physically divided roadway (two-way traffic), and was in lane 1 (of one lane).  V2 was traveling east on the not physically divided roadway (two-way traffic) that V1 was about to enter, and was in lane 1 (of two lanes) approaching V1's location.  V1 was turned to the left across the median strip and into the path of V2.  The left side of V1 came into contact with the front end of V2.  V1 departed the roadway on the left, overturned (3 quarter turns, leading right) and its right side came into contact with an earthen embankment.  V2 also departed the roadway on the left, and its front end came into contact with the same earthen embankment (at a different location).
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 2 (of four lanes), with V1 directly behind V2. The front end of V1 contacted the back end of V2.

V1 was traveling southwest through an intersection in the #3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling southeast turning right in the #1 lane of a 3 lane undivided roadway. V3 was traveling northeast in the #3 lane of a 4 lane divided roadway. V1 departed the lane to the right and the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. V1 went left and the front of V1 impacted the center median curb as it crossed into oncoming traffic. The front of V1 then impacted the front of V3.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling northwest on a 5 lane interstate in the number 4 lane. V4 was traveling northwest in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane interstate. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. The force of this impact caused V2 to rotate clockwise where the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3. The force of this collision caused V3 to start rotating counter-clockwise. The left side of V4 impacted the rear of V3 while V3 was rotating. V3 continued to move forward after the impact and came to rest on the east shoulder. V4 pulled to the right shoulder after the impact with V3. V1 and V2 continued in a northwesterly direction and departed the roadway to the left side where the front of V2 impacted a guard rail face. V1 came to rest behind V2 on the west shoulder.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a two way two lane roadway.  Vehicle 1 traveled off the roadway to the right.  Vehicle 1 corrected back to the left returning to the southbound lane.  Vehicle 1 traveled into the northbound lane and corrected back to the right.  Vehicle 1 tripped on the roadway and rolled eight quarter turns off the roadway to the right, coming to rest facing north on its wheels in the southbound ditch.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane, two way roadway.  V2 was traveling north on the same two lane, two way roadway.  V1 attempted to overtake a slower vehicle and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a one way, one lane roadway, approaching an intersection. V2 was westbound on a two way, two lane roadway, and made a U turn near the intersection.  The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1 departed the roadway to the left side and the front of V1 contacted the concrete steps attached to a building.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling west on a three lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection.  In the intersection V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a two lane divided roadway. V1 departed the first lane at left and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north bound behind vehicle 2 in the same north bound lane. Vehicle 2 stopped to let another vehicle in lane. Vehicle 1 front end made contact with vehicle 2's rear.

Vehicle 2 was traveling west bound within the round about attempting to exit on the south side of roundabout. Vehicle 1 was traveling east bound and entered the round about. Vehicle 1 front left quarter panel and left side made contact with vehicle 2's right front side.
V1 was traveling in an eastern direction on a northbound two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway. A deer entered V1's path from the right, where V1 impacted the animal with its frontal plane.

V1 was west on an unmarked roadway. V1 was negotiating a turnaround in a cul-de-sac. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a utility pole. V1 came to final rest on a private lawn.

All units were traveling south on a 6 lane divided interstate. V1, V2 and V3 were traveling in lane 3. V4 and V5 were traveling in lane 2. V6 was traveling in lane 1. V2 decelerated and the front of V1 made impacted the rear of V2 (Event 1). The front of V3 impacted the rear of V1 (Event 2). V1 was re-directed into lane 2, to the right. The front of V5 then impacted the rear of V1 (Event 3). The front of V4 impacted the rear of V5 (Event 4). V1 rotated counterclockwise impacting the concrete barrier wall with its frontal plane (Event 5) coming to final rest facing northwest in lane 3. V5 continued south contacting the left side of V6 (Event 6), then V5s right side contacted V6s  left side in a secondary side slap impact (Event 7)   The left fender of V2 collided with the east roadside concrete barrier (Event 8) and came to final rest facing south. V3 came to final rest facing south in lane 3 adjacent to V1. V4 was redirected to the right its right side plane impacted the concrete traffic barrier (Event 9) and came to final rest at point of impact. V6 continued south coming to final rest on the southbound shoulder facing south. V5 was redirected across lanes 2 and 3 where the left side impacted the wall (Event 10) before coming to final rest facing south at point of impact.
V1 and V2 were traveling in opposite directions on a 3 lane roadway. V1's LR tire came off of the vehicle and went across travel lanes to the left. The tire then impacted the front of V2.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 was negotiating a curve to the right. V1 departed the left side of the roadway. The front of V1 impacted a tree.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling eastbound on a two way two lane roadway. V2 and V3 were stopped in traffic. The front of V1impacted the back of V2. After impact the front of V2 was pushed into the back of V3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast in lane 4 of a 4- lane divided roadway.  V1 departed the roadway on the left and traveled in the grass median a distance before the front and left side of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier.  V1 rotated clockwise and rolled left 2-quarter turns coming to rest on its top in the grass median.
V1 was traveling northbound in lane one of a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway when the front of V1 contacted a deer running across the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a three lane, divided roadway in lane one when V1 exited the roadway and continued to drive along the shoulder until the front of V1 contacted a barbed wire fence (event 1) V1 then crossed an east/west farm access road then the front of V1 contacted another barbed wire fence, then the front undercarriage of V1 contacted the ground (event 3) and V1 came to rest in a pasture.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 swerved right, to avoid an animal in the roadway, causing the right wheels to go off the edge of the roadway. V1 then steered left, to return to the roadway, and entered a counterclockwise yaw crossing the center line. V1 then steered right returning to the right lane in a clockwise yaw, and departed the right side of the roadway. V1 then rolled three quarter turns, right side leading, and then back one quarter turn coming to rest on its roof.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 was making a left hand turn, crossing the path of V2. The front plane of V2 contacted the right plane of V1 in the intersection.

V1 was stopped at a stop sign at a three legged intersection. The involved roadways were two lane, two way undivided roadways.From a stopped position, V1 accelerated across the intersection, departed the roadway and contacted four trees with the front plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a curve. V1 departed the east road edge and contacted an embankment with the right side, before coming to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south approaching a four way intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the intersecting roadway. Both vehicle 1 and 2 entered the intersection proceeding straight. Vehicle 2's front made contact with vehicle 1's right side.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, five lane, roadway divided by an embankment.  V1 departed the right (southern) road edge contacting approximately fifty feet of guide wire with its frontal plane.  V1 came to final rest at an unknown location.

Vehicle 1,2,3,4,5,6 and 7 were traveling on a two-way physically divided roadway in the number 2 lane traveling in a westerly direction. Vehicle 1's front and Vehicle's rear made contact with each other. Vehicle 2's front and Vehicle 3's rear made contact with each other. Vehicle 3's front and Vehicle 4's rear made contact with each other. Vehicle 4's front and Vehicle 5's rear made contact with each other. Vehicle 5's front and Vehicle 6's rear made contact with each other. Vehicle 6's front and Vehicle 7's rear made contact with each other. All of the vehicles final rest were located in general proximity to their points of impact.

V1 was traveling North on a one-way roadway, V2 was traveling West on a one-way roadway. Both vehicles were approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic signal. The front of V1 contacted the right side of V2 and both vehicles came to final rest in the intersection.
V1 and V2 were traveling westbound on a four-lane undivided roadway. An unknown vehicle merged in front of V2 causing the front of V1 to contact the rear of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound. Vehicle 1 lost control on the icy roadway. As driver attempted to correct by steering left, the vehicle left the roadway toward the left and made contact with a cable barrier in the median.

V1 was traveling westerly, V2 was traveling easterly on a two- lane, two- way undivided roadway. Due to icy roads Vehicle 1 lost control of vehicle and traversed the centerlines, entering the north travel lane. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2 in a head-on crash collision (Event 1). During vehicle rotation, the right quarter-panel of V1 impacted the front (right corner) of V2 (Event 2).

V1 was traveling east approaching a 4 way intersection. V2 was traveling south approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles proceeded straight through the intersection the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.
V1 and V2 were both eastbound on a 3-lane divided highway. V1 was in lane two and V2 was in lane one. V1 changed lanes and its right side impacted the left side of v2.

V1 and V2 were traveling west on a five lane, divided interstate. V2 was traveling in lane 1. V1 was traveling in lane 2. The driver of V1 changed lanes to the right. V1 impacted with the right side (Event 1) plane of V2. V2 was redirected across the shoulder and across the exit lane impacting a guardrail (Event 2) with its front where it came to final rest facing north. V1 initiated a clockwise  rotation, traveling across  the exit lane impacting the guardrail (Event 3) before coming to rest.

V1, V2, nd V3 were traveling east on a two lane divided interstate. V3 and V2 slowed for traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. The front of V2 collided with the rear of V3. All vehicles came to final rest close to point of impact.

V1 was traveling west on a three lane roadway. V2 was heading east on the same roadway. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. The front of V1 impacted with the front of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest close to point of impact.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, unmarked roadway. V1 turned left to miss a deer and departed the left side of the roadway. V1 rolled 1 quarter turn, left side leading. V1 struck a tree with its left upper plane that interrupted its roll, and struck 1 tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to rest on its left side facing north.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. A deer ran in front of V1 from the left. V1 struck the deer with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest off the right side of the roadway heading south.

V1 was traveling west on a not physically divided roadway (two-way traffic) in lane 2 (of two lanes), and was passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 3 (of four lanes), and was passing through the same intersection. In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the right side of V2. V1 then continued in a northwesterly direction, where it contacted a curb, a pole (STOP sign), two shrubs/bushes and a wall.

V2 was traveling eastbound in lane No. 2 of an undivided five-lane roadway. V1 was entering the roadway making a westbound left turn. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2. Vehicle 2 continued forward and traversed lane No. 1 before departing the right roadside. The front of V2 impacted a tree before coming to rest, facing easterly.

V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway traveling off a bridge into a creek bed. Upon departing the bridge V1 began a right side leading overturn before hitting the south embankment of the creek with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 rolled six quarter turns before coming to final rest on its top facing east.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway impacting a road sign with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 continued hitting two trees with the frontal plane causing damage. Upon impact V1 began to rotate clockwise and overturned left side leading five quarter turns. During the rollover V1 impacted two more trees causing minimal damage. V1 came to final rest off the right side of the roadway on the driver's side facing east.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast, negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1 was attempting a right turn at a three-leg intersection when it departed its travel lane to the right and then departed the roadway to the right. Vehicle 1 struck a concrete pipe and came to final rest off the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest in lane one. Vehicle 2 was traveling northwest, in lane two, behind Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 attempted to make a left turn into a private drive. The left plane of Vehicle 1 was contacted by the front plane of Vehicle 2.

V1 was traveling north in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane roadway approaching an intersection. V1 and V2 entered the intersection and the right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise and V2 rotated clockwise causing the right side of V1 to impact the left side of V2. Both vehicles rolled towards the northwest corner of the intersection, coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 2 lane of a 2 lane interstate. V2 was disabled from a previous collision in the number 2 lane facing westbound on a 2 lane interstate. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.
V1 and V2 were traveling in the #3 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V2 came to a stop due to traffic. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a three lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a three lane divided roadway ahead of V1. V2 stopped for traffic ahead and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the single lane of a one-way roadway. V1 was negotiating a curve and departed the roadway to the left. The frontal plane of V1 contacted a sign (Event 1). The frontal plane then contacted another sign (Event 2). The rollover initiated and the left side of V1 contacted the ground (Event 3). The top plane of V1 contacted a chain link fence where it came to final rest. (Event 4).

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a four lane, two-way intersecting roadway. A non contact vehicle was traveling eastbound in the first lane of the four lane, two-way roadway. The non-contact vehicle took a right to travel southbound. V1 entered the intersection in an attempt to travel westbound. The left side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2.
V1 was traveling south following a two way, two lane road. V1 departed the road to the right, where the front of V1 impacted a curb.

V1 was traveling north on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the left, traversed the median strip and became airborne as it entered the opposing roadway.  V2 was traveling south on the opposing roadway in lane 1 (of two lanes).  The right side of V1 came into contact with the front of V2.  V1 then departed the roadway on the right, where it overturned (1 quarter turn, leading left) and its top came into contact with a fence.  V2 also departed the roadway on the right, where its front end came into contact with the same fence (in a different location); V2 then overturned (1 quarter turn, leading left).

V1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The undercarriage of V1 impacted with the upward slope of the embankment (event 1). V1 continued to travel up the embankment turning vertically clockwise until the left of V1 impacted with a tree (event 2). After impact with the tree, V1 was redirected vertically counter clockwise. The right rear of V1 impacted another tree (event 3). V1 came to final rest against a fallen tree facing south.

V1 was westbound on a two way, six lane, undivided roadway. V1 was in the process of a right turn when the front of V1 impacted the concrete wall. V1 came to final rest on the entrance ramp near the point of impact facing northwest.

V1 was eastbound on a two lane, non-divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right and attempted to re-enter the eastbound travel lane. V1 then began to yaw left side leading and departed the right road edge where it rolled left side leading 2 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its roof.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were traveling in a 2-way undivided roadway. Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast negotiating a right curve. Vehicle 2 was traveling southwest negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted Vehicle 2's front plane.
Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast and departed its travel lane to the left. Vehicle 1 then departed the left road edge and the front plane contacted a sign.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northbound and was executing a left hand turn. Vehicle 2 was heading southbound. Vehicle 2's front plane contacted Vehicle 1's right plane. Vehicle 2 continued traveling and the front plane of Vehicle 2 contacted the left plane of Vehicle 3, who was stopped at an intersecting road.

V1 was traveling north on a two-way, three-lane road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling west on a two-way, two-lane road passing through the same intersection. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2 causing V1 to rotate counterclockwise. The right side of V1 then side slapped against the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane 1 (of a four lane, divided trafficway - median strip with positive barrier) when it departed the roadway on the right and its front end came into contact with a concrete traffic barrier.
V1 was traveling east in lane 2 of a two-way, not physically divided roadway when it departed the roadway on the right and came into contact with a curb and a fence.

V1 was traveling north entering a light controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling south entering the same intersection. In the intersection V1 attempted to turn left, V2 continued straight. In the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the left side of V2. After the initial impact, the back left of V1 contacted the left of V2 before coming to rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1 went into a counter clockwise rotation and departed the left road edge. Vehicle 1's right plane contacted a guard rail. Vehicle 1 then rotated clockwise and became airborne.  V1 began a four-quarter turn rollover, impacting the ground on its right side and coming to rest on its wheels.

V1 was traveling southwest on a 4-lane divided road turning left across traffic.  V2 was traveling east on a 4-lane divided roadway passing through the intersection. The right plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise and came to final rest partially off the road, facing east.  V2 rotated clockwise continued east a short distance and came to final rest partially off the shoulder, facing west on the eastbound side of the highway.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the single lane of a one-way roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the single lane of a one-way roadway ahead of V1. V2 came to a stop and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a three lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in the second lane of a three lane divided roadway ahead of V1. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2 (Event 1). V1 then departed the eastbound travel lanes and the roadway at left crossing the center median. V1 then entered the westbound on-coming traffic roadway and crossed three travel lanes, then departing the roadway where the frontal plane of V1 contacted the guardrail on the north side (Event 2). V1 then rebounded off the guardrail crossing the three lanes again to the right and leaving the roadway. V1 came to rest facing southeast in the median.
Vehicles #1, #2 and #3 were traveling east. V2 and V3 stopped at an intersection. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2, then the front plane of V2 contacted the back plane of V3.

V1 was traveling eastbound in lane three of a divided roadway with two lanes of travel and a left turning lane. V2 was traveling westbound in lane two of a divided roadway with two lanes of travel and a left turning lane. As V1 was making a left turn to go northbound at the intersection, the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the left side plane of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling southbound in the number 5 lane of a 5 lane divided roadway. V3, V4, and V5 were traveling southbound in the number 4 lane of a 5 lane divided highway. V4 came to a stop for traffic ahead and the front of V3 impacted the rear of V4. V5 continued forward and the front of V5 impacted the rear of V3. The force from this impact pushed V3 across the number 5 lane where the front of V3 impacted a concrete traffic barrier. V2 stopped because V3 had crossed into their lane and the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

V1 was heading southwest in the #3 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway crossing through an intersection. V2 is traveling northeast in the #2 lane of a 6 lane undivided roadway crossing through an intersection. V1 began to turn left to head south. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest in the roadway. V2 rotated clockwise and came to rest on the sidewalk.

V1 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane of a 2 lane undivided roadway. V2 was stopped facing northbound in the number 1 lane of the same roadway, preparing to make a left turn onto a side street. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south in the second of two lanes. Vehicle 2 was traveling south in the first lane on the same roadway. V2 attempted to change lanes to the left. The left side of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 rolled over left to top and the top of V1 contacted the concrete traffic barrier. V1 rotated and the front of V1 then contacted the same concrete barrier. The driver of V2 lost directional control of the vehicle, departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V2 contacted the concrete traffic barrier.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning right; V2 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2.
V1 was traveling on a two-lane, two-way road that gradually curved up an incline to the right. A deer entered the road from the right side. The front of V1 impacted the deer.

V2 was traveling south in lane two of three on a divided highway passing through and intersection. V1 was traveling in the opposite direction in lane three of three. V2 avoided another vehicle that was traveling east through the same intersection. The front of V2 impacted the front of  V1.
V1 was stopped at an intersection traveling south. V2 was traveling north, making a left turn. The front plane of V1 contacted the right plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a 4-lane, two-way, physically divided roadway in the number one lane. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the left, crossed the median, entered the lanes of oncoming traffic and then departed the roadway to left again. Vehicle 1's front made contact with a concrete ditch, overturned, the rear of V1 made contact with a tree and the undercarriage of V1 contacted a wire fence.  V1 came to final rest on the fence facing in an easterly direction.  An engine compartment fire then started.

V1 was traveling north in lane 2 of a 4 lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling south in lane 4 of a 4 lane divided roadway and was turning left to travel northeast on a one lane roadway when it's frontal plane contacted the frontal plane of V1.

Vehicles #1, #2, #3 were all traveling north on a 6 lane roadway in lane #2. V#1's frontal plane contacted V#2's rear plane, then V#2's frontal plane contacted the rear plane of V#3.  All involved vehicles came to final rest within lane #2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway.  Vehicle 2 was traveling south on the same roadway when the front of Vehicle 1 contacted the front of Vehicle 2.  Vehicle 1 rotated counter clockwise and Vehicle 2 rotated clockwise and the right side plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and the front of V1 contacted a light pole. V1 continued off the roadway and the front of V1 contacted a signal pole.
V1 was traveling south. A deer entered the roadway from the right, and the front plane of V1 contacted the deer, then the right plane of V1 contacted the deer.
Vehicle #1 was traveling northwest.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south on the same roadway.  Negotiating a right curve, V1 departed its lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling south in lane 1. A non-contact vehicle was traveling south in lane 2. V1 and V2 began to slow for traffic when the non-contact vehicle moved to lane 1 and braked hard. The front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

Vehicle 1 was attempting to make a left hand turn to head east. Vehicle 2 was traveling north approaching the intersection that Vehicle 1 was attempting the left hand turn. Vehicle 1's right side made contact with Vehicle 2's front.

V1 was traveling north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V2 was traveling north on the same roadway behind V1. V2 slowed to make a right hand turn into a driveway. The frontal plane of V1 came into contact with the rear plane of V2. V1 then rolled one quarter turn onto its side.

V1 was traveling east on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 crossed the path of V2. The left plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a four lane two way roadway approaching an intersection. Before reaching the intersection, V1 departed the roadway to the right, and the front of V1 contacted a light pole on a traffic island. The pole then fell on top of the vehicle.
V1 was traveling south in lane 2 of a 2 lane divided roadway when the vehicle's front plane struck an animal (deer ) in the roadway.

Vehicles 4, 3, 2 and 1 were traveling west in lane 3 on a 3-lane grass median divided roadway with V1 in the lead when the front of V4 contacted the back plane of V3.  V3 then contacted the back plane of V2 with its frontal plane.  V2 then contacted the back plane of V1 with its frontal plane.

Vehicle #1 was travelling eastbound entering the intersection of a seven lane, non-positively divided roadway, Vehicle #2 was travelling westbound within the same intersection. Vehicle #2's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #1's frontal plane.
V1 was traveling west on a two lane two way roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left. The front of V1 contacted a creek bed.
V1 and V2 were traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling West on a two lane two way road. V1 departed roadway to the left striking an utility pole with front plane. V1 began to rotate in a counter clockwise rotation striking a row of mailboxes and its support post with it's front plane. V1 then contacted a hog wire fence with the front plane.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a four lane, two way road. Vehicle 2 was stopped at intersection on the same roadway. The front plane of V1 struck the back plane of V2.

V1 was traveling east (wrong way) on an interchange (one-way traffic) in lane 1 (of two lanes). V2 was traveling west on the same interchange in lane 1 (of two lanes). The front end of V1 contacted the front end of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a non-physically divided roadway (two-way traffic) in lane 2 (of four lanes).  V2 was traveling south on the same roadway in lane 1 (of four lanes).  V1 and V2 were brought to a stop for a posted sign.  V1 then turned to the right, and its right side came into contact with the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling from northeast to north, while making a left turn through an intersection from a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), and was in lane 3 (of three lanes).  V2 was traveling southwest through the same intersection from a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier), and was in lane 2 (of three lanes).  In the intersection, the right side of V1 came into contact with the front end of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling northbound in the number 2 lane of a 3 lane divided highway. V2 was slowing due to traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V2 rotated counter-clockwise, crossed lanes to the left where its front plane contacted a concrete barrier. V2 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and its back plane contacted the concrete barrier.

Vehicle 1 was entering the roadway from a private drive, making a left turn to head east. V2 was traveling west in the continuous left hand turn lane on a two-way, not physically divided seven lane roadway. Vehicle 1's left side and Vehicle 2's front made contact with each other.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling northbound in the right lane of a two way roadway, with two lanes of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, as V1 was making a left turn, the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the left side plane of V1. V1 then proceeded to yaw in the clockwise direction, and the rear right corner of V1 made contact with the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the right lane of a two way roadway with two lanes of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling northbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. At the above intersection, the frontal plane of V1 made contact with the right side plane of V2.

V1 was northbound in lane No.1 of an undivided, two-lane roadway and was approaching a three-leg (T-type) intersection. V1 traversed the adjoining roadway and its frontal plane impacted a concrete jersey barrier on the north roadside of the east/west roadway.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a 2 way roadway.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a 2-lane roadway.  V1 departed the road to the left and passed over a culvert, going airborne.  While airborne, V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise.  V1 came down and the front right of V1 dug into the turf.  V1 rolled end over end and rotated counter-clockwise with the most severe impact to the left back plane before coming to rest on its right side.  During the rollover, an unknown plane of V1 contacted a utility box.

V1 was traveling northwest on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  An animal entered the roadway from the eastern road edge contacting the frontal plane of V1.  V1 came to final rest on the roadway.
V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 lost control and exited the left road edge. The right side of V1 contacted a large rock, tree stump and an embankment.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane, non-positively divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left and it's left plane contacted a tree.

V1 and V2 were both traveling north on a 1 lane, one way interstate exit ramp roadway. V2 had stopped for a stop sign at the end of the roadway when it's back plane was contacted by the front plane of V1.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a 2 lane highway when a deer attempted to cross the roadway. V1's left side plane contacted the deer.
V1 and V2 were northbound on a three-lane roadway in the far right lane. V1 stopped due to traffic. The front of V2 collided with the rear of V1. V1 and V2 came to final rest at the point of impact.

V1 was traveling west in lane 2 of a two lane divided roadway when it came upon a ladder that was laying in lane 2 of the roadway. V1 then steered left on the roadway shoulder to return to the roadway. While steering left, V1 lost control and began to skid in a counter clockwise direction. The vehicle then departed the left side of the roadway, traveled down an embankment backwards, and struck a drainage culvert with the back plane of the vehicle before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling northeast on a 4 lane roadway in the number 4 lane, attempting to make a left-hand turn through an intersection. V2 was traveling southwest on a 4 lane roadway in the number 2 lane, crossing through an intersection. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling east approaching a three way intersection. V2 was traveling southbound approaching the same intersection. As both vehicles traveled through the intersection the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 was southbound in lane 1 of a 2 lane roadway. V1 was negotiating a slight curve to the left, when V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 rotated clockwise and impacted the side of a bridge with its frontal plane. V1 then returned to the roadway, crossing over both lanes of southbound travel, and impacted the bridge on the left side of the roadway with its frontal plane.  V1 rotated counter clockwise, where it struck the bridge with its back plane 2 times, then continued to rotate impacting its back plane. V1 came to final rest facing northbound in the number 2 southbound lane of travel.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, non divided, bidirectional roadway. V1 attempted to pass a commercial vehicle to the left. While V1 was in the left lane, it impacted a plastic barrel with its frontal plane. V1 then traveled off the right side of the roadway, where it rolled over 6 quarter turns before coming to final rest on its wheels facing north.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north bound. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway left side striking a utility pole with the front left corner. V1 rolled through a mailbox and completed 4 quarter turns coming to rest on its wheels in the middle of the southbound travel lane.

V2 was traveling south bound on a two lane roadway approaching a 4 way intersection. V1 was traveling west bound on the intersecting two lane roadway approaching the same intersection. As V1 and V2 entered the intersection, the right side of V1 was impacted by the front of V2.

V1 and V2 were traveling on a 2 lane non divided roadway in a easterly direction. V3 was traveling on the same roadway in a westerly direction. V2 stopped to wait for traffic to clear to make a left turn into a private driveway. V1's front contacted V2's back. V2 then crossed the lane line to the left. V2's left side contacted V3's left side.

V1 and V2 were in the first lane,traveling northeast on a one way, two lane, non-physically divided roadway. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2. V1 then departed lane to the right. The right of V1 impacted the guard rail and came to final rest in the shoulder facing northeast. V2 came to final rest in it's original lane facing north.

V1 was westbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway.  V2 was parked, facing west, on the same two-lane undivided roadway. The right front corner and right side of V1 impacted the left rear corner and left side of V2.
V1 was traveling south on a three lane roadway in lane three. V1 departed the roadway to the left and impacted a light pole in the median.

V2 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 2 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling northeast in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two way roadway. V1 had stopped to turn left at the intersection of the 2 lane divided roadway.  As V1 turned left to travel north on the 2 lane divided roadway, the vehicles left side plane was contacted by the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, non-divided roadway.  V2 was traveling north on a two-lane, non-divided intersecting roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the front of V1 contacted the right side of V2.  V1 came to rest on the roadway.  V2 continued in a northwest direction where it rotated counter-clockwise as it departed the left road edge and its right side contacted a ditch.

V2 was traveling south in lane one of a four-lane, two-way road. V1 was traveling east in lane one of a two-lane, two-way road approaching the travel lane of V2. The front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 was westbound in the first lane on a four-lane, non-physically divided roadway. V2 was westbound in the second lane on a four-lane, non-physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling east in the third lane on a two way physically divided roadway. V1 was traveling north in the second lane on a seven lane non-physically divided roadway. V1 was traveling south in the first lane on a 5 lane non-physically divided roadway. V1 departed roadway to the right.The front of V1 then impacted a utility pole and continued traveling on the sidewalk. V1 began to rotate counter clockwise and the RF tire contacted a parking block and then the front of V1 contacted the front left of V2. V1 came to final rest partially on the sidewalk and roadway, facing south.

V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, turning left at a four leg intersection. V1 came to rest in the intersection headed north west. V2 came to rest on the westbound shoulder, just west of the intersection, headed west.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the roadway on the left side. The front of V1 contacted a guardrail and caught fire.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 crossed through a T intersection traveling off the roadway, impacting a ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 continued forward traveling through a steel fence coming to final rest off the north side of the intersection facing north.

V1 and V2 were traveling on the same roadway in opposite directions. V1 was headed east crossed over the lane line to the left. V2 was headed west on the same roadway. V1's front contacted V2's left side. V1 then went off of the roadway and rolled over, coming to rest on its top.

V1 was traveling behind V2 north on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V1 departed the right side of the roadway contacting a mailbox with its frontal plane.  V1 then returned to the roadway and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.  V1 continued forward while yawing counterclockwise departing the right side of the roadway overturning three quarter turns to the right.  V1 came to final rest off of the roadway, and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection.  V1 departed the right lane line and contacted a utility pole with its frontal plane.  V1 came to final rest partially off of the roadway.
Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast when a deer entered the roadway. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted the deer.

V1 was traveling southwest on a 2-lane roadway, negotiating a left curve. The right tires of V1 departed the road edge to the right. V1 steered right, rotated clockwise then tripped and rolled left four quarter turns, fully ejecting the passenger and partially ejecting the driver before coming to final rest on its wheels.

V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east on a two-lane, two-way roadway approaching the same intersection.
