V2 departed the roadway on the right and the frontal plane impacted a tree, where it came to final rest. V1 rotated counter-clockwise and cam to rest in the southeast corner in the grassy area.
Vehicle 2 was traveling south into the intersection, Vehicle 1 was traveling west towards the same intersection. V1's front contacted vehicle 2's left front in the intersection.

V1 was traveling west approaching the intersection in the center turn lane. V2 was traveling East in lane 2 of 5 entering the intersection, V1 was attempting to turn left to head south in the same intersection. V2's front left corner contacted V1's front right corner.

V1 was traveling north in the second lane on a four lane, physically divided roadway negotiating a curve to its left. V1 traveled to its right and crossed lane one of northbound travel and departed the east road edge. V1 then re-entered the roadway in a right side leading yaw, crossing lanes one and two of northbound travel. V1 then departed the west road edge and the front of V1 contacted a barrier. V1 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest facing south near the barrier.

V1 was eastbound in the first lane on a two-lane, non-physically divided roadway. V1 attempted to turn left (north) and departed the northeast corner of the roadway. The right front corner of V1 impacted a concrete wall (Event 1). V1 then rotated counterclockwise, and its right side impacted a utility pole (Event 2). V1 came to final rest against the utility pole, facing northeast.
Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were traveling east bound in lane one. The front bumper of V1 contacted the back bumper of V2.

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a non-divided two way roadway.  V1 departed the right side of the roadway.  V1 impacted a mailbox with its left side and a rock with its right rear tire and rim.  V1 continued forward and impacted a 2nd rock with its left front tire, then a tree with the right front of the vehicle.  V1 then rotated clockwise, and rolled left, completing two quarter turns before coming to rest on the roof of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling west negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the road to the left and front left tire impacted a raised median curb. V1 then crossed all lanes of traffic to the left and the front of V1 impacted a guard rail.

V1 was traveling south approaching a 4 leg intersection. V2 was traveling east approaching the same intersection. V3 was stopped at the intersection facing north. Within the intersection the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1. After impact V1 rotated counter clockwise and the front of V1 impacted the front of V3.

V1 was negotiating a left curve while traveling south on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the left side of the roadway striking a ditch, a fence, and a tree. V1 came to rest heading southwest.
V2 was traveling south in lane one of a four-lane, two-way road. V1 was traveling in the same lane behind V2. The front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.
V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, two-way road that had a slight curve to the right. V1 departed the right side of the road and struck a utility pole with it's front plane.

V1 was traveling south, following a two way, two lane road. V1 began to enter the northbound travel lane. V1 then reentered its original travel lane and continued on to depart the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted a tree before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling north in the right lane, following a two-way, two lane road. V1 departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 contacted a pole. The right side of V1 contacted a support wire for the pole and an unknown part of the contacted pole or items attached to the pole contacted the left mirror and window of V1. V1 then returned to the roadway and crossed over both lanes of travel before coming to final rest on the west side of the road.
V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the west shoulder facing south.

V1 was traveling west in lane 1 of a 2 lane divided roadway passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling north in lane 1 of a 2 lane roadway passing through the same intersection. V3 and V4 were parked facing west on the north curb of a frontage road. The front of V1 impacted the right of V2. V1 and V2 rotated counterclockwise and both vehicle traveled off the roadway on the westbound side. The right tires of V1 tripped on the curb and V1 began to roll right. The right side of V1 impacted a metal hand rail and continued to rollover until it came to rest facing north on the frontage road. The right side of V2 impacted two stop signs positioned near each other. V2 started to roll over with the right side leading. As V2 was rolling over the right side of V2 impacted the back of V3. V2 rotated clockwise as it was rolling over V3. V2 landed on its wheels and slid sideways until the left side of V2 impacted a shrubbery and a tree where V2 came to rest. As V2 was rolling over the right front tire came off and rolled down the street where the tire impacted V4. After everything settled a small fire started in the engine compartment of V1.
V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane divided roadway. V1 departed the roadway at right and the frontal plane of V1 contacted two trees.

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V1 departed the roadway on the right side. The frontal plane of V1 impacted a wooden guard rail, where it came to final rest.

V1 was traveling eastbound in the single lane of a one way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 and V2 continued straight and the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side plane of V1.

Vehicle 1 was westbound on a two way, two lane roadway that curved left. Vehicle 1 departed the road to the right and the front plane of V1 contacted a reflector post. V1 began to travel down an embankment, and tripped into a right side leading rollover six quarter turns to the right.

Vehicle 1 was west bound on a two lane, two way roadway. Vehicle # 1 departed the roadway to the left. Vehicle # 1 struck a rocky embankment with its front plane and then rolled 8 quarter turns, right side leading.

V1 was traveling southwest, negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right and continued traveling off the roadway. The right plane of V1 contacted a tree. V1 came to final rest with the tree intruding into the vehicle.

Vehicles 1 and 2 were both traveling northeast negotiating a left curve with Vehicle 2 ahead of vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 attempted to pass vehicle 2 and lost control on the wet roadway. Vehicle 1 contacted the rear of Vehicle 2. Vehicle 1 then departed the left road edge and contacted a tree.

Vehicle 1 was northbound on a two-way gravel roadway.  Vehicle 1 was negotiating a curve to the left when it departed the left road edge, struck a dirt embankment and rolled two quarter turns coming to rest on its top in the roadway.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling southbound on the same roadway ahead of V1. V2 stopped and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.
V1 and V2 were both traveling on a 2 lane roadway. V2 was stopped at intersection and V1's front contacted V2's rear.
V3 was eastbound, stopped in traffic in lane one of a three lane, two way road. V2 stopped behind V3. V1 struck the rear of V2 who then struck the rear of V3.

Vehicle 1 was traveling eastbound on a 4 lane non physically divided roadway attempting to make a left turn at an intersection. V1 departed the northeast roadway apex and the front of V1 contacted a tree.
V1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway and approaching a four-leg intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling northeast on a two- lane, undivided roadway and approaching the same intersection. Vehicle #3 was northbound and was stopped at the south-leg of the intersection.Vehicle # 1 entered the intersection as its frontal plane contacted Vehicle #2's left side plane (Event  1). Vehicle #2 initiated a counterclockwise rotation and its right quarter-panel area impacted the front of Vehicle #3 (Event 2). Vehicle #2 continued forward into a ditch and initiated  a four-quarter turn roll-over sequence (Event 3), before coming to rest, off roadside.

V1 and V2 were traveling east in lane two of a five lane two way traffic. V1 was in lane two and V2 was in lane one. V1 changed lanes to its right and the right side of V1 contacted the left side of V1.
V1 was traveling west in lane 2 of a 2 lane divided interstate. The front plane of V1 impacted a deer, which continued over the hood and impacted the windshield and the windshield header.

V2 was traveling east in lane 1 of a 2 lane divided roadway. V1 was traveling west in lane 2 of the eastbound lanes of the same roadway (the same travel lane as V2).  The front of V1 contacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a 2 lane 2 way non-divided roadway. V1 departed the right side of roadway, returned to the roadway then departed left side of roadway striking an embankment and fallen tree with the front plane.

V1 was southbound on a two-lane roadway. V2 was westbound on an intersecting two-lane roadway. V2 came to stop at the stop sign at the intersection. V1 made a left turn onto the intersecting two-lane roadway. The front of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was east bound on a two way, two lane, non divided roadway. The roadway was wet and had loose gravel on it. V1 lost control on the roadway, and left the roadway to the right, where it impacted an embankment with its frontal plane and its right plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling southwest on a 2-lane, 2-way undivided roadway, negotiating a left curve.  V1 departed the roadway to the right in a clockwise yaw and the left side contacted barbwire fence and a 30cm diameter tree.  V1 then tripped and rolled left 2 quarter turns, coming to rest on its top plane.

V1 was traveling westbound in lane 3 of a 5-lane undivided roadway attempting to turn left at an intersection.  V2 was traveling eastbound in lane 2 of the same roadway attempting to crossover the same intersection.  In the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left of V2. Both vehicles came to rest within the intersection.

V1 was traveling west bound on a 2 lane road in lane 1 approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north bound on a 4 lane divided roadway in lane 1 approaching the same intersection. During the intersection the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling north in the #2 lane of a 5 lane undivided roadway. V1 departed the original travel lane to the left. V1 continued across the roadway and departed the road on the left. V1 traveled into a ditch where the front of V1 impacted the ditch embankment. V1 traveled to the top of the embankment where it rolled back down the embankment onto its roof and came to rest at the bottom of the ditch.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way roadway ahead of V1. V3 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way roadway ahead of V2. V3 then stopped attempting to turn left. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2 (Event 1). The frontal plane of V2 then contacted the rear plane of V3 (Event 2).

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in a single lane roadway. V1 and V2 crossed the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the right side plane of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound in a single lane, one-way roadway. V2 was traveling eastbound in a single lane, one-way roadway. Both vehicles approached the intersection at the same time. The frontal plane of V1 contacted the right rear tire of V2.

V1 was traveling northeast in the #2 lane of an undivided 4 lane road passing through an intersection. V2 was traveling north in the #1 lane of an undivided 2 lane road passing through an intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2. V2 traveled off the right side of the road onto an unpaved shoulder. V2 overturned and rolled until it came to rest on the passenger side of the vehicle.

V1 was traveling southbound in the number 2 lane of a 5 lane interstate. V2 was traveling southbound in the number 3 lane of a 5 lane interstate. V3 was traveling southbound in the number 4 lane of a 5 lane interstate. V4 was traveling southbound in the number 5 lane of a 5 lane interstate. V1 crossed over the left lane line into the number 3 lane where the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2. The force of this impact pushed V2 towards the number 4 lane into the path of V3. V3 started braking before an impact with V2 and lost control, spinning counter-clockwise into the number 5 lane facing the opposite direction. V4 attempted to brake and steer left to avoid a collision with V3 and the front of V3 was impacted by the front of V4. V4 continued to the left where the left side of V4 impacted a concrete divider.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northwest negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1 departed the right road edge and the RF wheel contacted a ditch. Vehicle 1 then contacted a tree with its front plane. Vehicle 1 then re-entered the roadway and rolled left, three quarter turns coming to rest on the passenger side.

V1 was traveling southeast attempting a left turn from a private driveway. The view of V1 was obstructed by a vehicle stopped in lane one of cross traffic. V2 was traveling southwest in lane two. The left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

Vehicle 2 was traveling east and vehicle 1 was traveling south. Both vehicles entered the intersection. Vehicle 2 made contact with  the rear passenger side of vehicle 1.  Vehicle 1 spun roughly 180 degrees clockwise coming to rest facing north.  As Vehicle 1 spun the front right corner made contact with the front right wheel of Vehicle 2.

Vehicle 1 was southbound and entered the intersection. Vehicle 2 was eastbound and entered the intersection.  The front of vehicle 1 made contact with the drivers side rear of vehicle 2, V2 then left the road way on the right side and struck a cable guy wire to a telephone pole.

V1 was traveling south on a tow-lane, non-divided roadway. V1 exited the roadway to the right, over corrected and re-entered the roadway, then exited the roadway to the left, over corrected and re-entered the roadway again to the right. Then V1 began to yaw in a clock-wise rotation. V1 then exited the roadway to the right, continuing to yaw, the front of V1 contacted the bottom of a ditch. V1 the rotated clockwise and rolled onto its left side impacting the ditch with its roof before falling back onto its wheels at final rest.

V1 was traveling west on a two lane, two way roadway.  A non-contact vehicle was eastbound on the same roadway when it lost control of the vehicle and crossed in front of V1.  V1 steered to the left to avoid the vehicle and departed the left road edge, striking a tree and coming to final rest in a treeline.

V1 was southbound on a two lane non-divided bidirectional roadway, negotiating a slight curve to the right. V1 left its lane to the left, left the roadway to the left, returned to the roadway, crossed both traffic lanes rotating clockwise, leaving the roadway to the right, where V1 impacted the embankment with its frontal plane. V1 continued to rotate clockwise, impacting a shrub and an embankment with its back plane. V1 then traveled up the ditch, where it impacted the embankment again with its frontal plane, and a mailbox post with its frontal plane before coming to final rest.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way, two lane highway, negotiating a curve. A non contact vehicle entered the westbound lane traveling eastbound in V1's lane of travel. V1 steered to the right, departing the roadway on the right side, striking a ditch with its front. V1 continued to travel off the roadway striking another portion of the same ditch with its front.
V1 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. The front of V1 impacted a deer causing damage. V1 came to final rest on the right side of the roadway facing south.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling west on the same roadway traveling behind V1.  An animal entered the roadway forcing V1 to stop suddenly.  The rear plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.  V1 and V2 both came to final rest on the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling south bound making a right hand turn within the intersection.  Vehicle 2 was traveling west bound, crossing straight through the intersection. The front of V1 made contact with the left side plane of Vehicle 1 in the intersection.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway. V1 ran off the roadway on the right side, where it struck a road sign and a utility pole with it's front plane before coming to final rest.

V1, V2, V3, and V4 were traveling southbound on a two-lane roadway. The front on V1 contacted the rear of V2 causing a chain reaction type crash where the front of V2 contacted the rear of V3 and the front of V3 contacted the rear of V4.
V1 was traveling west on a four lane physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling south attempting to cross the intersection to head east. The front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.

V1 was traveling south in Lane No.1 of a 6 lane divided interstate. V1 drifted to the left  as the left fender contacted the concrete barrier (Event 1). The left quarter-panel subsequently impacted the impacted the concrete barrier with its left quarter-panel (Event 2). The driver applied an aggressive left steering input as the left front impacted the concrete barrier again (Event 3). V1 rotated rapidly counterclockwise impacting the barrier with its right side (Event 4). V1 continued to turn counterclockwise coming to final rest against the concrete barrier facing south.
V1 was traveling west behind V2 on a five lane roadway.  V2 was slowing down and the front of V1 collided with the rear of V2. Both came to final rest close to the point of impact.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling northeast, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection going straight; V2 entered the intersection turning left. Within the intersection, the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a divided traffic way (median strip without positive barrier) in lane 3 (of three lanes) when it departed the roadway on the left.  The front end of V1 came into contact with an unknown object and V1 overturned (6 quarter turns, leading left).

V1 was traveling west on a six lane, divided roadway in lane five attempting to make a left turn at a light controlled four-legged intersection. V2 was traveling east on the same roadway attempting to go straight in the intersection. In the intersection the front of V2 contacted the right side of V1. V1 and V2 yawed slightly and the right rear of V1 contacted the left rear of V2 before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane two way roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the left at a high rate of speed where it crossed a private drive then launched over a culvert through a bush line and rolled end-over-end coming to rest on its roof.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane divided roadway, ahead of V1. Both V1 and V2 took a right onto an exit ramp to travel eastbound. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound in the third lane of a three lane two-way divided roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a three lane two-way divided roadway behind V1. V1 departed the third lane to the right into the second lane and the right side plane of V1 contacted the frontal plane of V2 (Event 1). V2 lost control and departed the second and third lanes to the left and then the roadway to the left. The left side plane of V2 contacted a guardrail face (Event 2). Both vehicles were able to regain control crossing all three lanes to the right and departing the roadway at right to enter the breakdown lane where they came to final rest facing west.
Vehicles #1 and #2 were traveling north, approaching an intersection. V2 stopped quickly at the intersection, and the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north bound approaching an intersection. Vehicle #2 was traveling west bound approaching an intersection. Both vehicles entered the intersection and the right of V1 contacted the front of V2. V2 then departed the road on the right side and contacted the front bumper on a utility pole.
Vehicle #1 and vehicle #2 were traveling west bound in lane one. The front of V1 contacted the back of V2.

Vehicle 1 was attempting to make a left hand turn to enter a private roadway. Vehicle 2 was traveling west in the number 1 lane on a two-way not physically divided roadway with a continuous left hand turn lane. Vehicle 1's right side and Vehicle 2's Front made contact with each other. Vehicle 1's final rest was located on the private roadway. Vehicle 2's final rest was on the northwest corner of the intersection.
V1 was traveling west on a three lane, two way roadway.  A deer entered the roadway and the front of V1 contacted the deer.

V1 was southbound on a four lane one way divided roadway in lane four. V1 traveled to its left and departed the east road edge. The left side of V1 contacted a concrete barrier with the front half of the vehicle then the rear half of the vehicle.
V1 and V2 were northbound on a two lane two way undivided roadway. V1 was behind V2. V2 stopped intending to turn left and V1 contacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane two way undivided roadway negotiating a curve to its right. V1 departed the east road edge and the front of V1 contacted eight trees along the east roadside. V1 then rolled one quarter turn onto its right side then came to rest.

Both vehicles were traveling south on a five lane divided roadway, approaching an intersection. V1 was traveling in lane two and V1 was in lane one, a right turn only lane. At the intersection, V1, a semi-truck with a trailer, attempted to turn right from lane two. The right side of V1's trailer unit impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling north on the Interstate in lane 1 (of three lanes) and was overtaking V2, which was ahead in the same lane, also traveling north.  V1 departed its lane to the left (partially) and continued traveling north in lanes 1 and and 2 (simultaneously).  The front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2's trailer, and V1 then overturned (8 quarter turns, leading left) on the roadway.
V1 was traveling north on the Interstate in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the left and overturned ( 7 quarter turns, leading left).

V1 was traveling southbound on a two-way, non-physically divided roadway in lane one (of two lanes). V1 departed the roadway on the right, contacting a curb. The right side of V1 then contacted two paddle markers before returning to the roadway. V1 rotated counterclockwise and overturned (6 quarter turns, leading right).
V1 was traveling south following a two-way, 2 lane road. A deer entered the roadway from the right. The deer impacted the right side of V1.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided road way. V1 exited the road way on the right side of the road contacting two small trees with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 on a 3-lane physically divided roadway.  V2 was traveling on the same roadway in lane 2.   V1 changed lanes to the left and the left side of V1 impacted the right side of V2.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise in front of V2 and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.  V1 continued to rotate counter-clockwise and the back of V1 contacted a concrete barrier.

V1 was traveling westbound on a major highway in lane 3. Due to a possible tire blowout V1 lost control and exited it's lane to the left. V1 then departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 impacted a concrete barrier. V1 rotated counter clockwise then rolled over right side leading 8 quarter turns.

V1 was north bound on a two lane non divided bidirectional roadway. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V2 then returned to the roadway, crossed both lanes of travel rotating counter clockwise, and departed the roadway to the left, where it impacted a road sign with its frontal plane. V1 traveled down an embankment, where it impacted a tree with its frontal plane. V1 then impacted a second tree with it's right plane, and impacted an unknown object with its undercarriage before coming to final rest.
V1 was westbound in lane 1 of a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. A deer entered the roadway striking the frontal plane of V1 causing damage. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing west.

Vehicle #1 was traveling northeast.  Vehicle #2 was traveling southeast on an intersecting roadway.  V1 began to turn left at the T-type intersection and the left of V1 contacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated clockwise and the left of V1 contacted the right of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east in lane 2.  Vehicle #2 was merging into lane 1 from an entrance ramp.   V1 began to change lanes to the right and the right of V1 contacted the left of V2.  V2 departed the road to the right and the right of V2 contacted a guardrail face.

V1 was traveling north approaching an intersection, following a two way, three lane road. V1 was in the second lane attempting to take a left at intersection. V2 was traveling south following a two way, two lane road approaching the same intersection. The right side of V1 impacted the front of V2.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way, three lane, undivided roadway. V1 traveled off the right side of the roadway. V1's undercarriage impacted an embankment. V1 continued traveling off the roadway and V1's RR tire then impacted a utility pole. V1 continued and began roll left side leading and came to rest on it's driver's side partially on the roadway and off the roadway.

V1 was traveling west in lane one of a two way, two lane, undivided roadway.  V2 was traveling east on the same roadway.  V1 departed the left lane line and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2.   V1 continued driving a short distance on the roadway before departing the right side (southern) road edge.  V2 then overturned two quarter turns right side leading before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a curve.  While negotiating the curve V1 departed the western road edge, returned to their initial travel lane, departed the center lane line, and then departed the eastern road edge.  V1 struck the embankment with their frontal plane before overturning two quarter turns.  V1 came to final rest partially off of the roadway.

V1 was traveling south in lane 1 of a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, negotiating a left hand curve. V1 went off the right road side striking a tree with its right plane and then a tree with its frontal plane. V1 came to final rest off the roadway heading south east.

V1 was westbound in lane 3 of a six lane, two way, undivided roadway, entering a four leg intersection. V2 was southbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, entering the same intersection. The front plane of V1 struck the left side plane of V2. V1 came to rest off of the south west corner of the intersection. V2 came to rest near the point of impact heading south west.

V1 was traveling east and departing a private two-lane driveway. The driver of V1 was attempting to traverse a three-lane adjoining roadway and continue easterly into another private driveway. V2 was an ambulance traveling northerly in lane 1 of the undivided three-lane roadway. The front of V2 impacted the left side plane of V1. The impact initiated V1 in a counter-clockwise rotation as it came to rest in the center turn lane, facing southwest. V2 was deflected off of the right roadside were it came to rest facing northeast and straddling the curb.

V1 was facing south in the #2 lane on a 3 lane roadway stopped at an intersection at a stop sign waiting to turn left. V2 was traveling west approaching the same intersection in the number 2 lane of a 4 lane roadway. As V1 waited for a heavy truck to turn left, V1 moved into the intersection and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.
Vehicle 1 and 2 were traveling west in the number 3 lane on a 3 lane two-way physically divided roadway. Vehicle 1's front and Vehicle 2's rear made contact with each other.

Vehicle 1, 2, and 3 were traveling east on a 7 lane two-way physically divided roadway in the number 3 lane. Vehicle 1's front and Vehicle 2's rear made contact with each other. Then Vehicle 2's front and Vehicle 3's rear made contact with each other.

V1 was traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 1 (of four lanes).  V2 was traveling west on the same roadway in lane 4.  V1 departed the travel lane to the right, over-corrected steering left, and entered into lane four.  The front end of V1 came into contact with the right side of V2.
V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling south, approaching the same intersection. Within the intersection, the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling west on a straight, downhill roadway. The driver tried to avoid a puddle of water on the roadway and steered to the left. Driver lost directional control of the vehicle and departed the roadway to the left. The left side of V1 impacted a guardrail (Event 1). V1 was partially on top of the guardrail and impacted a pole of the guard rail,  with its front (Event 2).  V1 rotated rapidly counterclockwise as the RF overrode the damaged guardrail (Event 3), coming to rest straddling the impacted guardrail.

V1 was traveling on a one way 4 lane highway. V1 was originally in  Lane 3 and then traveled over all lane lines to the right and struck a concrete barrier with its frontal plane (Event 1). V1 then climbed the barrier and the undercarriage slid on the top surface of the concrete barrier as the left side plane made contact with the roadway surface in a 1/4 turn rollover sequence (Event 2). After coming to rest, the vehicle was engulfed in a major fire (non-collision Event 3).

V1 was traveling eastbound on a non divided roadway. V1 traveled over the lane lines to the left and V1's LF tire struck a curb. V1 continued eastbound and struck another curb with LF tire. V1 then re-entered roadway and traveled across all lanes and left the roadway to the right. V1's front then contacted a post before coming to final rest.
V1 was following behind V2 on a 4 lane, two-way road, approaching an intersection. V2 stopped at a red light. The front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V2 was traveling south in lane 1 of a 4 lane physically divided roadway.  V1 was traveling west in lane 2 of a 6 lane non-physically divided roadway.  V3 was stopped facing east in lane 2 of a 5 lane non-physically roadway.  The front of V2 made contact with the front right side of V1 in the intersection.  V1 and V2 rotated and slapped together.  V1 continued traveling southwest through the intersection making contact with V3.  V1 and V3 sustained damage to the front ends.  V1 and V3 were towed from the scene.
V1 was traveling west on a physically divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 1 (of two lanes) when it caught fire and was then brought to a stop on an exit ramp.
V1 and V2 were both traveling north on a two lane, divided highway in lane one. V2 slowed due to traffic ahead, the front of V1 impacted the back of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a divided traffic way (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 2 (of two lanes) when it departed the roadway on the left. V1 then returned to the roadway, crossing lanes 2 and 1, before departing the roadway on the right where it contacted a guard rail. V1 then overturned (4 quarter turns, leading right). During the rollover, the left side of V1 contacted a large boulder, and then the front end of V1 contacted a fence before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling north through an intersection from a not physically divided roadway (two-way traffic), and was in lane 2 (of five lanes). V2 was making a left turn through the same intersection, traveling south to east from a not physically divided roadway (two-way traffic), and was in lane 3 (of five lanes). In the intersection, the front end of V1 contacted the front end of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway. V2 was traveling westbound in the single lane roadway. Both V1 and V2 entered the intersection at the same time. The left side plane of V1 was impacted by the frontal plane of V2.

V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a two lane divided roadway . V1 departed the roadway on the left side, where the frontal plane of V1 impacted the guardrail face. V1 began to rotate counterclockwise, and the right side plane of V1 impacted the guardrail face.

V1 was traveling westbound in the number 1 lane on an undivided 2 lane road. V2 was traveling northbound in the number 1 lane on an undivided 3 lane road. As V1 was making a left hand turn to travel south the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.

V1, V2, and V3 were traveling eastbound in the number 3 lane of a 3 lane road. V3 was stopped due to traffic ahead. V2 was decelerating due to traffic ahead. The front of V1 collided with the rear of V2. The force of this impact pushed the front of V2 into the rear of V3.

V1 was traveling west in the first lane of a three lane divided roadway. V2 was traveling west in the first lane of a three lane divided roadway ahead of V1. V2 Slowed down for traffic and the frontal plane of V1 contacted the rear plane of V2.

V1 was traveling south in the second lane of a four lane two-way undivided roadway. V2 was traveling south in the second lane of a four lane two-way undivided roadway behind V1. V1 slowed down for traffic and the frontal plane of V2 contacted the rear plane of V1 (Event 1). The right side of V1 then contacted the left side of V2 (Event 2) as they came to final rest.

V1 was traveling southbound in a single lane roadway. V2 was parked, not in transport, facing east. V1 made a left turn at the stop sign to travel eastbound. The frontal plane of V1 impacted the rear plane of V2.
V1 was traveling east on a two lane, two way roadway negotiating a curve to the right.  V1 departed the roadway to the left and the front of V1 contacted a utility pole.

V1 was heading east on a four lane two way roadway with a grass median. V1 began clockwise yaw and departed the roadway to the left. V1 then crossed over the grass median and west bound lanes. The front of V1 contacted a ditch north of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north, approaching an intersection and Vehicle 2 was traveling east, approaching the same intersection. V1 entered the intersection turning left; V2 entered the intersection going straight. Within the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.
Vehicle 1 was negotiating a right curve traveling west in the first of five lanes, approaching an exit ramp. V1 departed the road on the right side and the front of V1 contacted an impact attenuator.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound. V2 was parked on the north side of the roadway. V1 departed the lane and the roadway on the left side and contacted the wheel on a sewer cover. V1 proceeded east and contacted the front of the vehicle on a cable box. V1 proceeded east and contacted the left side on the front of V2. V1 then contacted the front on a fence post.

V1 was traveling north on an unmarked two-way roadway approaching a T-shaped intersection. As V1 was traveling north V1 lost control, departed the roadway on the left side where it struck a mailbox before it rolled over and came to final rest on a residential lawn.

V2 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane, undivided roadway; V3 was traveling westbound. The front of V3 contacted the front of V2. After the impact with V2, V3 experienced a fire. V1 was not involved in the contact between V3 and V2, but swerved onto the south road edge to avoid the crash and the front of V1 contacted a ditch.
V1 was traveling westbound. V2 was traveling eastbound attempting to make a left turn into a parking lot. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling north west on a two way, two lane undivided roadway approaching the same intersection. As V2 made a left turn at the intersection, the front plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V2. V1 and V2 came to final rest on the roadway.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way undivided roadway. V1 drifted into the opposite lane of travel and eventually off the left side of the roadway. The front plane of V1 contacted two utility poles and came to final rest off the roadway.

V1 was traveling northbound in lane one on a 2 lane roadway and V2 (Heavy Truck) was stopped due to traffic conditions in lane one. Then the front of V1 contacted the rear of V2. V1 was towed and occupant one was deceased at scene occupant two was transported.

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane non-physically divided roadway. The front of V1 made contact with a cow.  As the cow spun, an unknown part of the cow's body made contact with the right side of V1.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway approaching a 4 way intersection. Vehicle 2 was traveling east on the intersecting two lane undivided roadway approaching same intersection. As both vehicles entered the intersection, vehicle 1's front made contact with vehicle 2's front right side. After the initial impact, V1 rotated clockwise and V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the left side of V1 contacted the right side of V2.

V1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway negotiating a curve to its left. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The right side of V1 impacted a tree (event 1). V1 then rotated clockwise across a parking lot and the left side of V1 impacted a fence. V1 continued down an embankment where the back undercarriage contacted an embankment.  V1 came to final rest in a creek bed.

V1 was traveling west on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway. V1 veered to the right attempting to avoid an unknown vehicle encroaching into its lane. V1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 impacted a tree with its front end. V1 came to rest at point of impact facing west.

V1 was traveling west following a two way, two lane road. A deer entered the road from the right. Attempting to avoid the deer, V1 departed its travel lane to the left. V1 went on to depart the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted a tree before coming to final rest.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway striking a ditch with the frontal plane. V1 continued northwest striking a tree, utility pole, then a utility marker with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing northwest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling north and approaching an intersection attempted to stop. Vehicle 1 began sliding. Vehicle 2 was traveling west approaching same intersection. Vehicle 2 front made contact with vehicle 1 right rear quarter panel within the intersection.

V1 was traveling south on a straight roadway. V1 departed the road to the right and impacted a raised curb with its right front wheel. Driver lost correctional control of the vehicle and crossed all lanes of traffic to the left. V1 departed the roadway to the left and drove onto the raised median. The front of V1 impacted the pole of a traffic sign. V1 continued to drive on the median and impacted a tree with its front.

V1 and V2 were traveling east on a major highway. V1 changed multiple lanes attempting to access the exit ramp. The right side of V1 impacted the left side of V2 in a sideswipe manner. V1 and V2 then departed the roadway and impacted a guard rail with their front end planes. V1 then rotated clockwise across the highway and impacted a concrete barrier with it's left side. V2 rotated counter clockwise across the exit ramp and impacted a concrete barrier with it's back.

V1 was traveling east on a major highway when the right rear tire of V1 deflated.  V1 began to rotate counter clockwise, departed the road to the north, and rolled over 4 quarter turns coming to rest on its wheels on the grassy median of the highway.

V1 was north bound on a four lane, divided highway. There are two lanes north bound divided by a cable barrier and median and 2 lanes south bound. V1 was in the number 2 lane, when it left the roadway to the left, where the vehicle impacted the cable barrier with its frontal right and top plane. This impact caused the vehicle to rotate counter clockwise before coming to final rest facing south in the north bound lane of travel.

V1 was eastbound on a two way, two lane, non-divided highway. V2 was southbound on a two way, two lane, non-divided highway. V1 and V2 entered the intersection of the two roadways, and the front of V2 contacted the left side of V1. V1, continued in the same direction of travel, leaving the roadway off the right side, entering a ditch, and continuing into a field to final rest. V2 continued in the same direction of travel, losing control, leaving the roadway off the left side, and entering a ditch to final rest.

V1 was traveling southeast, in the second lane, on a five lane, two-way, physically divided roadway. V2 was traveling northeast in the second lane, on a four lane, non-physically divided roadway. Both vehicles entered the intersection. The front of V2 impacted with the right side of V1. V2 rotated clockwise, and came to final rest facing east in the intersection. V1 continued traveling and departed scene.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a 4 lane divided roadway in the number one lane. V1 departed the lane and continued to the right and departed the roadway. The front of V1 struck a roadside reflector.  V1 continued to drive on the shoulder and began to rotate in a counter-clockwise rotation as it traveled to its left and re-entered the roadway.. V1 departed the roadway again into the grass median. V1 traveled across the median while rotating counter-clockwise.  V1 then tripped on the westbound road edge where it rolled 4-quarter turns coming to rest on its wheels in the westbound #1 lane facing east.
Vehicle 1 was traveling NW when a horse entered the roadway from the right. Vehicle 1's front plane contacted the horse.

V1 was traveling in an easterly direction in the westbound travel lanes on a divided highway. V2 and V3 were traveling in a westerly direction on the same divided highway. V1 and V2 were in lane 2 and V1's front contacted V2's front. V1 then rotated counter clockwise on roadway.V3 was in lane 2 and V1's right side contacted V3's front. All vehicles came to rest off of the north side of the roadway.

V1 and V2 were traveling in opposite directions on the same 2 lane roadway. V1 was headed west bound when it departed the roadway to right, steered left, and began to rotate counterclockwise, entering into oncoming traffic. V2 was traveling east bound and V2's front contacted V1's right side. V1 rotated counterclockwise and its right side contacted the left side of V2.  V2 then rolled over, right side leading as it departed the roadway to the south. V1 also departed the roadway to the south and caught fire.  The fire spread to V2.

V1 was traveling south on a two way, two lane, undivided roadway negotiating a left hand curve.  V1 departed the western road edge, returned to the original lane of travel, departed the middle lane line and then the eastern road edge.  V1 overturned two quarter turns before coming to final rest off of the roadway.

Vehicle 1 was traveling northeast when it departed the right road edge. Vehicle 1 contacted a utility pole guy wire. Vehicle 1 then reentered the roadway and departed its travel lane to the left then departed the left road edge. The event with the guy wire snapped the utility pole causing the power lines to fall on Vehicle 1. Vehicle 1 then caught fire.

V1 was traveling east on a four lane two way roadway. V2 was traveling east in the first lane on the same two lane two way roadway. V1 attempted to change lanes and the front of V2 contacted the back of V1.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way roadway. V2 was traveling south on the same two lane two way roadway. V1 departed it's lane to the left and the front of V1 contacted the front of V2. V1 began a counterclockwise yaw and departed the roadway to the right. V1 then rolled two quarter turns and came to final rest off the roadway.
Vehicle #1 and vehicle #2 were traveling west, in lane 1, of a two way, four lane, undivided roadway. V2 slowed for traffic, and the front plane of V1 contacted the back plane of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north.  The front of V1 contacted an animal.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north.  V1 departed the road.  The front of V1 passed over a culvert, going airborne.  While airborne, the front of V1 contacted a tree.  V1 began to rotate counter-clockwise and rolled over 5 quarter-turns to the right.  During the rollover, the undercarriage of V2 contacted a stump and a tree.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two way, two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 1 departed the roadway to the right. V1 continued forward approximately 240 meters as it rolled to a stop in lane 3.  V2 continued forward, departed the left road edhe and contacted a breakaway post with its left side.  V2 then contacted a guardrail face with its front plane then again with its left side and came to rest in the grass median.

V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two lane, two-way roadway approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two lane two-way roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 was attempting to turn left after a non-contact vehicle was turning right. V2 went around the non-contact vehicle and the frontal plane of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was traveling west on a divided trafficway (median strip without positive barrier) and was in lane 1 (of two lanes) approaching V2, which was ahead in the same lane at a lower steady speed.  The front end of V1 came into contact with the back end of V2.  V1 then overturned (9 quarter turns, leading left).  During the rollover, Occupant 1 was totally ejected from V1, and V1 departed the roadway on the left.

V1, V2 and V3 were traveling south on a physically divided trafficway (median strip with positive barrier) in lane 3 (of six lanes), with V1 to the rear of V2 and V3 ahead of V2.  V3 was brought to a stop due to a stationary object in the roadway.  V2 was brought to a stop in response to V3.  V1 did not stop and its front end contacted the back end of V2.  V2 was propelled forward and its front end contacted the back end of V3.

V1 was traveling east in lane 1 (of five lanes) on a not physically divided roadway (with two-way left turn lane). V1 steered to the right (in a southerly direction) and onto an intersecting two-way, not physically divided roadway. V1 departed that roadway on the left and its front end contacted a curb and a utility pole.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling eastbound on the same roadway. V1 crossed the intersection and then departed its original travel lane on the left side. The left side plane of V1 made contact with the left side plane of V2.

V1 was northbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway. V1 departed the right side of the roadway, and then returned to the roadway before departing the travel lane to the left in a counter clockwise yaw. V1 tripped into a right side leading rollover (event 1).  The rollover was interrupted by a non-horizontal impact to the left side with a tree (event 2).  V1 rotated counter clockwise and rolled another quarter turn. coming to rest on its driver's side on the west roadside.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east, leaving a parking lot. Vehicle #2 was traveling south in a two-way left turn lane. Vehicle #3 was also traveling south. V1 entered the roadway and began to turn left. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2. After this impact, V1 rolled backwards slightly and the left plane of V1 contacted the left plane of V3.
Vehicle #1 was traveling NE in lane 1. Vehicle #2 was traveling NE in lane 2. V1 turned left at an intersection, and the left plane of V1 contacted the front plane of V2.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east towards an intersection.  Vehicle #2 was traveling west towards the same intersection. In the intersection, V2 began to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the right of V2.  V2 rotated counter-clockwise and the back of V2 contacted a pole.

V1 was traveling northbound on a two (2) lane roadway when V1 hydroplaned and departed the roadway to the right. V1 then continued into a drainage ditch area and the right rear tire loaded or impacted the ground causing significant damage to the tire/wheel (Event 1). V1 tripped and initiated a right side rollover sequence before careening off of a steep embankment. The frontal plane impacted the opposite side of the gulch before the vehicle came to rest on its roof and facing northwest.
V1 was attempting to make a left turn to head south exiting a parking lot. V2 was traveling north on a 5 lane two way roadway in lane 3. The front of V1 contacted the rear right side of V2.
V1 and V2 were headed westbound on a 3 lane non - physically divided roadway. V2 was stopped in the roadway waiting to turn left. V1's front contacted V2's rear.

V1, V2,and V3 were traveling south on a 7 lane undivided roadway in lane 2 with V3 leading.  V3 was stopped in traffic with V2 decelerating behind it.  V1 was behind V2 when the front of V1 impacted the rear of V2.  The front of V2 then impacted the rear of V3.  V1, V2, and V3 remained on the roadway at final rest.

V1 was traveling north on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway, following V2 in lane one. V2 slowed and turned left while V1 changed into the left lane proceeding straight. The front plane of V1 struck the left side plane of V2 causing damage.

V1 was headed west on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway in lane one. V1 went off the right side of the roadway striking a utility pole. V1 then rolled 1 quarter turn, left side leading, and came to rest on its left side near the point of impact, heading northwest.

V1 was traveling east approaching an intersection. V1 was following a two-way, three lane road, in the second lane of travel. The intersection was blocked by construction cones diverting the traffic to the left or the right. V1 drove through the cone barricade, and the front of V1 impacted a large hole in road.

V1 was traveling south, following a two lane, two lane road with a two way left turn lane in the middle. To avoid a non-contact bicycle, V1 departed its original travel lane the to left. V1 continued on the depart the roadway to the left. The front of V1 impacted the side of a building before coming to final rest.

Vehicle 1 was traveling southeast on an exit ramp. Vehicle 2 was traveling southwest on the adjoining roadway. Vehicle 1 crossed the travel lanes of Vehicle 2, intending to turn left. The front plane (corner) of Vehicle 2 struck the left plane (corner) of Vehicle 1. The front plane of Vehicle 1 then contacted the right plane of Vehicle 2 as Vehicle 2 continued southwest. Vehicle 1 came to rest on the roadway facing southeast. Vehicle 2 came to rest partially on roadway and on a grassy median facing southwest.

Vehicle 1 and Vehicle 2 were both traveling southwest negotiating a left curve. Vehicle 2 was ahead of Vehicle 1. Vehicle 2 was changing lanes to the left attempting a "U" turn. Vehicle 2's front plane contacted Vehicle 1's right plane.

V1 was westbound on a two lane, two way, undivided roadway approaching a 4-leg intersection. V2 was southbound on a two lane, two way, roadway approaching the same intersection. V1 came to a stop before traveling through the intersection. The front of V2 impacted the right side of V1 causing damage. Upon impact V1 spun counter clockwise traveling off the southwest side of the intersection impacting a ditch with the frontal plane causing damage. V1 came to final rest off the roadway facing southwest. After initial impact V2 traveled off the southwest side of the intersection impacting the ditch and traveling up a slight embankment coming to final rest off the roadway facing southwest.

V1 was traveling westbound on a two way roadway with a single lane of travel in each direction. V2 was traveling on the same roadway in the same direction behind V1. As V1 attempted to make a u-turn approaching an intersection, the frontal plane of V2 made contact with the left side plane of V1.

Vehicle 1 was southbound on a divided highway. Vehicle 2 and 3 were northbound on the same roadway. Vehicle 1 departed its lane to the left, crossed over the median, and entered oncoming traffic lanes. The front plane of V1 contacted the front plane of vehicle 2. Vehicle 3'* front plane contacted the back plane of vehicle 2.

Vehicle 1 was eastbound on a two way, two lane roadway. Vehicle # 1 departed the roadway to the right. The front plane of V1 contacted a fence. V1 crossed over another two way roadway and its front plane contacted a house, ramping up over concrete porch steps. V1 flipped over two quarter turns, and contacted the building a second time with its front plane and undercarriage/tires.

Vehicle #1 was traveling west.  V1 departed the road to the right and the front of V1 contacted a fire marker followed by a mailbox.  V1 entered the road and departed the road to the right again.  V1 began to rotate clockwise.  V1 tripped over 2 quarter-turns to the left.

V1 was traveling west on a six lane, two way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling east on a five lane two way roadway approaching the same intersection.  At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left and the front of V1 contacted the left side of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south, negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the road to the right and the front plane contacted an embankment. V1 rolled over one quarter turn to the left.

Vehicle #1 was traveling north. V1 suddenly steered left and departed the road to the left. The front plane of V1 contacted a boulder, and V1 ramped up and flipped over one quarter turn to the left. The left plane of V1 contacted a tree.

Vehicle #1 was traveling east bound. Vehicle #2 was parked in a private drive facing south bound. V1 departed the roadway on the right side and contacted the back right of V2. V1 then contacted its front on a house and then contacted its right side on the house.
V1 was traveling southeast in lane 1 of a 2 lane, two way roadway when the vehicles front plane struck an animal (deer) in the roadway.

Vehicle #1 was traveling eastbound and Vehicle #2 was traveling southbound on an intersecting roadway. As Vehicle #1 was making a left turn, Vehicle #1's frontal plane contacted Vehicle #2's frontal plane.

Vehicle #2 was traveling northbound on a four lane median divided roadway and was slowing for traffic. Vehicle #1 was traveling northbound on the same roadway and contacted the back plane of Vehicle #2 with its frontal plane.

V1 was traveling eastbound on a four-lane, undivided roadway approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic signal. V2 was traveling south on a five-lane, undivided roadway making a left turn at a light controlled four-legged intersection. V2 departed the roadway contact the curb with its right rear rim and also its left front rim before coming to rest.

V1 was traveling west. V2 was traveling north. V1 front plane contacted V2 right plane. V1 rotated clockwise while V2 rotated counterclockwise and the left front/mid of V1 contacted V2. V1 was traveling north on a two lane roadway negotiating a left curve. V1 departed the roadway to the right. The front of V1 impacted with a utility pole.

V1 and V2 were traveling north on a four lane interstate. V1 departed its initial travel lane to the left. V2 was decelerating for traffic ahead. The front of V1 impacted with the rear of V2. Both vehicles came to final rest on the roadway near the point of impact.

V1 was stopped at a traffic light facing west on a divided 7 lane traffic way.  V2 was traveling westbound on the same traffic way. V2 departed its travel lane to the right. The front of V2 impacted the left rear of V1. Both V1 and V2 came to final rest on the traffic way near the point of impact.
V1 was traveling east on a 2-lane roadway through an intersection.  V2 was traveling south on a 2-lane roadway through same intersection.  The front of V2 contacted the left side of V1.

V1 was eastbound exiting a private drive.  V2 was southbound in lane 2 of a 2-lane, non-physically divided highway.  V1 turned right out of the driveway, entering the roadway. V1 was traveling west, in the first lane, on a two lane non-physically divided roadway. V1 departed roadway to the right and impacted a utility pole with the right side. V1 continued traveling west, and departed the lane and the roadway on the left. V1 then impacted another utility pole with the front of the vehicle, where it came to final rest facing west.

V1 (heavy truck) V2 and V3 (heavy truck with double trailers) were all traveling Northbound on a 2 lane roadway in the number one lane. V3 slowed due to traffic conditions. V2 slowed as well. V1 was traveling northbound on a 3 lane roadway when V1 began to yaw and exited the roadway to the left. V1 was west bound on a two lane non divided, bidirectional roadway, when a deer entered V1's lane of travel. V1 impacted the animal with its frontal plane.

V1 was traveling south negotiating a left curve on a downhill dirt road. D1 fell asleep and woke up to the vehicle "fishtailing."  The vehicle started to slide sideways and tripping on the right side rolling 4 quarter turns amd coming to rest on its wheels off the roadway.
V1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway and V2 was traveling north in lane one of a five lane roadway.  As the vehicles entered the intersection, the front of V1 struck the right side of V2.

V2 and V3 were traveling westbound on a major highway. V1 was traveling in the same direction merging onto the highway. V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection. V2 was traveling west, approaching the same intersection. At the intersection V1 attempted to turn left into the northbound lanes. The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.

V1 was traveling northbound approaching a three leg intersection. At the intersection V1 turned left. V1 then departed the roadway to the right and the front of V1 impacted a concrete utility pole. V1 rotated clockwise and the back of V1 impacted a speed limit sign.

V1 was northbound on a two way, six lane, median divided, three lanes on each side interstate highway in lane 1. V1 departed the right side of the roadway. The right side plane impacted a guard rail.
